title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, creamed corn, vanilla and nutmeg.
Melt butter and mix it in.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top.
Cook 1 hour or until knife is clean at 325°.
Serve hot.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: chocolate chunk brownies
directions: Heat the oven to 350°.
Grease rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches.
In a medium mixing bowl, combine cocoa and baking soda; blend in 1/3 cup melted butter.
Add boiling water; stir until the mixture thickens.
Stir in the sugar, eggs and remaining 1/3 cup of melted butter; stir until smooth.
Add the flour, vanilla and salt; blend completely.
Stir in the nuts (if desired) and chocolate chunks.
Pour into a prepared pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until brownies begin to pull away from the sides of the pan.
Cool completely in the pan.
Cut into squares.
Makes about three dozen brownies.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into pie shells and bake at 375° about 50 minutes.
Yields approximately 3 pies.

title: orange zucchini cake
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg; set aside.
In large bowl, beat sugar, oil and eggs until well mixed.
Stir in cereal, peel and vanilla.
Add flour mixture, zucchini and nuts.
Mix well.
Spread evenly in greased baking dish.
Cool; spread with Orange Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: beef goulash
directions: Broil meat on rack about 5 to 10 minutes on each side until done.
Combine remaining ingredients, except noodles, into a heavy skillet.
Simmer, covered, for 2 hours until meat is tender.
Stir in noodles.
Divide equally into 2 portions.

title: chicken, rice and broccoli
directions: Cook bacon and put broccoli in and chicken in and put the rice in and put bacon and sausage in.
Put on the lid and boil it up. Pick the lid up and pick them out and put them on the plate and take a fork and spoon and eat them all up and drink a big glass of milk and a big glass of juice!

title: easy jelly biscuits
directions: Place biscuit dough on a cookie tray.
Take a knife and cut into each biscuit halfway through in the shape of a star.
Fill the middle with a spoonful of jelly.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°.

title: sassy franks
directions: In butter or margarine, saute celery and green pepper until tender.
Add all but franks.
Simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes. Add franks and cook in sauce until they swell.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Make French's spaghetti sauce according to directions.
Add next 7 ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce temperature and simmer for 3 hours.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on box.
Break cake into 1-inch chunks and layer bottom of punch bowl.
Sprinkle 1/3 box of pudding.
Make a layer of crushed pineapple, sliced bananas, strawberries (semi-drained), Cool Whip and nuts.
Repeat layers 3 or 4 times.
Add a cherry on top.
Assemble cake a couple hours before serving.

title: bar cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In 9 x 13-inch baking pan, melt butter in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs evenly over the melted butter.
Pour milk over crumbs.
Top with remaining ingredients.
Press down firmly. Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: ole country dinner
directions: Slice cabbage into thin strips.
Combine with rice in a large pot filled with water enough to cover cabbage and rice.
Cook until tender.
Brown hamburg with onion, draining off fat.
Put into pot with cabbage and rice.
Add soup base, salt and pepper.
Cook about an hour to get the flavor throughout all ingredients.
Makes about 4 quarts of dinner but can be decreased by the size of cabbage. Use your own judgment.
Serve with hot homemade bread.
You can also add other spices such as garlic if you like.

title: chocolate covered cherry cookies(makes about 40 to 48 cookies)
directions: In large bowl, stir together flour, cocoa, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
In mixer, beat together butter and sugar on low speed until fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla; beat well.
Gradually add dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Beat until well blended.

title: chicken divine
directions: Cook broccoli slightly in little salted water.
Drain; debone chicken and cut up into bite size pieces.
Put broccoli in layer in buttered casserole.
Put layer of chicken over broccoli.
Mix a sauce of soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Cover the chicken and broccoli with sauce.
Top with grated cheese. Sprinkle with bread crumbs and paprika.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Beat sugar and shortening until smooth; add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Mix flour, salt and cocoa together; add to mixture.
Add milk, coloring and vanilla; mix well.
Add soda on top of batter; pour vinegar on soda and mix with fork.
Divide batter in 2 cake pans that have been greased and floured.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Ice with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Roll chicken breasts in Parmesan cheese until coated.
Sprinkle with salts.
Spray baking dish with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: pat's secret barbecued spareribs
directions: Mix well.
May be stored in airtight container in refrigerator for up to 2 weeks.

title: tarts
directions: Beat together cream cheese, vanilla, sugar and eggs until smooth, 5 to 8 minutes.
Put cupcake liners in a muffin tin. Place vanilla wafers in bottom.
Fill 1/2 full with batter.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Batter will rise almost to the top, it will go back down.
Put cherry pie filling on top of cooked batter and refrigerate.

title: marshmallows
directions: Lightly butter a 9-inch square pan.
Set aside.
In a small bowl, combine gelatin and cold water.
Stir with a spoon until very thick.
Allow to stand 5 minutes.
In a 2-quart saucepan, combine hot water, 1/2 cup corn syrup and 2 cups granulated sugar.
Place over high heat and stir with a wooden spoon until mixture comes to a boil.
Cook to 238° or 115°C or soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Stir in remaining 1/4 cup corn syrup.
Pour into medium size bowl.
Using an electric mixer at high speed; beat hot syrup and gelatin mixture 1 tablespoon at a time.
Continue beating until gelatin is incorporated, candy is thick and has cooled to lukewarm, about 10 minutes.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour into a greased pan.
Cool 3 hours or until marshmallows are firm enough to cut, using a knife dipped in hot water.
Cut marshmallows into pieces 1 3/4 inches square.
Roll cut marshmallows in powdered sugar to prevent sticking.

title: union station chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
In separate bowl mix flour, oats, salt and baking powder.
Mix creamed and dry ingredients together.
Add chips, melted chocolate and nuts. Place dough on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for approximately 8 minutes.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: stromboli
directions: Thaw bread and let rise.
Roll thin.
Mix next 6 ingredients together and spread on dough.
Add remaining ingredients.
Arrange in center of dough; roll like jelly roll with seam side down. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with pizza sauce.

title: pork chops 'n' rice
directions: Spread rice in bottom of Pam sprayed 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook pork chops in oil to brown on each side.
Lay on top of rice. Saute onion in the same pan the pork chops were browned in.

title: onion casserole
directions: Peel and slice onions.
Place in a shallow greased 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Place a layer of Swiss cheese over the onions.
Layer onions and Swiss cheese only once.
Combine in a large bowl the flour, milk, salt and Tabasco sauce.
Beat until smooth.
Add eggs; beat again.
Pour over the onions and cheese.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: tuna casserole
directions: In a large casserole pan, sprayed with Pam, mix macaroni, tuna (leave in chunks), diluted soups, salt and pepper and pimento. Decorate top with potato chips and heat in oven.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Serves 8.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Pour soup over meat after placing in casserole dish.
Cover with Tater Tots and bake at 350° until Tater Tots are done.

title: homemade chicken soup
directions: Put the chicken, carrots, celery, onion, garlic powder and parsley in a large pot.
Cover with water.
Bring to a rapid boil and then reduce heat to medium-high. Boil until the meat falls off the bones. Remove the bones and skin from the soup. Bring to a boil again.
Add pasta and cook for 10 minutes. Enjoy!

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Arrange frozen hash browns in a 9 x 13 pan (thaw slightly). Mix remaining ingredients well and pour over potatoes.

title: chicken fried steak
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients; sprinkle on both sides of steak.
Combine egg and 2 tablespoons milk in a shallow dish.
Dip steaks in egg mixture.
Pour oil to depth of 1/2 inch into a large, heavy skillet.
Fry steaks in hot oil over medium heat until browned, turning once.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer, turning occasionally, for 15 minutes, or until tender.
Remove steaks and drain on paper towels.
Keep warm.

title: crescent cream bars
directions: Put 1 package rolls in bottom of 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Beat softened cream cheese with 1 cup sugar, vanilla and egg yolk. Spread mixture over rolls. Layer second package of rolls on cheese mixture.
Beat egg white only until foamy.
Mix in 1/4 cup sugar.
Brush over rolls.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and nuts.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: baked kraut
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in 325° oven for 7 hours.
Stir several times.
Mash tomatoes so there won't be any lumps.

title: corn casserole
directions: Prepare rice according to package directions.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour mix into prepared yellow rice.
Pour into a greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: In medium bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in lemon juice.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill to blend flavors.
Serve with tortilla or potato chips.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Place cooked broccoli in baking dish.
Mix soup and milk until smooth.
Pour over broccoli.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese. Pour Bisquick over top.
Pour melted butter over Bisquick.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Place Parmesan cheese, olive oil and red pepper flakes in a large bowl.
Add potatoes and toss until well coated.
Arrange in a single layer on a baking sheet with sides.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour, turning the potatoes after 30 minutes (using a spatula will help keep the coating from tearing off).
Remove from oven when golden brown; sprinkle with basil.
Serve hot.
Makes 4 servings. Serve with French Prime Rib.

title: alpine chicken
directions: Mix well and bake in covered casserole dish at 350° for 45 minutes.
This dish freezes very well.
You can freeze half and bake half.

title: cereal and nut cookies
directions: Mix ingredients in order listed.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten slightly.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes in 350° oven.

title: "delicious" jello
directions: Pour prepared Jell-O in 9 x 13-inch pan and allow to set until firm.
Add a layer of your choice of the fruits over the Jell-O. Next, spread the prepared pudding over the fruit.
Cover this with the whipped topping.
Garnish with coconut or toasted coconut. Red or green maraschino cherries may be added.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Cream together peanut butter, margarine, vanilla and powdered sugar.
Add graham cracker crumbs and mix well.
Shape into small balls.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin wax.
Dip balls in chocolate and place on waxed paper.

title: quick lasagna
directions: Generously grease a 3-quart casserole or baking dish.
Cook noodles as package directs for al dente.
Drain the noodles and toss them with the salad oil.
Set aside.

title: pecan-pecan pie
directions: Can add 1/2 teaspoon of liquid Braggs amino acids.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Cream margarine and peanut butter in medium bowl until light. Add confectioners sugar gradually, mixing well after each addition.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place balls on waxed paper-lined tray.
Melt paraffin and chocolate chips in heavy saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly.
Insert toothpick into each peanut butter ball; dip into chocolate mixture.
Place on waxed paper-lined tray.
Let stand until set.
Store in airtight container.
Paraffin measurement assumes paraffin to have 4 blocks in box.
May add chopped pecans to peanut butter mixture or place pecan over hole made by toothpick.
Yield: 80 servings.

title: applesauce muffins
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Blend egg, milk and oil in a bowl.
Sift all dry ingredients together.
Gradually add to liquid mixture until dry ingredients are moistened.
Grease muffin cups or use paper cups.
Drop teaspoon of batter in each cup, then drop teaspoon of applesauce on each one.
Then fill 3/4 full with more batter.
Bake about 25 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: blond brownies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread evenly.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: aunt eva's bread
directions: Whole Wheat Variation:
Use 3 cups flour and 3 cups whole wheat flour.

title: no crust coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a pie pan.
It makes its own crust.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: grandma's french toast
directions: Beat all of the ingredients except cinnamon together.
Soak slices of bread well in mixture; place in heated skillet, sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Fry until golden brown on each side.
Use fresh bread.
(If dry bread is used, add 1/2 cup more milk.)

title: peas oriental
directions: Cook peas per box instructions.
Reserve the liquid. Mix peas and next 3 ingredients.
Spread 1/2 of this mixture in a casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese and dot with oleo.
Spread rest of pea mixture on top and top with remaining cheese and oleo.
Top with onion rings.
Bake at 350° until cheese bubbles.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Melt butter.
Crumble in Blue cheese and continue to melt. Remove from stove. Beat in enough milk to desired consistency. Add spices and combine with mayonnaise last.
Stores for no more than 48 hours.

title: jambalaya
directions: Brown sausage, onion, garlic, celery and bell pepper together; drain well.
Mix with broth from chicken; simmer for 30 minutes.
Add rice and chicken; cook until rice is tender.	Serve hot.

title: country vegetable soup
directions: In large heavy bottom pot, heat oil.
Saute celery, carrot, garlic and onion over medium heat until tender (about 15 minutes). Add beans.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 1 hour.
May serve sprinkled with Parmesan cheese.
Serves 6.

title: hawaiian delight ice cream
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, milk and vanilla.
Stir in other ingredients. Fill ice cream freezer the rest of the way with milk.

title: layered nacho dip
directions: Mix beans and seasoning mix.
Spread in a 12 x 8-inch dish. Layer other ingredients in order listed.
Chill.
Serve with crackers or nachos.

title: milk gravy
directions: Heat shortening; add flour and stir until smooth.
Continue stirring while adding milk, salt and sugar.
Boil until desired thickness.
Pour over bread slices.

title: fruit cake bars
directions: Stir flour and baking soda; add other ingredients.
Pour in jelly roll pan.
Bake at 300° for 40 to 45 minutes until toothpick comes out clean.

title: fruit soup
directions: In a large saucepan, combine prunes, raisins, dried apples and water.
Set aside for 8 hours or overnight.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring mixture to boil over medium heat.
Reduce heat.
Simmer 1 hour.
Discard cinnamon sticks before serving. Serve hot or cold.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: tropical lemon bars(yields 12 bars; pan size: 8 x 8-inch)
directions: Place butter in glass baking dish.
Microwave on High for 45 seconds to 1 minute or until butter is melted.
Stir in cookie crumbs and lemon rind.
Reserve 1/4 cup mixture.
Press remaining mixture evenly in glass baking dish.
Beat sweetened condensed milk and lemon juice in bowl until smooth.
Spread over crumb mixture.
Sprinkle with reserved crumbs.
Microwave on Medium-high for 10 to 12 minutes, turning dish 1/2 turn after 5 minutes.
Let stand until cool.
Cut into bars.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and oil.
Add sugar and cream together.
Add eggs one at a time.
Cream together and add flour alternately with milk; add vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake longer in a tube pan.

title: boxty(irish potato pancakes)
directions: Peel the raw potatoes and coarsely grate them onto a clean cloth.
Wring the cloth to extract as much moisture from the potatoes as possible.
Put the grated potato in a large mixing bowl.
Add the mashed potatoes and beat in the eggs with a wooden spoon.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook and drain noodles to package directions.
Brown ground beef and drain off fat.
Pour a little of the Prego sauce on the bottom of two 13 x 9-inch pans.
Layer the noodles, sauce, ground beef and cheese in that order.
Top the casserole with remaining sauce.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: quick hot rolls!
directions: Scald
milk.
Stir
in sugar, salt and butter.	Cool to lukewarm.
Measure	warm
water
to
large	bowl.
Sprinkle in yeast.
Stir
until dissolved.
Add lukewarm milk mixture, egg and 2 cups flour; beat until smooth.
Stir in enough remaining flour to	make
soft dough.
Cover and let rise in warm place until double in bulk (30 minutes).

title: impossible pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender and blend for about 1 minute.
Pour into large buttered pie pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix together.
May be served as salad or dessert.

title: chicken enchilada
directions: Place tortillas in boiling water, one at a time for 1 second before filling.
Fill each tortilla with 1/4 cup of chicken. Sprinkle 2 tablespoons of cheese and 1 tablespoon of onion.
Roll tortilla and place seam down in baking dish sprayed with Pam.

title: cheese spread
directions: Cook over medium heat until thick.
Stir in 1/2 lb. velveeta cheese, cubed.
When melted, add 3 Tbsp. minced onion or bacon bits.
Pour into serving dish.
DO NOT substitute other cheeses for Velveeta, as they do not get smooth and creamy.

title: gazpacho salad(4 to 6 servings)
directions: Soften the gelatin in 1/4 cup of the tomato juice for about 5 minutes.
Meanwhile, heat 1 cup of tomato juice; add the gelatin and stir until thoroughly dissolved.
Chop the fresh tomato, saving the juice; add vinegar and remaining tomato juice to make 1/2 cup liquid.
Add to the hot mixture with the garlic, cucumber, green chili, onion, salt and pepper.
Pour into a 1-quart mold.
Chill until firm.
Unmold on bed of crisp greens.

title: lela's praline cookies
directions: Line a cookie sheet with graham crackers.
Melt together brown sugar and margarine.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly and boil 2 minutes.
Add pecans.
Pour over graham crackers.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cut nearly as possible on sections of crackers.

title: sweet and sour vegetable salad
directions: Mix together sugar, salt, pepper, celery seed, vinegar and oil. Bring to a boil. Pour hot mixture over drained vegetables and marinate 24 hours before serving.

title: quail casserole
directions: In an earthenware or heavy pot, arrange half of the eggplant, potatoes, garlic, pepper and onion.
Add the quail, and then arrange the second half of the vegetables on top of them, with the bay leaf, parsley, pepper, wine and cover all with tomatoes.
Add a little water, cover and cook over low to moderate heat until quail is tender.
Serves 8.

title: apple pecan sheet cake
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt together. Combine oil, sugar and eggs in mixer bowl. Beat until thick and lemon-colored. Add dry ingredients at low speed until smooth. Stir in apples, pecans, cinnamon and vanilla. Spoon into greased 11 x 14 sheet cake pan. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes. Cool on wire rack.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown hamburger, onions and pepper.
Drain and set aside. Pour pork and beans in a large baking dish.
Add hamburger mixture, brown sugar, molasses, barbecue sauce and bacon bits to pork and beans.
Place in oven heated to 350°.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour, or until mixture is bubbling.

title: cherry vanilla punch
directions: Beat ice cream and gelatin with a mixer or a blender until smooth.
Add 2 cups milk.
Beat just until foamy.
Add remaining milk.
Serve at once.
Makes 6 servings (8 ounces each).

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Put sugar, milk, cocoa and butter in saucepan on medium heat. Cool 1 minute.
Add salt and vanilla.
Mix peanut butter and oats together and add to first mixture.
Spread on foil by tablespoons.

title: kay's salsa
directions: Put all ingredients in blender or food processor, adding onions and peppers first.
Flash blend just briefly until peppers and onions are well chopped and combined with tomatoes.
Salsa will be soupy.
Chill 30 minutes to 1 hour until thickened.
Serve with chips, tacos, baked potatoes, etc.

title: chili with rice
directions: Cook and stir meat, pepper and seasonings.
Mix in large skillet on medium-high heat until meat is browned.
Stir in water, beans and tomato sauce.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in corn. Return to boil.
Stir in rice; cover.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir.
Serve with shredded cheese, chopped onion, sour cream and salsa.
Makes 6 servings.

title: rice pudding(low-fat)
directions: Combine rice, water, 1 1/2 cups skim milk, sugar and salt in saucepan.
Bring to a boil while stirring constantly.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer about 25 minutes or until rice is tender. Combine remaining skim milk, egg substitute and vanilla; beat slightly.
Add to cooked rice and continue cooking over low heat until thick and creamy (about 10 minutes more).
Fold in raisins. Spoon into dessert dishes and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken what-the-hell
directions: Arrange chicken in pan; sprinkle with mint, rosemary, salt and pepper.
Now pour wine, Worcestershire, honey and oil mixture around chicken; add mushrooms to top of chicken and pecans final layer.
Cover with foil; bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: kleeman's apple pie
directions: Stir flour into melted butter.
Add nutmeg, orange juice and sugar and mix.
Put chopped apples in unbaked pastry shell.
Pour above mixture over them and top with strips of pastry or full top which has several vents cut into it.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 300° and bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Press coconut and pecans into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Add cake mix.
Mix sugar, cream cheese and oleo well.
Spoon this over the cake mixture.

title: coconut-cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and cream cheese; gradually add sugar, beating at medium speed of an electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.

title: best ever chili
directions: In Dutch oven, cook meat until brown.
Add chopped onion, green pepper and celery; simmer slowly.
Add beans, tomatoes, tomato paste and spices.
Simmer slowly for 1 1/2 hours.
Freezes well.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: In a Dutch oven cook salt pork or bacon over medium heat until fat has been rendered. With a slotted spoon remove the bits of pork and reserve. Add the onion and cook, stirring frequently until onion is transparent (about 5 minutes). Add potatoes, clam broth, salt and pepper. Simmer until potatoes are tender but not mushy (about 15 minutes). Add clams and simmer for 5 minutes. Add milk, butter and reserved pork pieces. Heat, but do not allow to boil after milk has been added. Adjust seasoning as required.

title: dan's pickled pigs feet
directions: Scrub feet thoroughly; singe if necessary.
Cover with cold water.
Add vinegar and heat to boiling.
Skim.
Add seasonings and simmer 2 hours.
Cool in liquid and serve cold.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix cake mix, pudding mix and poppy seed well.
Add eggs, oil and water.
Blend together.
Bake in angel food cake pan, greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
When done, sprinkle with powdered sugar while warm.

title: orange delight
directions: Mix jello and boiling water and allow to thicken slightly. Cream the sugar and cream cheese.
Add the whipping cream and beat until fluffy.
Add thickened jello.
Beat until well blended. Stir in nuts and pineapple.
Pour into mold.
Chill 2 hours or overnight.

title: banana punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in hot water.
Let cool.
Mix and freeze together with all ingredients except ginger ale.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Beat eggs. Add sugar, oil and vinegar.
Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Add flour and milk to mixture.
Add vanilla and food coloring.
Bake for 30 minutes at 300° to 350°. Makes 3 layers or sheet.

title: glazed lemon squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix 1 cup baking mix and the powdered sugar.
Cut in margarine.
Press in ungreased square pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inch.
Bake until light brown, about 10 minutes.

title: england pound cake
directions: Cream the soft margarine and sugar together until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla and then add flour.
Pour in tube pan or Bundt pan and bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes. Reduce heat to 325° until done.
This makes a good, heavy pound cake.

title: renee's a-doe-bow
directions: Mix water and soy sauce in skillet or stir-fry skillet.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook on medium heat about 10 to 15 minutes. Serve over cooked Minute rice (follow instructions on box), green beans, cooked cabbage and carrots.
Low in calories.

title: bruschetta
directions: Mash the garlic cloves in a bowl big enough to hold tomatoes. (I use the garlic press, then mash them.)
Squeeze or pour lemon juice.
Sprinkle liberally with salt and mix well.
Add about 2 tablespoons olive oil and a dash of Italian dressing if you like. Add tomatoes and toss.
Add more oil or dressing if the tomatoes aren't thinly coated.
Add basil, about 15 leaves.
Chill.
Toast the bread and serve with extra virgin olive oil and the tomato mix. If you want to toast the tomatoes already spread on the bread, DO NOT add basil until you remove it from the oven.

title: fruit salad dish
directions: Mix all ingredients; spread the rest of the Cool Whip on top. Refrigerate.

title: heavenly pastrami original pastrami sandwich
directions: Open the bun up and lay on a cookie sheet.
Put the crab (munch up the crab for a better spread) on next.
Top with Swiss cheese. Bake it in the oven until it is good and hot.
You can tell its doneness when the cheese is melted and the bun is toasty.

title: frozen sweet pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and onions very thin. Sprinkle salt over them and let stand for 2 hours. Boil sugar and vinegar until sugar dissolves. Let cool. Drain cucumbers and onions. Add celery seeds and mix together. Put this mixture in 1 pint freezer containers. (This will be approximately 2 containers.) After sugar and vinegar mixture is cooled, pour over cucumbers. Seal containers and freeze.

title: speedy bread sticks
directions: Cut each biscuit in half.
Roll into pencil shape, about 4 to 6-inches long.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet; brush with beaten egg white.
Sprinkle with salt.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes until golden brown.
Makes 20 bread sticks.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix with spoon.
Cut apples into slices and put in salt water to keep from discoloring.
You may also use other fruit.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix and pour into graham cracker crusts.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Makes 2 pies.

title: mock plum pudding
directions: Chop fine the nuts, prunes, raisins and Grape-Nuts.
Mix jello and boiling water.
While mixture is hot, put in all the other ingredients.
Mix gently.
Refrigerate until set.
Serve with whipped cream.
This is rich and delicious.

title: seafood stew
directions: In 5 to 6-quart slow cooker, combine onions, celery, garlic, tomatoes, clam juice, tomato paste, water, vinegar, oil, Italian seasoning, sugar, pepper flakes and bay leaf; mix well.

title: sweet potato rolls
directions: Pare yam and cut in several pieces.
Add enough water to cover and cook until tender.
Drain, saving 1/4 cup of water in which yam was cooked.
Cool yam-water to lukewarm and dissolve the yeast in it.
Mash yam; then beat in salt, sugar and butter vigorously. Heat milk until a film shines on top; skim.
Stir into yam mixture and cool to lukewarm.
When right temperature has been reached, add the softened yeast.
Stir in flour, a cupful at a time, until dough is thick enough to knead.
Lift onto a floured board and knead until smooth and elastic.
Place in a greased bowl.
Cover with a tea towel and let rise in a warm place until double in size.
Bake in preheated oven at 425° for 13 to 15 minutes.

title: italian love cake
directions: Mix fudge marble cake as directed on package.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
In separate bowl, mix Ricotta cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla well.
Spoon cheese mixture on top of unbaked cake.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove from oven and cool.
Frost with following recipe:

title: mexican chicken
directions: Layer chicken breasts (that have been torn apart).
Next, layer onions, bell peppers, cubed cheese and 3/4 crushed chips. Then layer mushroom soup, chicken soup, Ro-Tel and broth.
Put rest of chips over all.
Cook 30 minutes at 350°.

title: grandma martha's egg custard
directions: Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, then at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: apricot jello salad
directions: * Freeze milk until crystallized.

title: cherry chip brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine pie filling, cake mix, eggs and almond extract in large bowl.
Mix until well blended.
Spread mixture into a lightly greased and floured 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until done. Cool.
Combine sugar, milk and margarine in small saucepan.
Mix well.
Bring to a boil and boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat, add chocolate chips.
Stir until melted.
Spread over cooled brownies. Cool completely and cut into bars.

title: easy onion bread(bread machine)
directions: Put all the ingredients in the inner pan in order for your machine. Select bread setting, medium setting (I thought it came out a little well done and will put it on light next time), and press start.

title: norwich relish
directions: * Measured before sliced thin.

title: dill dip
directions: Blend and use with cauliflower, carrots, tomatoes, green peppers and broccoli.

title: cheese nibbles
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend cheese and margarine with mixer until creamy.
Stir in flour and baking powder, kneading until a stiff dough forms.
Knead in caraway seed.
Roll dough into large marble sized balls.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet and flatten slightly with a fork.
Sprinkle with salt.
Bake about 15 minutes until pale golden.
Serve hot or at room temperature. Makes 40.
Store airtight or freeze unbaked, thawing to bake as directed.

title: lemon-sesame asparagus
directions: Wash and trim asparagus.
Bring water and chicken broth to a boil.
Add asparagus and cook covered 10 to 15 minutes until crisp tender.
In small pan, heat and stir margarine, garlic powder and sesame seeds over low heat for 5 minutes or until seeds are golden brown.
Add lemon juice and salt.
Drain asparagus and pour lemon mixture over hot asparagus and serve immediately.

title: rhubarb custard pie(sugar-free)
directions: Mix crust and press into a 9-inch greased pie pan.

title: congo bars
directions: Mix all of the ingredients with hands.
Spread in ungreased pan (9 1/2 x 13-inch) and bake for 1/2 hour or until edges are brown.
Cool 10 minutes before cutting into bars.
Makes 12 good sized bars.

title: prune cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Stir all others in order given.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for about 40 minutes.
While cake is baking, make glaze.

title: pink punch
directions: Combine all ingredients except ginger ale.
Add ginger ale just prior to serving.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add taco seasoning, water and kidney beans.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
When ready to serve, combine all ingredients with meat mixture in large bowl.
Toss well.

title: chicken and noodles
directions: Brown the cubed chicken pieces and onion in oil.
Add seasoning to taste.
Add soup, gravy and mushrooms to chicken.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Serve over noodles.

title: brown beef in beer
directions: Brown beef in butter.
Add beer, basil, salt and pepper. Cover and simmer 45 minutes.
Stir in gravy.
Mix and cook 5 to 7 minutes.
Serve with hot, cooked egg noodles.

title: creamy hash brown casserole
directions: In a large bowl, combine hash browns with cheese, soup, sour cream and onion.
Spread in 9 x 13 baking dish that has been sprayed with Pam.
Combine crushed cornflakes with melted margarine.
Spread on top.
Sprinkle with savory and paprika. Bake uncovered in 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes or until bubbly.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in casserole dish.
Top with butter and crackers.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: marinade(beef, chicken)
directions: Need to marinate meats for at least 1 hour before broiling or grilling.

title: bologna
directions: Mix and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Separate into 4 parts and roll into logs.
Bake, uncovered, in broiler pan, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crab meat mold
directions: Combine the soup, lemon juice and gelatin over heat, stirring until gelatin is dissolved and mixture is warm.
Add cream cheese and blend well; add mayonnaise and blend well.
Add crab meat, celery and onions and mix well.
Place mixture in a mold and refrigerate until jelled.

title: easy cornbread
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into a well-greased pan (8 x 8-inch). Bake at 400° for 35 minutes.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach in small amount of water.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Beat eggs and add 1/4 of spinach water, cottage cheese and flour.
Season with nutmeg and mustard or lemon juice.
Add drained spinach.
Bake in a greased baking dish for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 7 or 8.

title: lasagna
directions: Boil noodles until tender.
Brown hamburger; add salt, pepper and garlic to taste.
Drain hamburger and add the tomato paste. Add water until it looks creamy.
In a cake pan put some meat on the bottom, then put a layer of noodles, next layer put two kinds of cheese and then repeat.
Fill to top.
Put in a 350° oven, covered, for 1 hour.
Then serve.

title: harry's chocolate cake
directions: Cream together the butter and sugar. Add egg, dry ingredients sifted together, milk, coffee and vanilla.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch pan (lightly greased) and lined with wax paper. Bake 40 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cool and top with whipped cream

title: pineapple and cream cheese mold
directions: Cook the pineapple and sugar together 3 minutes after it comes to a boil.
Add the Jell-O and dissolve. Add softened cream cheese and mix until cheese is blended thoroughly.
Set aside to cool. When cool, add the whipping cream (maraschino cherries, if you desire).
Pour into buttered mold and refrigerate for several hours.

title: kip's dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients. Whip thoroughly. Cover and allow to marinate 24 hours. Keep mixed.
Store in large wine bottles (glass).
Place in refrigerator.

title: knockwurst and cabbage
directions: In saucepan, cook cabbage in boiling water 10 minutes; drain. In 1 1/2-quart shallow baking dish (10 x 6 x 2-inch), arrange cabbage.
Combine soup, milk, apple and caraway; pour over cabbage.
Arrange knockwurst between cabbage wedges.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until hot.
Stir sauce before serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: tomato salad
directions: Stir together in bowl the tomatoes, green pepper, parsley and onion.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Boil water; add oats.
Let stand for 20 minutes.
Cream margarine and sugars; add well beaten eggs.
Mix altogether.
Add vanilla, flour, cinnamon, salt and soda.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes in a well-greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: rhubarb cream pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and nutmeg.
Beat in eggs.
Add rhubarb. Put into bottom crust in 9-inch pie pan.
Dot with margarine; put on pie crust top and make steam vents.
Bake at 400° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: pennsylvania apple pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Lightly spread in shallow greased pan. Bake in preheated (350°) oven for 25 minutes or until macaroon-like crust forms on top.
Serve warm or cold with whipped cream.
Serves 6.

title: holiday fruit drops
directions: Cream shortening and brown sugar; beat in 2 eggs.
Mix well. Add sour milk, then dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Add nuts, dates and cherries.
Chill 1 hour.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles until done in salted water and drain.
Brown beef and garlic in oil.
Stir in tomatoes, sauce, onion, salt, pepper and oregano.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Alternate noodles, meat and Mozzarella cheese.
Then top with grated Parmesan cheese. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Yields 4 large servings.

title: hot bean dip
directions: Blend on high in blender until smooth.
Crumble 4 slices crisp fried bacon on top.
Serve hot or cold.

title: party punch
directions: Combine all ingredients and float fruit in punch bowl.
Sugar may be added.

title: quick garlic bean dip
directions: In food processor, combine all ingredients.
Process 1 minute or until smooth, scraping bowl twice.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: apple butter muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease inside of 12 muffin cups. Combine milk, oil, apple butter, egg and honey in a medium size bowl.
Blend with a electric mixer on low speed until well mixed and add self-rising flour and beat at low speed until flour is mixed in and lumps are gone.
Spoon into muffin cups until each cup is about 3/4 full.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until toothpick in center of muffin comes out clean.
Allow muffins to remain in pan for 1 or 2 minutes before removing.
Serve warm. Makes 12 large muffins.

title: plum cake
directions: Sift flour, salt, cloves and cinnamon together.
Combine oil, sugar and eggs.
Beat until blended.
Beat in plums.
Add flour mixture and mix well.
Fold in nuts.
Turn batter into greased and floured tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.

title: hot chicken or turkey salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a baking dish except the potato chips and cheese, then top with the crushed chips (approximately 8 ounces) and the cheese.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°. Serve hot.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Mix together corn flakes and melted butter.
Put 1/2 of this mixture in a greased casserole dish.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, milk, salt and pepper.
Spread cabbage and onions over crumb mixture and pour soup mixture over this.
Spread cheese over this and add remaining corn flake mix over cheese.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Put cabbage in 2-quart casserole dish sprayed with oil.
Brown turkey and onion.
Add rice, soup and water.
Mix and pour over cabbage.
Bake, covered, at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: apple dapple cake
directions: Mix together the first 6 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: texas baked chicken
directions: Put rice in first (no water).
Put chicken on top of rice.
Add soups which have been mixed with water.
Sprinkle dry onion soup mix on top.
Do not mix.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: strawberry sour cream pie
directions: Mix crumbs and butter; press on bottom and sides of a 9-inch pie pan.
Chill for 1 hour.

title: corn chowder no. 2
directions: Cook potatoes in water with broth cubes in soup pot until tender.
Meanwhile, cook onion, bacon and celery in skillet.
When browned, add to potato/water pot.
Add parsley, salt, pepper and corn.
Cook several hours.
During last 1/2 hour, add cream.

title: lourde's coffee flan
directions: Beat eggs on low speed until foamy.
Add all ingredients, except brown sugar; blend together.
Sprinkle brown sugar on bottom of loaf pan (9 1/2 x 5 1/2-inch).
Pour mixture into pan. Place pan into pan of 1/2-inch hot water.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, until toothpick comes out clean.
Chill for at least 4 hours.
Turn upside down; remove from pan.

title: squash bake
directions: Wash and slice squash; boil in salted water with onion and bell pepper until tender. Drain off excess liquid and mash. Add egg, milk and cracker crumbs. Season with salt and pepper; pour into buttered dish. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until firm.

title: peach pecan cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together adding flour last.
Put into a large oiled Bundt pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° until done in center.

title: sunshine pasta salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 2 tablespoons liquid for Spring Dressing. Combine pineapple, cooked pasta, broccoli, peas, celery, parsley, onion and pimento in a large bowl.
Toss with Spring Dressing. Chill at least 1 hour.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cajun chicken pasta
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions to al dente stage. Saute chicken in margarine until browned.
Remove from skillet. Saute mushrooms, green onions, garlic and parsley.
Mix water and cornstarch.
Add to vegetable mixture.
Cook and stir until thickened slightly.
Stir in chicken and pasta.
Simmer a few minutes.
Correct seasoning by adding more Cajun Magic if you want it hotter or salt it if it needs more flavor, but you don't want it too hot.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef, then drain and cool.
Meanwhile, chop coarsely and place in large bowl the tomatoes, onions, lettuce and avocado.
Drain and add olives, chiles, beans and cooked meat; toss with Italian dressing.
Crush chips before opening bag and add to salad.

title: spice cookies
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and molasses; beat again.
In a separate bowl, sift together flour, baking soda and spices.
Add the dry ingredients to the wet and stir.
If necessary, gradually add more flour until you are able to roll a small ball of dough in your palms without it sticking.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls and roll them lightly in granulated sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets and bake in 375° oven for 15 to 18 minutes, until very lightly browned.
They should be chewy, if overbaked, becomes tough.

title: sugarless applesauce cake
directions: Cream together the oil and eggs until well blended.
Sift flour, soda, cinnamon and nutmeg; set aside.
Add liquid sweetener and applesauce.
Mix well.
Cook
raisins and water until all the water is gone.
Add flour and mix well.
Add vanilla and raisins last.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: pecan dream cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients; bake in oven at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: vernice's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix thoroughly the Crisco, butter, sugars, eggs and vanilla. Blend in remaining ingredients.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet. Bake until light brown (about 10 minutes).
Makes about 7 dozen.

title: macaroni beef casserole
directions: Mix beef, eggs, ketchup, milk and onions.
Mix macaroni, mustard and mayonnaise.
Spread in 2-quart baking dish.
Spread beef mixture over top.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Top with mixture of crumbs and butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: heath cake
directions: Mix and press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Simmer for 20 minutes.
Brown meat.
Add water and bay leaves. Bring to boil and add remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil, then simmer until vegetables are tender.

title: peach surprise
directions: Mix lemon juice in milk.
Stir in peaches.
Pour in crust. Beat cream and put on top.
Garnish with peaches.
Refrigerate until serving time.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Add eggs one at a time. Grease Bundt pan and sprinkle with granulated sugar, just enough to coat pan.
Pour batter in pan and bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 325°.

title: teen's date cake
directions: Cream sugar and eggs.
Combine flour, salt and baking powder. Sift over nuts and dates until well coated.
Combine with sugar and egg mixture.
Add vanilla to mixture.
Bake in loaf pan 1 hour and 20 minutes at 275°.

title: meatballs and applesauce
directions: Mix all ingredients except tomato sauce.
Roll in balls.
Put in flat casserole dish.
Pour tomato sauce over meatballs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lazy day cobbler
directions: Melt stick of margarine in large baking dish. Mix flour, milk, sugar, baking powder and salt together. Pour this batter in baking dish over melted margarine. (Do not stir.) Pour fruit over batter; add cinnamon. Bake for 40 to 50 minutes at 400° until golden brown. Batter will rise and cover fruit.

title: rich cocoa fudge(hershey's original recipe)
directions: In heavy 4-quart saucepan over medium heat, cook sugar, cocoa, salt and milk to a full boil, stirring constantly.
Boil, without stirring, to 234° on candy thermometer or until syrup, when dropped into very cold water, forms a soft ball that flattens when removed from water.
Bulb of thermometer should not rest on bottom of saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Add butter or margarine and vanilla extract; do not stir.
Cool at room temperature to 110° (lukewarm).
Beat with wooden spoon until fudge thickens and loses some gloss.
Quickly spread in buttered 8 or 9-inch pan.
Cool. Cut in 3 dozen squares.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Brown hamburger and onion together.
Drain.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix well and bring to a boil.
Let stand approximately 15 minutes and serve on buns.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in a covered saucepan in boiling water for 20 to 25 minutes until just tender; drain well.
Cool slightly.
Peel and cube potatoes.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Combine flour, oats, baking soda, cinnamon and salt. Cream butter and sugars. Beat until light and fluffy. Add eggs and vanilla. Mix well. Alternate the dry ingredients and pumpkin to butter and sugar mixture. Mix well. Add raisins or chocolate chips. Bake (one-fourth cup cookie dough for each cookie on greased cookie sheets) 20 to 25 minutes until firm and light brown.

title: corn flake treats
directions: Heat Karo and sugar until mixture just begins to boil.
Stir in peanut butter and corn flakes.
Drop by teaspoonful onto cookie sheet lined with foil until able to handle.

title: chewy cake
directions: Melt butter; add brown sugar and mix well.
Add eggs and flour.
Blend in vanilla and nuts, mixing well.
Bake in greased pan at 350 degrees for 25-30 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook meat, onion and mushrooms until done, season to taste; drain.

In oblong dish, place a layer of fries, layer of meat, part of soup (you need to mix soup with water before pouring over meat), layer of cheese; repeat layers until you get as much as you want. Place in a 350° oven until cheese melts and is turning brown.
On this recipe, you put as much or as little ingredients as you want.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Beat yolks until well blended. Gradually add sugar and 1/2 milk. Mix cocoa and flour; fold into mixture. Add remaining milk. Cook in double boiler until thick. Add butter; mix well. Pour into shell and top with meringue.

title: rhubarb gelatin salad
directions: Cook enough rhubarb to yield 2 cups of sauce. Dissolve strawberry gelatin in boiling water. Add the crushed pineapple (including juice) and 2 cups rhubarb. Pour into large (1-quart or larger) mold or bowl. Chill in refrigerator for several hours or overnight. Unmold and serve.

title: fruit dressing for salad
directions: Boil first five ingredients for 1 minute.
Add beaten eggs, slowly, to boiling mixture.

title: erewhon crispy rice snacks
directions: Mix peanut butter, nuts, vanilla and cinnamon together in a bowl.
Add crispy brown rice cereal and stir gently until cereal is well coated.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Mix butter and brown sugar.
Let bubble 2 minutes.
Stirring constantly.
Add 1/2 c. water and milk.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat, beat in sugar.
Add vanilla.

title: pineapple date bread
directions: Sprinkle brown sugar into greased 9-inch square pan. Top with pineapple slices. Place a cherry in the center of each pineapple slice. Dot with butter. In a bowl, combine quick bread mix and nuts. In another bowl, combine the water, eggs, applesauce and oil. Stir until just combined. Spoon over pineapple slices. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean. Immediately invert onto a serving plate. Cool 15 minutes before cutting. Serve warm. Makes 9 servings.

title: peanut butter clouds
directions: Mix shortening, butter, sugar and powdered sugar.
Add eggs and peanut butter.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add vanilla.

title: dogs in a sweater
directions: Separate dough.
Roll each piece into a 15-inch rope.
Insert stick in hot dog.
Wrap hot dog in spiral form around dough.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: kahlua
directions: Bring brown sugar,
white sugar and water to a rapid boil. With wire whisk, stir in instant coffee.
Pour into a jug and add 1 quart vodka and vanilla.
Cover tightly and let stand on counter for 2 weeks.
Stir a bit each day.
Makes 7 1/2 cups.
Serve over ice or in Black Russian Cake.

title: heavenly peanut butter fudge
directions: Place sugar, butter and milk in large heavy pan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until ingredients melt.
Continue cooking to soft boil stage or 235°.
Remove from heat and quickly stir in marshmallow cream and peanut butter.
Mix well.
Pour into large greased pan (10 x 15 x 2-inch).
Cool and cut into squares. Makes 5 pounds.

title: scripture cake
directions: This a fruit and nut cake.
Just get out the family Bible and follow directions.
Bake in a moderate oven for 35 minutes or longer at 360° to 375°.

title: beverly hills steak (gizzards)
directions: Brown gizzards in skillet with oil, flour, salt and pepper. Place in small 8 x 8 dish. Add chopped carrots, celery, onions, steak sauce and mushrooms.
Cover with water.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Lower heat to 250°.
Cook 4 hours until very tender.

title: ginger ale pound cake
directions: Cream
sugar,
margarine and Crisco.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating
well
after
each addition.
Add lemon extract. Add flour
and	ginger	ale
alternately.
Bake in greased and floured tube or Bundt pan for 1 hour 15 minutes or until done.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Let cheese soften.
Blend with chili sauce.
Add Miracle Whip, onion and shrimp and chill before serving.

title: easy homemade ice cream
directions: Mix together and pour into ice cream churn; freeze.

title: independence day cake
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; set aside at room temperature.
Prepare and bake cake as directed on package for 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool cake in pan on rack for 25 minutes.
Poke deep holes through top of cake with fork.
Space holes 1 inch apart. Slowly pour gelatin mixture over cooled cake.
Set in refrigerator while preparing frosting.

title: christmas breakfast
directions: Spread croutons in a lightly greased 13 x 9 pan. Cook sausage well until brown, stirring to crumble. Drain well. Sprinkle sausage over croutons. Combine eggs, milk, soup, mushrooms and mustard; mix well and pour over sausage. Cover and refrigerate at least 8 hours or overnight. Remove from refrigerator and let stand 30 minutes. Bake uncovered at 325° for 50 to 55 minutes. Sprinkle cheese over top and bake an additional 5 minutes.

title: all-bran muffins
directions: Mix the first two ingredients; set aside and cool.
Add the oil.
Combine the eggs, sugar, buttermilk, flour, soda and salt. Mix. Combine the two mixtures.
Add the remaining All-Bran.
Spray muffin pans.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Also will keep 7 or 8 days in refrigerator.

title: jiffy casserole
directions: First day, sprinkle brisket with meat tenderizer; rub in well. Place the brisket on heavy foil and put 4 tablespoons of liquid smoke on brisket; rub in.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: pears hilda
directions: Drain syrup from canned pears.
Cover with Kahlua and marinate in refrigerator overnight or at least several hours.
Place 1 or 2 halves in dessert dish.
Serve with whipped cream and Hershey almond shavings.

title: fudge brownies
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine the first six ingredients.
In another bowl, combine oil, eggs and vanilla; add to dry ingredients.
Do not overmix.
Spread in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with nuts if desired.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.
Yield:
about 2 dozen.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Mix and place in greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs or crushed Ritz crackers.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Cut zucchinis lengthwise.
Scoop out centers leaving a wall around it.
After cutting up the insides, cook them until soft in salted water.
Drain well when done.
Then mix together with all the above ingredients, except the boats.
When mixed thoroughly fill the boats.
Take a baking pan and place some spaghetti sauce in the bottom and then add the boats.
Finally, drizzle some sauce on the top of the boats.
Cover and bake at 350 degrees for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries and orange peel.
Pour boiling water over sugar and Jell-O.
Stir well; add to cranberries.
Add cold water and pineapple last.
Let refrigerate until set.

title: cranberry loaf
directions: Wash cranberries in a strainer.
Let drain.
Chop cranberries in a blender.
Place in a large mixing bowl.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Sift first 5 ingredients.
Add nuts.
Keep separate.
Melt butter; add orange juice.
Add enough water to make 1 1/2 cups liquid.
Stir in the eggs.
Pour over dry ingredients all at once, mixing just enough to dampen mixture.
Fold in the cranberries. Bake in greased lined loaf pans in 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes. Let stand 15 minutes in pans before removing.
Slices better after storing overnight.
Makes 3 loaves (7 1/2 x 3 1/2 x 2 1/8).

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in dish.
Mix flour, sugar and milk.
Pour peaches in dish.
Then, pour flour mixture over peaches.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Brown onion in oil; add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 30 minutes. Makes 2 cups.
Can be used over chicken, pork chops or deer meat.

title: alphabet macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Drain fruit.
Keep juice and put in saucepan.
Add white sugar, salt and flour to juice.
Mix and when it starts to thicken, add eggs and cook longer.
Add vanilla.
Mix fruit sauce with macaroni and let stand in refrigerator all night. Before serving, add fruit and Cool Whip.

title: biscuit monkey bread
directions: Sprinkle the pecans in the bottom of a well-greased Bundt pan. Combine the sugar and cinnamon and set aside.
Cut the biscuits into quarters and roll in the sugar and cinnamon mixture and layer them in the Bundt pan.
Combine the brown sugar and melted margarine and pour over the biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool about 10 minutes and turn out onto a serving plate.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Combine brown sugar, margarine, syrup and salt in a 2-cup glass measuring cup.
Bring to a boil in microwave about 2 minutes; then after stirring, boil for 2 more minutes.
Remove from microwave and add the soda.
Stir.
It foams up so use a large dish.
Put popped corn in a large brown grocery bag.
Pour mixture over popped corn and shake bag well.
Put in microwave and cook for 1 1/2 minutes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Combine eggs, milk, cheese, salt and pepper; mix well.
Add potatoes, onion, pepper (green) and ham.
Pour mixture into greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes or until set.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: In heavy 10-inch skillet (ovenproof) or 10-inch baking dish, melt the butter and sprinkle the brown sugar evenly over the butter.
Arrange drained pineapple in an attractive pattern on the sugar coating.

title: dorcas pohl's honey mustard dressing
directions: Place all of the ingredients in a bowl and whisk or blend together.
This dressing is also great on sandwiches as well as salads.
It will keep at least a week in the refrigerator.

title: christmas cheese ball
directions: Get two cheeses at room temperature.
Mix all ingredients together and shape into ball or log.
Roll in chopped pecans (wax paper) and refrigerate 24 hours before serving.

title: sally lunn bread
directions: Mix 1 cup flour, sugar, yeast and salt.
Heat milk, water and oleo.
Beat into flour mixture.
Add eggs and 1 cup flour.
Beat 2 minutes.
Stir in rest of flour to make stiff dough.
Cover and let rise until double in bulk.
Stir down and spoon into well-greased and floured Bundt pan.
Let rise until doubled.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: puppy chow
directions: In a big bowl, mix white chocolate, peanut butter and a small amount of oil.
Melt in microwave.
Stir in cereal.
Pour powdered sugar in a paper sack.
Dump in cereal and shake.

title: easy hamburg casserole
directions: In a large deep dish casserole, 3-quart or larger.
Layer the potatoes on top of hamburg, then onions, peppers, carrots and spread tomatoes and seasoning next.
Last, top with cheese and bake for 2 hours at 300° or microwave at Medium heat for 1 hour or until potatoes are tender.

title: crab and shrimp appetizers(microwave)
directions: Microwave green pepper, onion and celery until tender.
Mix together with shrimp, crab, salt, mayo, Worcestershire sauce, pepper and lemon juice.
Spread in serving dish and put crushed potato chips on top.
Microwave for 10 minutes at 70% power.
Give dish 1/4 turn twice during cooking.
Serve as a spread on crackers.

title: magalia firefighter's bean soup
directions: Wash beans; place in a large kettle.
Cover with water.
Add 3 tablespoons of salt.
Soak overnight.
In morning, drain and add 2 quarts of water and chunks of bacon or ham or if you prefer, ham hock.
Add seasonings and simmer 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in an ungreased 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with crushed cheese crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: butternut bisque
directions: Cube, peel and set aside squash.
Melt the butter in a large soup pot.
Add the carrots, onion and celery. Saute until soft. Stir the squash and potatoes into the veggies.
Add the stock. Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer, partially covered, for 40 minutes. Add curry, nutmeg and ginger.
Puree the soup in batches in a blender.
Return to saucepan.
Add more stock, if necessary, to thin.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve hot with a dollop of sour cream, if you like.

title: play doh
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Cook on low heat until stiff.
Cool and knead well.
Store in airtight container.

title: stir-fry chicken and peppers
directions: Heat half of oil in skillet.
Add chicken and cook about 5 minutes until no longer pink.
Remove to plate.
Add rest of oil to skillet.
Add peppers, garlic, onion, salt and oregano.
Cook, stirring, until vegetables are tender-crisp.
Add chicken, salsa and drained beans; heat through.
Serve with warm tortillas.

title: strawberry sour cream jello
directions: Dissolve Jell-O with water; add strawberries, pineapple and bananas.
Mix.
Pour 1/2 mixture into ring mold or bowl. Refrigerate until firm.
Cover with sour cream and pour remaining Jell-O mixture on top; refrigerate until firm.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift sugar,
add oil; beat.
Add beaten egg yolks, then hot water;
mix well.
Add carrots, then dry ingredients.
Add nuts; fold in
egg
whites.
Bake
at
375° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until done in greased and floured tube pan.

title: sausage egg brunch(great for holidays)
directions: Place bread pieces in the bottom of a buttered 1 1/2-quart shallow baking dish.
Place sausage on top of bread and sprinkle with cheese.
Combine eggs, milk and dry mustard.
Pour evenly over cheese. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 50 to 55 minutes.
Serves 4.
Can easily be doubled.

title: gayle's baked beans
directions: Combine ingredients and bake at 250° until desired dryness. The slower and longer the better.

title: grandma brugger's pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, butter and sugar in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 8 minutes at 400°.
Mix together cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip. Put on top of crumbs.
Mix jello, water and strawberries.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Pour on cheese mixture.
Refrigerate 2 hours.

title: cocktail hot dogs
directions: Simmer mustard and jelly together.
After jelly melts, add bite-size hot dogs and continue to simmer for 1 1/2 hours.

title: spaghetti
directions: Brown ground chuck and drain well.
In a separate pan, saute onion; add green pepper, followed by sliced mushrooms.
In a large saucepan, combine stewed tomatoes, tomato sauce, garlic and oregano.
To sauce, add drained beef, onions, peppers and mushrooms.
Stir well and simmer for 1 to 2 hours.
Serve with pasta and garlic bread.

title: rum cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour cake pan (Bundt or tube).
Sprinkle pecans over bottom of pan.
Mix all ingredients. Pour over pecans.
Bake 1 hour.

title: mints
directions: Mix ingredients together using food coloring of your choice. Roll into desired thickness; cut into shapes of your choice.

title: polish easter cake
directions: Scald 1/2 cup milk.
Stir in sugar, salt and butter.
Cool to lukewarm.
Pour lukewarm water into large bowl.
Sprinkle yeast over water; stir until dissolved.
Add milk mixture, eggs and flour; beat vigorously 5 minutes.
Cover; let rise in warm place, free from draft, for 1 1/2 hours or until double in bulk.

title: double rich chocolate brownies
directions: Add 1 cup chocolate chips in butter in saucepan. Stir until melted. Remove from heat. Add sugar.
Add eggs (one at a time). Mix well.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour dry ingredients into chocolate mixture. Stir until smooth. Add remaining chocolate chips.
Pour into a greased 8-inch square pan. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking soda, salt and cinnamon in a large bowl.
Add eggs and oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not beat.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, pecans and bananas.
Spoon batter into 3 greased and floured round cake pans. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until pick comes clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove and cool completely.
Spread with a cream cheese frosting between layers and on top and sides of cake. Sprinkle with pecans if desired.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Grease and flour 3 coffee cans (1 pound) or 4 small loaf pans.

title: suzie's sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Combine ground round, egg, cornstarch, salt, onion and peppers. Form into small balls.
Brown in skillet with 1 tablespoon of oil. When brown, drain and set aside.
(May be frozen and kept in freezer up to 3 months.)

title: spring salad
directions: Dissolve jello in
hot	water and let stand until cool. Add juice, cottage
cheese (or sour cream) and crushed pineapple. Pour in mold.

title: conch fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients, except conchs, to make batter, dicing onion and bell pepper.
Add conchs and fry in heated oil until golden brown.

title: cajun style venison
directions: Season meat with salt and peppers.
Dredge meat completely with flour. Brown in hot oil. Remove to baking pan prepared with heavy-duty aluminum foil large enough to completely seal meat. Place remaining ingredients on and around meat.
Seal foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove meat from pan. Let gravy thicken. Serve over rice.

title: dip for fruit
directions: Mix thoroughly and chill.

title: pina colada muffins
directions: Cream sugar, egg, margarine and sour cream.
Add dry ingredients.
Fold in coconut and pineapple.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: shrimp sandwiches
directions: Beat all ingredients with mixer until well blended.
Spread on bread.
Garnish with tiny whole shrimp (there are approximately 75 per can) or parsley.

title: cream tacos
directions: In large Dutch oven brown meat.
Drain.
Add all ingredients except Doritos.
Warm over medium heat, stirring constantly until cheese is melted.
Serve over crushed Doritos in bowls.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix hash browns, salt, pepper, onion, soup, sour cream, cheese and butter together.
Put into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan or dish. Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: cheese spinach soup
directions: Blend oleo and flour in large saucepan.
Cook until bubbly, stirring constantly.
Add beef bouillon; mix well.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Mix in cheese.
Cook until cheese is melted, stirring constantly.
Add spinach and seasonings; mix well.
Heat to serving temperature.

title: spicy skillet chicken
directions: Combine flour and salt in plastic bag.
Add chicken and shake to coat well.
In large skillet, brown chicken in oil; continue cooking, uncovered, over low heat 15 minutes.
Add other ingredients; blend well.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat to simmer and cook for 20 to 25 minutes (until liquid is absorbed).
May sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and/or parsley before serving.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Blend margarine with sugar, cocoa, milk and vanilla. Mix in nuts. Spread on cake.

title: slow cooked pork chops with apples
directions: Place pork chops in a slow cooker (crock-pot).
Slice the apple and place over pork chops.
Put 1 teaspoon brown sugar on each apple and pork chop.
Then place 1 teaspoon butter on each apple and pork chop.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Then cover it all with apple cider; make sure the cider is deep enough to cover it all.
Cook on low for 10 hours.
Serve the apples with the chops.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine eggs, sugar and butter.
Cream with electric mixer.
Add salt, zucchini and vanilla; mix well.
Combine flour, soda, baking powder and spices. Mix well.
Add to zucchini mixture and mix well.
Add nuts and stir in well.
Pour into 2 loaf pans sprayed with Pam.
Bake 1 hour.
Cool in pans for about 15 minutes.
Remove from pans and put on cake rack to finish cooling.
Serve with whipped topping, if desired.

title: overnight egg bake
directions: Place 8 slices of bread on bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle with cheese and ham.
Cover with remaining bread slices. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Before baking, top with corn flakes and drizzle with butter.
Bake uncovered 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Let stand 10 minutes and serve.

title: spiced tea
directions: Blend all ingredients well and store in well sealed container. Serve 2 teaspoons per cup of hot water or to taste.

title: banana cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in 15 x 11-inch pan at 350° until golden brown, usually 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Cut a core in cabbage about 3 inches deep.
Cook in a large kettle about 15 minutes.
Let stand until cool enough to handle. Cook rice until partially tender.
Cool, then add meat, egg, salt, pepper, bacon and onion; mix well.
Separate cabbage leaves, put 1 tablespoon meat in each leaf.
Roll up, tucking in ends.
Place into a 4-quart pot.
Mix tomato soup with 2 cans water.
Pour over cabbage rolls and cook slowly for about 1 hour.

title: easy garden bake
directions: Spread first 4 ingredients in lightly greased 8 x 8-inch pan or 9-inch pie plate. Beat remaining ingredients in blender on high for 15 seconds or 1 minute with hand beater.
Pour in pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 400°.
Let stand 5 minutes.
May add cooked chicken cubes for Easy Chicken-Garden Bake.

title: lasagna
directions: Combine hamburger, garlic, parsley, basil, salt, tomatoes and tomato paste.
Simmer 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: In a large bowl, combine chicken, celery, onions, chestnuts, rice, soup, salt, pepper and lemon juice.
Mix mayonnaise with water and add to chicken mixture; add eggs.
Pour into a large baking dish (greased).
Top with potato chips.
Bake at 450° about 15 minutes or until bubbly and slightly golden brown.

title: kentucky fried chicken - old fashioned recipe
directions: Melt butter in a pan to coat pan.
Place remaining ingredients into a bag and shake well to mix.
Put chicken in bag to coat and place in pan.
Bake in oven at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: easy turkey tetrazzini
directions: Cook mushrooms in margarine for 1 minute over low.
Add salt and pepper, turkey, soup and sour cream.
Mix well.
Alternately layer cooked and drained spaghetti and turkey mixture in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Mix thoroughly and chill.

title: ham ball
directions: Mix cheese and mayo.
Stir in next 4 items; mix well and chill.
Form into a ball and roll in chopped nuts or crushed crackers.
Store in fridge until ready to use.

title: cheesey potato soup
directions: Peel and dice potatoes. Rinse when finished. Put in big pot. Cover with clean water, just enough to cover potatoes. Add pepper, garlic salt and onion. Place on medium heat until potatoes are tender (about 20 minutes). Turn heat to low and add milk and cheese. Stir often. Serve when cheese is melted.

title: tolerinie
directions: Brown beef, onions, peppers and garlic.
Cook noodles until tender and drain.
Mix all but half of cheese, spread in 9 x 13-inch dish and top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: curried ham and chicken
directions: Combine onion, green pepper, curry powder and margarine in 1 1/2-quart glass casserole dish.
Microwave on High, uncovered, 3 to 4 minutes.
Stir once.
Add flour, salt, bouillon and milk. Microwave on High 7 to 8 minutes until mixture boils and thickens. Stir once or twice.
Stir in chicken and ham.
Microwave on High, uncovered, 3 to 4 minutes or until well heated.
Sprinkle with almonds.

title: green bean soup
directions: Cube potatoes and cook (half pan of water).
Leave water in pan.
Add other ingredients.
Simmer until mixture is soupy. Serve with vinegar and sour cream.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Place onions in bottom of crock-pot. Add chicken. Stir remaining ingredients together and pour over the chicken. Cook on low 7 to 9 hours or on high 3 to 4 hours. Serve with noodles or pasta.

title: pineapple frappe
directions: Put marshmallows in bowl.
Cover with pineapple, juice and all.
Set in refrigerator overnight.
Fold in the Cool Whip.
Top with crushed nuts, if you wish.

title: cheese fans(like me!)
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together in a bowl.
Cut in shortening until mixture looks like coarse corn meal.
Make a well in center of mixture and add milk all at one time.
Stir with fork until dough follows fork around bowl.
Gently form dough into a ball and put onto a lightly floured surface.
Knead it lightly with fingertips 10 to 15 times.

title: barbecued round steak
directions: Trim fat from steak and cut steak crosswise into 1-inch wide strips.
Heat oil in a large skillet over medium heat until hot. Add meat and cook, stirring constantly, until meat is evenly browned.
Drain meat and pat dry with paper towels.
Transfer meat to an 8-inch square baking dish and set aside.

title: apple date squares
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Stir gently.
Combine eggs, pie filling, almond extract, oil and vanilla.
Stir in dates and walnuts.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: no fuss chicken
directions: Combine salad dressing, preserves and soup mix. Put chicken in 11 x 17 pan.
Top with dressing mixture. Cover. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Baste. Bake uncovered for 20 minutes or until juices run clear.
Serve over rice.

title: mexican casserole(club member: mindy daniels)
directions: Brown meat over medium heat. Drain excess fat. Add taco seasoning and 1/2 cup water. Simmer until most water is absorbed. Melt cheese in a small saucepan on medium heat with Ro-Tel tomatoes. In a baking dish, layer broken chips, meat and cheese. Bake for 10 minutes.

title: meatball italian wedding soup
directions: In a large saucepan, heat broth to a boil. Add remaining ingredients and return to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium and cook for 10 minutes or until pasta is tender, stirring frequently. Serve sprinkled with Parmesan cheese. Serves 10 to 12.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream together powdered sugar, cream cheese and peanut butter, then fold in Cool Whip.
Mix well and pour into crust.
Add a little more Cool Whip to cover top of pie.
Ready to eat.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Place flour in a paper bag; shake chicken, a few pieces at a time, to coat.
In a large skillet, heat oil over medium-high. Brown chicken on all sides.
Remove chicken and set aside.
In skillet, add garlic and onion; saute until onion is soft.
Add mushrooms, broth, tomato puree, oregano, parsley, salt and pepper. Bring to a boil.
Return chicken to skillet.
Cover and simmer 1 hour or until chicken is tender.
Serve over spaghetti.
Yields 8.

title: quick cranberry relish
directions: In small mixing bowl, stir together the ingredients.
Cover and chill thoroughly in refrigerator.
Stir mixture before serving.
Sprinkle chopped walnuts over mixture.
Makes 12 servings.

title: sweet cornbread
directions: In a large bowl of electric mixer, sprinkle yeast over the water.
Add 1 tablespoon granulated sugar.
Let stand until yeast is soft (about 5 minutes).
Add remaining granulated sugar, milk, salt, orange rind and softened butter.
Add 3 cups all-purpose flour.
Mix to blend, then beat at medium speed until smooth and elastic (about 5 minutes).
Add eggs, one at a time, beating until smooth after each addition.
Stir in whole wheat flour, then about 1 1/2 cups more all-purpose flour to make a soft dough.

title: cheese ball 2
directions: Mix all ingredients and 1/2 of pecans.
Make a ball and roll in the rest of pecans.

title: coconut cake
directions: Make cake per directions on box. Mix cream of coconut mix, coconut and sour cream together.
Ice cake while warm.
Put toothpick holes in layers.
After you ice each layer and put cake together, refrigerate for several hours and then ice around cake. Store cake in refrigerator.
Makes 3 layers.

title: snickerdoodle drops
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease cookie sheet.
Beat together the margarine, brown sugar and 3/4 cup sugar.
Add eggs and mix well. In medium bowl, mix flour, oats, cinnamon (1 teaspoon), baking soda and salt.
Add to sugar mixture and mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Combine other tablespoon of sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Sprinkle lightly over cookies.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: uncle bob's barbecue chicken recipe
directions: Mix with fork the oil, vinegar and egg.
Add salt, pepper and poultry seasoning.
Apply to chicken occasionally as you barbecue. Makes enough for 2 chickens.

title: baked chicken breasts with horseradish cream sauce(serves 4)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium saucepan, melt butter over medium heat.
Stir in flour and cook, stirring, until sauce is thick and smooth, about 3 minutes.
Stir in horseradish, sour cream, sugar, mustard and vinegar.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix butter, sugar and flour together.
Add eggs and stir.
Add remaining ingredients and stir thoroughly, saving coconut until last.
Place mixture in thawed pie crust.
Cook at 350° until set.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Top with bread crumbs or croutons.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°. Serves 12.

title: lap cakes
directions: Mix candied fruits, raisins or dates and pecans with 1 cup flour; set aside.
Mix melted chocolate, syrup and sugar.
Add beaten eggs.
Add cinnamon, allspice, ground cloves, nutmeg, baking soda and salt.
Add enough flour so mixture will not run. Now, add fruits and nuts.
Dough will now be thick.
Spread dough to 1/2-inch thickness in greased and floured pans; pat down with hand dipped in water.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Remove from pans; serve while still hot.
Edges will be hard, but will soften when stored tightly covered.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add soups, tomato juice and chilies; cook until all mixed.

In a large flat casserole or cake pan, put a layer of tortillas which have been cut in fourths. Next put a layer of ground beef mixture, then another layer of tortillas and remaining layer of ground beef mixture.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, uncovered. Serve with chopped lettuce, tomatoes and more grated cheese and taco sauce.

title: beignets
directions: In a large mixing bowl, pour the boiling water over the shortening, sugar and salt.
Add the milk and let stand until warm.
In a small bowl, dissolve the yeast in the warm water and add to the milk mixture with the egg.
Stir in 2 cups flour and beat.
Add enough flour to make a soft dough.
Place the dough in a greased bowl, turning to grease the top.
Cover with wax paper and a cloth and chill until ready to use.
On a lightly floured surface, roll the dough to 1/8-inch thickness.
Do not let dough rise before frying.
Cut into 2-inch squares and fry in deep hot fat at 360°.
Brown on one side.
Turn and brown on the other side.
Drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle with the confectioners sugar and serve hot.
Makes 30 doughnuts.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Combine crushed graham crackers, peanut butter, confectioners sugar and melted butter.
Mix well.
Press mixture into a well-greased 10 3/4 x 7-inch pan.
Pour melted chocolate chips over mixture and place in refrigerator.
When cool, cut into squares.
Makes 3 dozen pieces.

title: corn, corn, corn
directions: Melt butter, add eggs and rest of ingredients.
Pour into 2 qt. casserole dish. Bake at 350 degrees, about 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sweet and sour brussels sprouts
directions: Combine the salt, sugar, vinegar, horseradish and dry mustard. Stir.
Add the onion and the thawed Brussels sprouts.
Stir. Allow to marinate 8 hours.

title: green rice(from stephenson's apple orchard restaurant)
directions: Mix rice, parsley, cheese, onion, green pepper and garlic in greased 2-quart casserole.
Blend rest of ingredients.
Mix into rice.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes or until like a soft custard.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and simmer 30 minutes.
Add California vegies and chicken soup and simmer another 30 to 45 minutes.
Add cheese gradually and simmer until melted and hot.

title: neutron bananas
directions: Here's a recipe that's sure to "brighten" any mother's day:

title: mary's mosaic fruit slices
directions: *Use both red and green cherries for color.

title: salsa
directions: In a large saucepan mix olive oil and garlic.
Brown.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 1/2 hour.

title: easy coconut pie
