directions: Beat eggs, mix flour and sugar and add to eggs. Add other ingredients. Beat well and pour into 2 greased pie pans. Bake 30 - 40 minutes in 350° oven. Makes 2 pies. Makes its own crust.

title: classic cobb salad
directions: Preheat the grill. Drizzle the chicken breasts with olive oil, then season with the Essence. Grill the chicken until the juices run clear, about 4 minutes per side.

Remove from the grill; cool and dice. Cook the bacon in a large skillet over medium heat until just crispy, 6 to 8 minutes. Remove from the skillet and drain on paper towels. Whisk the olive oil and lemon juice in a mixing bowl. Whisk in 1/4 pound of the Blue cheese, a handful at a time. Season with salt and pepper. Toss the lettuce in a large bowl with the dressing.
Season the avocado, tomatoes and eggs with salt and pepper.

title: chocolate nut pie
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Pour over chocolate chips in bowl; stir until chocolate chips are melted.
Add sugar and brown sugar; mix well.
Stir in flour, eggs, vanilla and pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: mary kocman's dressing
directions: Toast bread.
After bread cools, soak in cold water and squeeze and pull apart into small pieces.
Add sauteed onions, celery, salt and pepper.
Add eggs and cold broth.
Bake 1/2 hour at 300°.

title: ma's meatballs
directions: Put all ingredients in bowl except bread.
Dip bread into milk; squeeze and crumble into meat mixture.
Roll into balls of any size.
Fry in frying pan with shortening or oil until brown all around.
Place in sauce; simmer for 4 or 5 hours.
Serve with noodles or spaghetti.
Can also be put into crock-pot.

title: cherry-fruit cocktail surprise
directions: Mix cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Add well drained fruit cocktail, mixing well.
Sprinkle dry jello over and stir. Refrigerate overnight.

title: baked brandied cranberries
directions: Place cranberries in shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle with the sugar.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Remove from oven.
Stir in brandy and sprinkle with 1/4 cup sugar.

title: beef or pork barbecue
directions: In large Dutch oven, put meat, onion, salt and pepper.
Add enough water to almost cover meat.
Cook until meat is tender and separates.
Add chili con carne.
Add brown sugar.
Add barbecue sauce to desired thickness.
Cook over medium low heat until hot. Serve on a bun.

title: cherry-pineapple dessert
directions: Put layer of cherry pie filling in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Next, add crushed pineapple, drained.
Next, add white or yellow cake mix (dry).
Next, add chopped pecans.
Next, add melted oleo. Bake approximately 1 hour at 300°.

title: earl jenkins' peach ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients together and freeze in ice cream churn.

title: orange glaze chicken wings
directions: Mix glaze ingredients together.
Put chicken wings in oiled baking pan and pour orange glaze over.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: ham and cheese stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Place a ham and cheese slice on each breast half.
Roll up chicken from narrow end and secure with toothpicks.
In skillet in hot oil, cook chicken for 10 minutes or until browned on all sides.
Spoon off fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients and heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 10 minutes or until chicken is fork-tender.
Garnish with chopped parsley, if desired. Prep time:
10 minutes.
Cook time:
25 minutes.

title: pizza rounds
directions: Brown hamburger meat and sausage together.
Drain grease. Melt Velveeta into meat.
Season to taste.
Put about 1 tablespoon of mixture on each rye round.
Broil in oven until brown and bubbly.

title: chicken stew
directions: Mix flour, salt, paprika and pepper; coat chicken and brown. Fill large kettle, a little over half, with water.
Add chicken. Add celery, onions, garlic, carrots and potatoes.
Cook for 2 hours or until chicken is done.
Take chicken out and debone.
Place chicken back in stew.
Add dumplings; this will make the stew thicken.
If too thick, just add a little water.

title: president reagan's favorite macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni as directed and drain well. Stir in butter and egg. Mix mustard and salt with 1 tablespoon hot water. Add to milk.
Add cheese, saving enough to sprinkle on top. Pour into buttered dish; add milk. Sprinkle cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Churn until ingredients are firm.
Makes 4 quarts.

title: cornucopias
directions: Beat egg slightly in small deep dish; add sugar and continue beating until very thick.
Add water gradually until thick and light.
Add flour all at once; fold in with a spoon.
Drop dough from tablespoon onto a greased and floured cookie sheet.
Spread dough into a very thin 5-inch circle.
Bake only 3 cookies at a time so you can roll them quickly.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Remove cookies immediately and roll into a cone.
Fill with fruit or Cool Whip.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° until firm.

title: tortellini salad
directions: Tear spinach leaves into bite-size pieces and lay in bottom of 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Shred cabbage into strips and lay on spinach leaves.
Halve cherry tomatoes and place on cabbage. Layer cooked tortellini on salad.
Drizzle dressing all over salad.
Just before serving, sprinkle bacon on salad.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix together butter and sugar. Mix eggs and milk together and cream with butter mixture. Mix dry ingredients together and add to butter mixture. Add oatmeal and mix well. Bake on ungreased pans for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: frosted cranberry salad
directions: Drain pineapple
and cranberry sauce.
Add enough water to juices to
make
2 cups liquid.
Bring to a boil.
Dissolve jello in	hot
liquid.
Chill
until partially set.
Add salad dressing to	cream
cheese
and
beat until fluffy.	Gradually beat in partially set jello.
Fold mixture into whipped cream. Set aside 1 1/2 cups of this mixture for topping.
Add drained fruit to remaining jello mixture.
Add pecans and apples.

title: oriental salad
directions: Saute sunflower seeds, almonds and noodles until lightly brown in the oleo.
Mix romaine, that is torn in bite-size pieces, the broccoli and green onions together and then sprinkle the nut mixture on top.
Add the dressing and toss lightly.

title: 7 layer cookie
directions: Pour the melted butter into an 11 x 14 pan and add the remaining ingredients in the order given.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
Cut in squares.

title: taco salad - california style
directions: Brown ground beef and onion until crumbly and drain.
Add 1/2 package taco seasoning.
Chop and put in large bowl, lettuce, green onions, avocado, celery and tomatoes.
Drain and add whole kernel corn, kidney beans and olives.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Put flour and seasoning into paper bag.
Put cut up chicken in bag and shake well.
Then place in dish in butter and put into preheated oven at 325° or 350°. Cook 30 minutes and turn over. Cook about 30 minutes longer. Depends on the size of chicken.

title: individual egglets
directions: Spray a 6-cup muffin tin with Pam.
Place one tablespoon butter in each muffin cup.
Gently break egg into each cup and sprinkle with 1 tablespoon cheese, 1 tablespoon bacon and 1 teaspoon parsley.
Add salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce, paprika and Tabasco to taste.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: peppermint salad
directions: Put the vanilla wafer crumbs in the bottom of dish or pan (Tupperware 7 1/2 x 12-inch container works well).
Save some of the crumbs to sprinkle on the top.
Whip the cream and add the cut marshmallows and the ground peppermint together.
Spread over the wafers and sprinkle the remaining wafer crumbs on top. Refrigerate until time to eat.

title: baked sliced potatoes
directions: Cut unpared potatoes into 1/4-inch thick slices.
Place overlapping slices in buttered 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Mix butter and oil.
Brush slices with mixture.
Pour remaining over potatoes.
Sprinkle with garlic salt.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes or until potatoes are done and browned at edges.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 servings.

title: spiced zucchini bread
directions: Cream shortening at medium speed of an electric mixer; gradually add the sugar, beating well.
Add the eggs, zucchini and water; mix thoroughly.
Combine flour, soda, baking powder, salt and spices; add to creamed mixture, stirring well.
Stir in pecans.
Spoon batter into a 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan greased only on bottom.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes; remove from pan and let cool completely.

title: honey raisin bread
directions: Preheat oven to slow (325°).
Grease a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Sift together the flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt into a medium-size bowl.
Beat together the egg, shortening and honey in a large bowl.
Stir in the flour mixture alternately with the milk and buttermilk, just until dry ingredients are moistened. Stir in the raisins and pecans.
Spoon into prepared pan.
Bake in preheated oven on slow for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Remove the bread from the pan to a wire rack.
Let stand overnight before slicing.

title: parmesan spinach
directions: Saute onion in margarine until translucent.
Add drained spinach; heat thoroughly.
Pour into serving dish and top with Parmesan cheese.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Mix all together, including 1/2 of grated cheese.
Place in ovenproof bowl.
Spread the other half of cheese on top.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Sometimes you need to lower temperature after 30 minutes to 300°.

title: red cabbage and apple salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine cabbage, apples, raisins and walnuts. In a measuring cup whisk together vinegar, oil, mustard,
sugar, salt and pepper.
Toss with salad.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 1 hour or more.
Makes 8 servings.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift together flour, cinnamon, soda and salt.
Blend eggs and sugar until fluffy.
Blend in carrots and oil.
Add flour mixture. Add optional ingredients if desired.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan or Bundt pan or 8-inch square pan or loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Frost with Glaze or Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: basic pancakes
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Slowly add to the remaining items; mix only until moistened.

title: easy divinity
directions: Boil water.
Mix dry frosting mix, corn syrup and vanilla to water.
Beat mixture on highest mixer speed for 5 minutes. Gradually stir in sugar while mixing on low speed.
Blend in pecans.
Spoon the mixture by teaspoon onto a cookie tin lined with wax paper.
Allow to sit uncovered.
Once mixture feels firm to touch, turn over.
Cover the tin and allow to sit over night.

title: zucchini sauce with garlic
directions: Cut zucchini
lengthwise in quarters, then cut in half. Bring 1 inch of water with bay leaves to a boil in a saucepan. Add zucchini
and
boil
for
minutes, covered.
Remove bay leaves and
discard.
Add remaining ingredients and put everything in a blender and blend well.
Serve over pasta.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix together butter, cake mix and 2 eggs and place in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Mix powdered sugar, cream cheese and 2 eggs and pour over first layer.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes. Let cool and top with 1/2 cup powdered sugar.

title: stuffed manicotti
directions: Brown beef, onion and garlic; drain and cool. Add Cheddar, cottage and Mozzarella cheeses and mayo. Mix well. Carefully spoon into shells and place in a large casserole dish. Cover with spaghetti sauce. Sprinkle with oregano. Sprinkle with extra Cheddar and Mozzarella cheeses. Cover and bake for 15 minutes at 350°. Uncover and bake an additional 15 minutes at 350°.

title: frozen banana salad
directions: Mix together the sour cream, lemon juice, sugar and salt.
To this, add the pineapple, cherries, pecans and bananas.
Freeze in cupcake papers in muffin tins or in 7 x 11-inch pan and cut into squares.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: orange  julius
directions: Place all ingredients in blender container.
Blend on high speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into glasses.
Makes 1 quart.

title: chocolate fat-free angel food cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Use directions on cake box for egg white packet.
Mix cake mix packet with cocoa and coffee; add slowly to egg whites after peaking.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes for regular sponge texture, less time for brownie texture.
Do not oil pan.
Use either Bundt or angel food cake pan.

title: beef and blue cheese casserole
directions: Microwave ground beef on High for 4-5 minutes and drain. Stir in soups, cheese and pepper.
Cook on High, covered for 7-8 minutes.
Serve over noodles and garnish with parsley.

title: fruit cake balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and shape into balls.

title: lime punch
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients.
Add pineapple juice.
Mix well and freeze in any size container.
To serve:
Pour ginger ale over partially thawed punch mix.

title: goulash(steelworkers hungarian beef)
directions: Heat oil in Dutch oven.
Saute onions until golden.
Add meat; brown lightly.
Add remaining ingredients except for the cornstarch and water.
Cover; simmer slowly for 1 1/2 to 3 hours until meat is tender.
Skim off fat.
Mix cornstarch and water; stir into meat gravy mixture.
Bring to a boil, still stirring. Stir while it boils, 2 minutes.
Serve with buttered noodles. Makes 6 servings.

title: cheesy biscuits
directions: Stir ingredients together.
Place in greased pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.

title: carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F.
Grease two 9" round layer cake pans; set aside.

title: cheesy baked ziti and vegetables
directions: Cook ziti/pasta according to package.
In medium saucepan over low heat, melt butter; remove from heat.
Stir in flour, mustard, salt and pepper until smooth.
Slowly stir in milk; return to heat.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils. Stir in half the cheese; over very low heat, cook just until cheese is melted.
Drain pasta thoroughly; stir into sauce.
Stir in scallions, broken zucchini and tomato.
Mix well.
Into 2-quart baking dish, pour pasta and vegetable mixture.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and paprika.
Bake 20 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 2-quart casserole.
Mix rice, corn, garlic, milk, chili powder, salt, pepper and 1 1/2 cups cheese.
Pour into casserole.
Place tomatoes on top.
Cook in oven for 35 minutes.
Remove.
Sprinkle on 1/2 cup cheese and cook 5 minutes longer.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Stew chicken until tender.
Remove bones and cut chicken into small pieces.
Add other ingredients and pour into baking dish (you'll need a deep dish).
Place uncooked pie crust on top.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes or until brown on top.

title: milky way ice cream
directions: Chop Milky Ways and pour 1/2 can Pet milk on them and melt in microwave.
Mix other ingredients.
Pour into freezer.
Fill to line with milk.
Freeze as instructed by freezer instruction.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream sugar, Crisco and oleo.
Add egg yolks, flour, soda, buttermilk and coconut.
Beat egg whites, then fold into the rest of the mixture.
Add vanilla and salt.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and ice.
This recipe will serve 8 people.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Heat oil in deep skillet or fryer.
Cut eggplant into thin slices.
Dip in egg.
Dip in flour.
Place slices into hot oil and cook until lightly browned.
Remove from oil and drain.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper, then cheese.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix all of the above ingredients, refrigerate.
Can be made a day ahead of serving.

title: saucepan brownies
directions: Melt shortening and chocolate in saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly.
Cool.

Beat in vanilla and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Sift flour and salt. Add nuts. Combine with chocolate mixture and blend. Turn into greased, waxed paper lined 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan. Bake in moderate oven at 325° for about 25 minutes. Turn out on cake rack; remove paper. Cool. Cut in squares.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Season chops with seasoned salt and black pepper.
Brown in skillet sprayed with Pam.
Drain; set aside.
Mix together hash browns, soup, onions, milk and cheese.
Season with seasoned salt and pepper.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch casserole dish sprayed with Pam. Bake covered with foil 1 hour at 350°.
Uncover and put 1/2 slice Velveeta cheese on each pork chop.
Return to oven until cheese melts on chops.

title: super quick peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together all in bowl until evenly mixed.
Roll into walnut-sized balls (smaller will make crispier cookies and larger balls will be chewier).
Place on cookie sheet (ungreased).
Press crisscross pattern into each cookie with sugar-dipped fork.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Yields 24 to 30 cookies.

title: baked chicken salad(yields 12 servings)
directions: Melt 1 stick of butter in pan and brown 2 cups of croutons in oven.
Combine all ingredients except cheese and 2 cups croutons. Pile chicken mixture in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with cheese and 2 cups croutons.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes in 425° oven. Cut into squares before serving.
Enjoy!

title: chicken stuffed shells
directions: In a large bowl combine soup and water.
Cook shells according to directions of package.
Prepare stuffing according to package directions.
Combine chicken, stuffing and mayo.
Pour about 2 c. of soup mix on the bottom of a 9 X 13 pan.
Stuff shells with chicken mixture.
Layer in pan.
Pour remaining soup on top.
Sprinkle with
cheese.
Best if made the day before. Bake in a 350 degree oven for 45 minutes.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour water over the oatmeal.
Let cool 20 minutes. Cream the sugars, margarine and oatmeal mixture.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake 40 minutes
at 350° in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: cauliflower italiano
directions: Defrost cauliflower under running water until separated.
Dry on paper towel.
Roll cauliflower in crumbs and arrange in single layer on pan.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs over cauliflower.
Add salt, pepper and garlic powder to taste.
Pour oil over cauliflower.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
About 20 minutes into cooking, turn with spatula.
Bake at 350°.
Time:
30 to 45 minutes.

title: tuna cake variations
directions: Mix all together and mold into patties.
Brown in skillet, about 10 minutes or less.

title: barbecue shrimp
directions: Thread shrimp on metal skewers.
Place skewers on grill over medium hot coals.
Grill 2 minutes on each side or until shrimp turn pink, brushing generously with barbecue sauce.

title: blackberry gravy
directions: Mix together in bowl until it thickens.
Serve over hot biscuits, ice cream, etc.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown beef and all spices, tomatoes and tomato paste.
Cook about 30 minutes.
Boil noodles; add olive oil to water.

title: candied yams
directions: Parboil and
cut potatoes in quarter-inch slices.
Cook the other ingredients
to
form
syrup.
Place	the
slices of potatoes in the syrup and simmer gently for one hour, then let syrup boil away slightly.

title: mam-ma's apple butter(mountain style)
directions: You will need a large 16-quart metal dish pan, 18 pint cans and lids (washed and heated), large stirring spoon, ladle, funnel and medium spoon.
Move oven rack on bottom (second notch).
Heat oven to 500°.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: Drain the fruit and set aside.
Slice oranges in half. Combine cottage cheese, Cool Whip and dry gelatin.
Stir well and add fruit.
Chill at least an hour.
May be served on lettuce.

title: chicken livers and mushrooms
directions: Simmer chicken livers in the water/stock until done.
Add onion, mushrooms, salt, pepper and wine.
Simmer for five (5) minutes.
You may thicken with a little cornstarch if so desired. Serves 4.

title: broccoli tuna roll-ups
directions: Combine milk and soup.
Set aside. Combine meat, broccoli, half of the cheese and 1/2 can of onions.
Stir in 3/4 cup of the soup. Divide the meat mixture evenly between the tortillas and roll up.
Place seam side down in a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour remaining soup over the tortillas.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes. Top tortillas with remaining cheese and onions. Bake, uncovered, for 5 minutes.

title: chicken divine
directions: Arrange broccoli in greased baking dish.
Place boned chicken on top (chicken can be boned before or after cooking in salt water).
Mix next 4 ingredients.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over top.
Bake at 350° until heated through and crumbs are browned, 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve with rice (1 cup uncooked rice = 4 servings).

title: green beans with water chestnuts
directions: Defrost green beans.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Place in greased casserole.
Cover.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 minutes.

title: pumpkin nut bread
directions: Put into 4 one pound coffee cans or 2 loaf pans. Fill half full.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let stand 10 minutes, then dump out.

title: mandarin cream cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into four greased 8-inch cake pans.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: coconut pie 1
directions: Bake in a 9-inch uncooked pie shell at 425° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and bake until firm.

title: fireside punch
directions: In a medium saucepan, bring cranberry juice and water to a boil.
Add cinnamon apple herbal tea bags; cover and brew 5 minutes.
Remove tea bags; stir in sugar.
Pour into mugs and garnish with cinnamon sticks and fresh cranberries.

title: toffee almond cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars. Add vanilla and eggs. Mix in the flour, baking soda and salt.
Stir in the toffee bits and almonds. Drop onto ungreased cookie sheets and bake 8-10 minutes.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Beat milk lightly and add lemon juice, pecans, coconut and pineapple.
Fold together with all of Cool Whip.
Fill pie crust. Add cherries to top of pie and chill.

title: fresh peach fried pies
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar, salt and water in a small saucepan until thoroughly dissolved.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thick and clear.
Add diced peaches and flavoring and set aside while preparing pastry.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Boil chicken in plenty of water.
Let the chicken set in broth until cool.
Chop chicken.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth (skim fat from broth first).
Drain the spaghetti and combine with the chicken.
Add bell pepper, onion, mushrooms and pimentos.

title: chicken divan
directions: Butter bottom of pan; put cooked broccoli on butter; lay chicken on top of broccoli.
Mix other ingredients except cheese and bread crumbs.
Pour mixed ingredients over chicken.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and top with cheese.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes to 45 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Combine crumbs, sugar and margarine; press onto bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: homemade stuffing
directions: Mix all together.
Mix up with hands like dough.
Keep folding for about 10 minutes.
Make out patties and fry in electric skillet until brown.
Put on cookie sheet and put in oven for 5 minutes to dry oil off.
Goes good with turkey or chicken.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Combine sugar and flour.
Add salad dressing, water and chocolate.	Beat well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and egg.
Add soda, vanilla and buttermilk, then flour, salt and cinnamon.
Beat well.
Stir in chopped rhubarb and 1/3 cup nuts (if desired).
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle top with mixture of 1/3 cup sugar, 1/3 cup nuts and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat 2 eggs.
Add 1 can of cream of mushroom soup and mix.
Add cup of mayonnaise and 1 cup grated sharp cheese.

title: tofu and brown rice
directions: Start rice.
Rinse tofu cakes, cube into 1 x 1 1/2-inch pieces. Place on
terry
towel
in	a single layer; cover with another towel.
Top
with
cookie
sheet and weight with heavy object.
Let sit
for 20 minutes while you prepare vegetables. Have everything handy.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and put into greased baking dish.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add cocoa, baking soda, hot water and salt.
Mix well.
Add flour and cold water; mix well. Put in a greased and floured large 9 x 13 x 2-inch cake pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken broccoli dish
directions: Tear chicken into pieces.
Layer into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer broccoli, then 2 cans of soup (do not dilute), next cheese, then onion rings.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: not crescent cookies
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients and 1 tablespoon water.
Stir in flour and nuts; mix well.
Shape into crescents.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool on rack, roll in powdered sugar.

title: natchez cookies
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and egg yolk; beat well.
Add flour and cinnamon; mix well.
Beat egg white until foamy; spread batter thin on cookie sheet.
Brush egg white on top; sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Bake at 300° for 25 to 30 minutes.
When done, remove from cookie sheet at once.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Beat butter and shortening together.
Gradually add sugars, creaming until mixture is light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Sift together dry ingredients and add alternately with milk and vanilla.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: southern style squirrel stew
directions: Wash and dry
squirrel	pieces.
Place 2 quarts boiling water with onions,
celery, salt and pepper.
Simmer, covered, for 2 hours or
until
squirrels	are nearly tender.
Add carrots, potatoes and
corn.
Simmer,
covered, for 30 minutes or until all are tender.
Blend	flour
with cold water to make a paste.
Then stir
into stew.
Cook until thickened.
Serves 6 people.

title: cottage potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients and add enough milk to moisten.
Top with bread or cracker crumbs and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Sprinkle over vegetables the salt and let stand overnight or 3 hours.
Drain off salt water.
Boil vinegar, sugar, mustard seed and turmeric.
Put pickles in and boil up and can.

title: easy carrot cake
directions: Combine cake mix, salad dressing, eggs, water and cinnamon, mixing at medium speed until well blended.
Stir in carrots and walnuts.
Pour in greased pan (13 x 9-inch).
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.
Cool and spread with frosting.

title: cherry chocolate cake
directions: Stir together cake mix, pie filling, extract and eggs.
Bake at 350° in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan for 25 to 30 minutes. While baking, mix sugar, margarine and milk over low heat; bring to boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add chocolate chips.
Stir until smooth and pour over warm cake.
Can also be baked in a greased and floured 15 x 10-inch pan for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: fried oysters
directions: Wash and drain fresh oysters.
Season with salt and pepper. Roll in flour.
Dip in beaten egg.
Roll in cracker crumbs.
Roll off surplus in colander.
Press each flat in original shape.
Drop into hot, deep fat and fry to a golden brown.
Drain well.

title: chocolate crinkle cookies
directions: Mix oil, melted chocolate and sugar.
Blend in 1 egg at a time until well mixed.
Add vanilla.
Measure flour.
Stir flour, baking powder and salt into oil mixture.
Chill.
Heat oven to 350°.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into confectioners sugar.
Roll in sugar and shape into balls.
Place 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: ice pops
directions: Dissolve first 3 ingredients in 2 cups hot water. Add 2 cups cold water.
Mix well and freeze in molds.

title: chocolate cheese delight
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes; cool.
Mix cream cheese and sugar together; fold in Cool Whip.

title: microwave caramel popcorn
directions: Pop the popcorn.
Put into a brown grocery bag.
Mix together the brown sugar, oleo, syrup and butter-vanilla flavoring.
Put the mixture in the microwave until it boils.
Add the baking soda and stir.
Microwave the mixture for another 2 minutes.
Pour the mixture over the popped corn in the brown bag.
Shake the bag. Microwave the brown bag with the popped corn and mixture for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes.
Shake and let cool.

title: cheeseball
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.
Enjoy!

title: better than sex cake
directions: In one 9 x 13-inch cake pan or two 9 x 9-inch cake pans, bake yellow cake according to box instructions.
(Because of a lot of ingredients, two 9 x 9-inch pans work better.)
In a saucepan, mix 20 ounce can of crushed pineapple with 1 cup of sugar and bring to boil.
Boil about 5 minutes.
Let pineapple mixture cool.
Let cake cool, then poke holes in cake with a toothpick.
Pour cooled pineapple mixture over cakes.
Make vanilla pudding (cooked) according to box instructions.
Let cool.
Pour over pineapple. Slice three bananas and place on top of pudding layer.
Cover all layers with Cool Whip.
Top with coconut, nuts, cherry halves as desired.
This cake must be kept refrigerated.

title: squash casserole
directions: Chop onions and squash.
Add salt and pepper.
Cook until tender.
Have a little liquid when strained.
Beat eggs.
Pour into squash.
Add butter.
Pour part of squash into bottom of casserole dish.
Add part of cheese and then the rest of squash. Top with rest of cheese and bake for 20 minutes.

title: frank's spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook bacon in 6-quart pan until brown.
Set aside, draining all but 1 to 2 tablespoons grease from pan.
Brown ground beef, discarding fat.
Stir in onions, green pepper and garlic.
Cook 10 minutes.

title: caramel chocolate brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Heat caramels and 1/4 cup of cream in double boiler, stirring constantly, until melted.
Keep warm.
Mix cake mix dry; add margarine, remaining cream and pecans.
Spread half of dough, 1 1/2 cups, in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 6 minutes.
Remove from oven; sprinkle chocolate chips over cake. Drizzle caramel over cake.
Add remaining cake by spoonful over top.
Spread evenly.
Bake until cake is slightly dry to touch, 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool completely.
Cut into 2 1/4 x 1-inch bars.

title: potato cheese soup
directions: Combine potatoes, onion and salt; cover with water (not too much water, just until the potatoes are covered).
Bring to a boil.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Place 24 mushrooms on cookie sheet.
Mix all the ingredients and stuff mushrooms.
Brush in butter and sprinkle in Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: bourbon dogs(appetizer)
directions: Combine ingredients and heat for 25 minutes in saucepan, or in 300° oven.
The links may be heated separately, if desired. Makes approximately 50 appetizers.
May be kept in crock-pot on low and reheated, if necessary.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, flour and salt.
Add other ingredients except vanilla.
Cook until thick, 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove from heat; add vanilla.
Pour in baked pie shell.
Top with meringue made with 4 egg whites, 1/2 cup sugar and a pinch of salt.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar a little at a time; add salt.
Beat until very stiff.
Pour on pie and bake at 400° until brown.

title: spicy pumpkin cheesecake
directions: Beat egg yolk and brush on crust.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven 5 minutes.
Set aside.
In a large mixer bowl, beat cream cheese, sugar and eggs on medium speed until smooth.
Add pumpkin and spices.
Continue mixing until well blended.
Spoon into prepared pie crust and bake at 350° until set, about 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool, then refrigerate several hours or overnight. Garnish with whipped cream and toasted pecan halves.
Serves 12.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix instant vanilla pudding and milk; heat slowly for 2 minutes.
Fill pie crust with pudding.
Mix powdered sugar and peanut butter until crumbly.
Put 1/2 of this mixture on top of vanilla pudding.
Then put the Cool Whip on top of powdered sugar-peanut butter mixture.
Sprinkle the remaining 1/2 of the powdered sugar-peanut butter mixture on top of the Cool Whip. Chill before serving.

title: blintz souffle for 6
directions: Lay butter in bottom of dish.
Lay blintzes (frozen) on top of butter. Beat other ingredients together and pour in casserole over blintzes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: glazed fresh strawberry pie
directions: Place sliced strawberries in a bowl; add sugar and lemon juice. Stir to dissolve sugar. Allow to sit 15 or 20 minutes and make a juice.

title: cherry-pecan-pineapple muffins
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt, baking soda and cinnamon together.
Set aside.
In large mixing bowl, mix together eggs, sugar and vegetable oil until well blended.
Add gradually to flour mixture until smooth.
Next, add pineapple with juice, cherries, cut in half and chopped pecans.
Place mixture into paper cupcake cups.
Place pan in a 350° oven until muffins spring up in middle, approximately 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together all of above.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with Ritz crackers and butter.

title: stuffed pizza
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Grease rectangular 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cook and stir sausage and ground beef until brown. Drain and set aside. Mix baking mix and water until dough forms. Divide into 2 parts, one slightly larger than the other.
On surface dusted with baking mix, roll larger portion of dough into 16 x 14-inch rectangle. Fold in thirds.
Place in dish; unfold.
Press on bottom and up sides of dish.
Sprinkle with 1 cup cheese. Cover with 3/4 cup pizza sauce. Add meat mixture and other toppings. Cover with 1/2 cup of the cheese.
Roll remaining dough into a 13 x 9-inch rectangle; fold in thirds.
Place over cheese in dish; unfold.
Press bottom and top together to seal.
Make small slits in top crust. Spread crust with remaining pizza sauce and cheese.
Bake 22 to 25 minutes until crust is golden.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Combine all ingredients together and blend for 5 minutes. Pour into greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: pimento cheese
directions: Leave cheese out overnight to soften.
Large grate the cheese and blend everything together.

title: cheese meat loaf
directions: Beat eggs in a large bowl.
Add milk and bread, torn into pieces.
Let soak a few minutes.
Chop onion.
Mix all ingredients well.
Shape in a loaf in a baking pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Makes 6 servings.

title: baked squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender.
Saute onion and bell pepper in margarine.
Mix together well beaten eggs, crackers, milk and dash of pepper.
Drain squash and mash.
Add remaining ingredients and put in 8 x 12-inch buttered Pyrex pan.
Cook about 20 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and add cheese.
Return to oven for about 10 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: angel cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugars until light and fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla; mix well.
Add dry ingredients and stir in nuts. Drop from spoon onto baking sheet.
Bake at 350°; takes 10 to 15 minutes.

title: southern ham and biscuits
directions: Cut 1 cup butter into flour until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Stir in buttermilk until dry ingredients are moistened. Knead dough 3 or 4 times on lightly floured surface.
Roll dough to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with a 1 1/2-inch biscuit cutter. Place on lightly greased baking sheets.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Brush with melted butter.
Serve with ham and mustard.

title: garlic balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together but pecans.
Roll into balls. Roll balls in pecans.
Refrigerate in tightly sealed plastic container.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Select bite size mushrooms. Wash and dry completely.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over mushrooms.
Marinate 2 hours, stirring occasionally. Drain and serve on toothpicks.

title: veal louisa
directions: Trim away any fat from meat.
Cut into medium size chunks. Combine paprika, salt, rosemary and flour; dredge meat thoroughly. Heat oil in heavy skillet or Dutch oven.
Brown meat on both sides over moderately high heat.
Add garlic, onion, broth and wine.
Cover tightly and simmer until meat is tender, about 1 1/2 hours.
Just before serving, stir in sour cream, using proportion according to your own taste.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: roasted chicken
directions: Rub mixture into chicken, inside and out.
Seal in plastic bag and refrigerate overnight.
Stuff chicken with onions and roast, uncovered, at 250° for 5 hours.
Baste with juices.

title: homemade eagle brand milk
directions: Place all ingredients into blender.
Blend until smooth. Store in refrigerator.
Yields 14 ounces.

title: old-fashioned bread pudding
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Put bread crumbs in 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Blend in remaining ingredients and stir.
Place baking dish in pan of hot water, about 1-inch deep and bake for 45 to 50 minutes until knife inserted comes clean.

title: baked apples
directions: Cut off a slice at top and bottom of each apple; core each apple.
Butter the top and dip in vanilla flavored sugar.
Put apples in heavy baking dish.
Put large slice of lemon peel in each cavity.
Fill cavity with dark brown sugar.
Sprinkle with cinnamon over top.
Place a vanilla bean in dish along with 1 or 2 cinnamon sticks.
Bake in a 400° oven until cracks appear around the rim of apples (approximately 30 to 40 minutes depending on type of apples.)
Serve warm or cool with vanilla ice cream.

title: bread and butter pudding
directions: Break bread into bite size pieces and put in pan of melted butter.
Stir until all butter is soaked into bread.
Beat eggs; add sugar and blend well.
Add vanilla and milk.
Stir until all ingredients are well mixed.
Put buttered bread into baking dish and pour liquid mix over bread mixture.
Mash bread down into liquid a few minutes to soak up some of the milk.
Sprinkle raisins and nutmeg on top if you wish.
Bake in 400° oven until firm.

title: chow mein candy
directions: Cook chips over low heat until melted.
Stir in nuts and chow mein noodles.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper to cool.

title: squash dressing
directions: Cook squash and onion together.
Drain and mash.
Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Place potatoes, margarine and milk in a large pot.
Add Cheez Whiz.
Heat on medium heat.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: vietnamese fried eggs(cha trung)
directions: In a bowl mix eggs with salt, sugar, sauce, pepper and green onion.
Using low fire, put oil in a pan and when hot, fry the chopped onion until golden and saute the sausage for about 5 minutes.
Then pour egg mixture and spread over the whole pan. Wait until it cooks and serve.

title: country-style vanilla ice cream
directions: In large mixing bowl, beat eggs until foamy.
Gradually add sugar; beat until thickened.
Add cream, vanilla and salt and mix thoroughly.
Pour into ice cream maker container; add milk to line on container and stir well.
Follow your ice cream maker instructions for proper freezing.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter and both sugars until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs; add vanilla.
Add oats, cornflakes, coconut and nuts.
Mix until well blended.

title: south of the border casserole
directions: Split wieners lengthwise, but do not cut through.
Divide green chilis and cheese in equal amounts to each wiener.
Sift flour, baking powder, sugar and salt.
Stir in cornmeal.
Combine milk, eggs and oil in small bowl and stir until smooth.
Pour into buttered 13 X 9 X 2 baking dish.
Tilt pan to allow batter to spread evenly to corners.
Arrange wieners in double row over batter.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.
Let cool 10 minutes.
Serve with salsa topping.

title: linda davis' hash brown casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter casserole dish. Combine first 6 ingredients well and place in casserole dish.
Sprinkle crushed cornflakes on top and bake for 50 minutes.

title: twenty-four hour fruit salad
directions: Drain all fruit well.
Beat egg yolks; add vinegar, pineapple juice, salt, sugar and butter.
Cook, stirring constantly until thickens and coats spoon (about 10 minutes).
Cool to warm, then pour over fruit and marshmallows.
Mix gently.
Fold in whipping cream.
Chill 24 hours.

title: barbecue
directions: Boil the meat in a crock-pot 6 to 8 hours or overnight.
Let the meat cool and pick all the fat and bone out by hand.
Shred the meat.
Add the other ingredients and serve with Pam's Cole Slaw (see salads).

title: pepper strips
directions: Put peppers in quart jar, taking out seeds and cutting them in strips.
Add salt and olive oil to jar.
Bring sugar, vinegar and pickling spice to boil.
Pour mixture over peppers.
Use more hot peppers than mild.
Good with all types of veggies.

title: popsicles
directions: Mix all ingredients. Store in airtight container.
To make, add 3/4 cup boiling water to 6 tablespoons of mix, then add 3/4 cup cold water.
Pour into molds or ice trays and freeze.

title: easy peanut butter chocolate fudge
directions: In a large bowl, place creme drops, peanut butter and oleo. Cover and microwave long enough to melt the candy.
Stir until well blended and spread in buttered 8 x 8-inch dish.
(This may be made in saucepan over low direct heat on top of stove.)

title: chocolate trifle
directions: Bake mix as directed. Break up in 1/2-inch pieces.
Place half in bottom of bowl. Alternate other ingredients. Top with Cool Whip.

title: stevo's salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl; stir together.
Let sit for at least 2 hours in fridge.

title: corn relish
directions: Combine sugar, vinegar, salt, Tabasco, celery seed and mustard seed.
Bring to a boil; boil for 2 minutes.
Combine with remaining ingredients.
Chill for 24 hours.

title: breakfast ham and egg casserole
directions: Spread butter on both sides of bread.
Cut bread into cubes. In a big bowl, combine bread, ham, cheese, salt and pepper. Separately beat eggs until foamy.
Stir in milk with eggs.
Add eggs to bread mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Before baking, remove cover.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 1 hour.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: In large bowl, mix flour, corn meal and salt and pepper. Add tomatoes and gently stir to evenly coat tomatoes. Transfer to a large, hot skillet with enough oil to nearly cover then. Once well browned on one side, turn and brown the other side. Drain on paper towels and serve hot.

title: cookies and cream
directions: Mix ice cream and Cool Whip.
Blend in crushed Oreos.
Place in large casserole dish.
Freeze and serve.

title: chocolate fudge(heritage recipe)
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk.
Bring to rolling boil. Cook rapidly 5 minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly.

title: homemade brunswick stew
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Mix all ingredients with beef and cook for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: fudge dipped strawberries
directions: Wash and stem strawberries and place a toothpick in each; place on waxed paper on countertop.

title: aggression cookies
directions: Put all ingredients in a large bowl and mash, mix, squeeze and knead, adding little flour to hands so dough doesn't stick.
Form into small balls.
Place on cookie sheet.
Butter bottom of small juice glass and dip in granulated sugar or colored sugar and mash the cookie balls flat.
The more you knead the dough the better the cookies.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add egg yolks, then milk.
Cook until thick all ingredients.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with 3 beaten egg whites and 2 tablespoons of sugar.
Top pie!
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: sweet potato candy
directions: Mix all ingredients, except the peanut butter, into a dough. (Add a little extra 4X sugar to stiffen the dough, if needed.) Roll out the dough 1/4-inch thick on to a floured surface.
Spread the peanut butter evenly over the rolled-out dough.
Start at one end and roll it over like a jelly roll.
Cut into slices approximately 1/2-inch wide.
Let set until slices are firm.

title: chop suey
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan or Dutch oven.
Add hamburg, salt and pepper.
Cook on medium, stirring occasionally, while meat is cooking.
When meat is cooked, add celery and onions, 1 1/4 cups water and La Choy brown gravy.
Turn up heat so it will boil.
Turn heat to low and cook 20 minutes or until celery is crispy.
Add chestnuts, egg noodles and bean sprouts.
Turn up heat so it will boil again.
Then turn down to low and cook 10 to 15 minutes.
Add cornstarch in cup to make a smooth paste by adding La Choy sauce. Then add to chop suey.
Shut off and let stand 5 to 10 minutes. Serve with chow mein noodles.

title: creamy chicken manicotti
directions: Cook manicotti shells according to package directions, omitting the salt.
Drain; set aside.
Combine soup and sour cream; mix well.
Combine half of sour cream mixture and chicken; mix well.
Reserve remaining soup mixture; set aside.
Stuff manicotti shells with chicken mixture.
Place in a greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Saute onion and mushrooms in butter in a large skillet until tender; set aside.
Combine water and bouillon granules, stirring until dissolved.
Add to reserved soup mixture, mixing well.
Stir soup mixture into mushroom mixture; mix well. Spoon over manicotti.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 15 minutes. Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese; bake an additional 5 minutes. Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: pecan cookies(russian tea cakes)
directions: Cream the butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour, then add the nuts.
Roll into balls about the size of walnuts.
Put on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 1 hour in slow oven (250°).
Roll in powdered sugar while still warm.

title: salsa spread
directions: Place block of cream cheese in serving bowl and pour salsa on the cheese.
Serve with sturdy corn chips.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix gelatin in boiling water until dissolved.
Add cream cheese and other ingredients.
Mold and chill until firm.
Unmold; garnish as desired.

title: crock-pot enchiladas
directions: Do not add water to soup.

title: strawberry cream roll
directions: Lightly grease 15 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan. Line with waxed paper.

title: layered mexican dip
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and salt and pepper in bowl; mix well.
Spread refried beans in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Sprinkle with taco seasoning mix.
Add layer of avocado mixture and layers of sour cream and remaining ingredients, in order listed.
Yields 8 servings.

title: orange glaze cake
directions: Mix and pour over hot cake.
Pour into small holes formed on top of cake made with fork or ice pick.

title: texas pinto beans
directions: Wash beans and soak overnight.
Cover beans with 2 inches of water; simmer, covered, with other ingredients until tender. Taste for seasonings and serve hot.

title: creamy new york cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Moisten fingers with water and press cookie crumbs over bottom and slightly up sides of 9 or 10-inch spring-form pan.
Chill while preparing remaining ingredients.

title: tiny tuna pizzas
directions: Combine first five ingredients, mix well.
Spread on rye slices.
Place on baking sheet and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 425° for 4 minutes or until heated.
Serve hot.

title: rainbow cookies
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Break up cookie dough into large bowl.
Add 1/2 cup oats, candy baking bits and raisins and mix well.
Roll cookie dough into 2-inch balls and place 3-inches apart on ungreased large cookie sheet.
Flatten each ball to form a 3-inch round.
Sprinkle with oats for garnish.
Bake 14 minutes or until set and dry in center.
Cool 2 minutes and remove from cookie sheet.
Makes 12 large cookies.

title: cinnamon oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together first 5 ingredients.
Stir together flour, baking soda and cinnamon.
Mix with creamed mixture.
Stir in oats and raisins.
Mix well.
Drop batter by teaspoon onto oiled cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add cranberry sauce; mix until well blended.
Add celery, apple and nuts.
Put into one large mold.
Serve on lettuce.

title: cranberry pineapple salad
directions: In a large bowl dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Break up and stir cranberry sauce.
Add pineapple, orange juice and lemon juice.
Chill until partially set.
Stir in nuts.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares; need to put in a 11 x 7 x 2-inch pan before it sets up.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown the ground beef and drain off fat.
Add the next 8 ingredients.
Simmer for 1/2 hour.
Stir about twice while this simmers.
Cook noodles and drain.
Mix the cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese and the beaten eggs.
Layer in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan 1/2 noodles, 1/2 cheese filling, 1/2 the Mozzarella and 1/2 the meat sauce.
Repeat the layers and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: carolina delight cookies
directions: Combine sugar, butter, cocoa and milk in
a saucepan and bring to a boil for 1 1/2 minutes. Remove from heat and add oatmeal and peanut butter. Stir until well mixed.
Drop onto wax paper.

title: greek lemon chicken
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in large bowl to make marinade. Add chicken.
Cover and chill at least 8 hours.
Remove chicken from marinade.
Reserve marinade.
Place flour in plastic bag. Add chicken and shake to coat.
Heat oil in large skillet.
Add chicken and brown on all sides.
Drain on paper towel.
Place in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pour marinade over; cover with foil and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream the first 5 ingredients together.
Add flour, salt and baking powder.
Place half of batter in Bundt pan and sprinkle the last 4 ingredients in, then add remaining batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: stickens
directions: Roll out biscuit dough very thin.
Put a layer of sugar or margarine, cinnamon and pecans.
Roll up and cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Bake at 350° for about 35 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: hot spiced percolator punch
directions: Combine pineapple juice, cocktail, water and sugar in 30-cup automatic coffeemaker.
Place the remaining ingredients in basket assembly.
Plug in and perk.
Serve piping hot.

title: peanut butter chocolate bonbons
directions: Combine sugar, graham cracker crumbs, pecans or walnuts and coconut in small pan.
Soften butter or margarine and peanut butter and put over coconut mixture and blend.
Shape into balls about 1-inch size.
Set aside on waxed paper.

title: rancho sausage supper
directions: In large skillet, fry sausage until browned.
Drain.
Add onions and peppers and cook slowly for 5 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes, sour cream, macaroni, chili powder, salt and sugar. Cover and simmer for 30 minutes, stirring frequently until macaroni is done.
Serve hot.

title: special jello salad
directions: Mix the gelatine with cold water to dissolve.
Save juice from fruit to make 1 cup; add 2 cups of water and the puddings.
Heat, stirring constantly, until boiling.
Add gelatine mixture and beat thoroughly.
Add fruits and refrigerate.
Double recipe for a 9 x 13-inch pan.
This jello will not melt.

title: overnight buttermilk biscuits
directions: Cream together the sugar and margarine. (I use a fork.) Sift the remaining dry ingredients with the first 2 cups of flour just to get them all in and well mixed. Alternately combine some flour and buttermilk to the sugar/margarine mix. Use all the buttermilk and enough flour to form a soft and slightly moist dough. Place dough in a covered, not sealed, container in refrigerator for anywhere from 4 hours to 2 weeks. The dough will rise while it is cold. Use some or all of the dough any time.

title: reuben sandwiches
directions: Spread dressing on bread.
Arrange beef, cheese and sauerkraut on bread and top with the rest of the bread.

title: orange-champagne swizzle
directions: Mix champagne and orange juice and serve immediately.

title: spoon bread
directions: Add corn meal to scalded milk, stirring constantly to prevent lumping.
Combine butter; blend until smooth.
Cool slightly.
Add well beaten egg yolks, beating while adding.
Combine salt, sugar and baking powder, then stir in.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into a hot baking or casserole dish.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Cook for 30 minutes.
Serve hot.
Bread will be soft; serve with spoon.

title: boyfriend chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in hot water over low heat; cool.
Cream shortening with sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in cooled chocolate.
Sift flour with salt and soda; add alternately with milk to dry ingredients.
Blend until smooth.
Pour into prepared layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: pesto sauce
directions: Put all ingredients in blender or food processor.
Puree. Serve over hot pasta or fettuccini noodles.
Do not cook pesto or it will turn very dark.
Can be frozen and sliced off as needed for smaller amounts.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix dry cake mix and dry gelatin together.
Blend well eggs with vegetable oil.
Combine flour into nuts and add to mixture. Add strawberries.

title: choco-mallow brownies
directions: Cream butter in a large mixing bowl.
Add sugar, beating until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating at medium speed of electric mixer.
Set mixture aside.
Combine flour and next 3 ingredients; add to creamed mixture, stirring well.
Stir in vanilla and chopped pecans.
Spoon batter into greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Remove from oven; sprinkle with marshmallows.
Cover with foil; allow to stand for 5 minutes to melt marshmallows.
Remove foil.
Spread frosting on top of warm brownies; cool and cut into squares.

title: west african stew
directions: Boil
chicken
until tender and remove from broth. Heat palm oil until it "smokes out" and becomes translucent.	(Use electric frypan
out
of doors since smoke may make breathing difficult for a few moments.) Add onion and pepper as soon as oil "clears" and simmer for	10
minutes.
(It will stop smoking.) Add the oil mixture to broth. Cook butter beans and add. Cut up vegetables and put
them
in
broth to cook. Add tomato sauce. Simmer 15 minutes. Mix
peanut
butter
with water and stir into stew.
Add seasoning.	Add cooked chicken and simmer until it thickens a bit. Serve hot over cooked rice.

title: pecan cream cheese pie
directions: In a bowl, combine pecans, coconut and butter.
Pour onto an ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 10 minutes or until golden brown, stirring occasionally; cool.
In a mixing bowl, beat the cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spoon into pastry shell.
Sprinkle with coconut mixture.
Drizzle with caramel topping. Refrigerate for 2 hours.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: my favorite pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Beat eggs slightly. Add sugar, syrup, vanilla and margarine. Mix until well blended. Add pecans. Pour into pie crust. Bake 55 minutes.

title: french silk frosting
directions: In small mixer bowl, blend sugar, butter, chocolate and vanilla on low speed.
Gradually add milk; beat until smooth and fluffy.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: You will also need jars (size of your choice), lids and rings.

title: lemon souffle
directions: Combine and beat egg yolks, oleo, sugar, flour, lemon and milk.
Beat egg whites and fold into mixture with a pinch of salt. Bake in buttered casserole in hot water at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes. Chill and serve with whipped cream.
(This also makes a good parfait.)

title: banana cream pie
directions: Stir together sugar, cornstarch and salt in saucepan.
Blend milk and egg yolks.
Stir into sugar mixture.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Blend in margarine and vanilla.
Cool.
Peel and slice bananas and mix into pudding. Pour into baked pie shell.
Cool 2 hours.
Serve with whipped cream or meringue on top.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring sugar and milk to a boil until it forms soft ball stage. Take off heat, add marshmallows and peanut butter.
Mix.
Add vanilla.
Pour onto greased pan, cool and cut.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Slice green peppers, onions and raw potatoes.
Saute in small amount of olive oil until potatoes are near done.
Add sliced zucchini and cut up tomatoes.
Simmer all ingredients together until zucchini is soft.

title: fruit and angel dessert
directions: Break cake into bite size pieces.
Arrange half of the cake pieces in bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with half of the undrained pineapple and cherries.
Spread half of the dessert topping over all; top with half of the coconut.
Repeat layers, ending with dessert topping and coconut.
Cover; refrigerate overnight.
Makes 12 servings.

title: strawberry jello mold
directions: Mix together; put half in 9 x 9-inch pan.
Spread on 2 cartons of sour cream, then add rest of Jell-O mixture.

title: pork chops with apples
directions: Fry pork chops until brown; sprinkle with salt and sage. Core apples and cut into rings. Put chops in baking dish; top with apple. Sprinkle sugar. In skillet, add flour to fat; blend. Add raisins and pour over chops. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour. Delicious....

title: banana bread
directions: Cream together sugar and oil;
add
beaten egg, bananas and milk.
Sift dry ingredients together and
fold into creamy mixture.
If using nuts, add to creamy mixture
before the dry ingredients.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake about 60 minutes at 350°.

title: hammy dip
directions: Cream softened cheese; mix remaining ingredients.
Use as dip or on crackers.

title: easy cake
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into an ungreased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: regal cranberry cheese cake
directions: Combine crumbs, sugar and margarine; press into bottom of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.
Combine cream cheese, sugar, flour and vanilla, mixing at medium speed on electric mixer until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Blend in sour cream; pour over crust.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes.
Loosen cake from rim of pan. Cool before removing rim of pan.

title: monkey bread
directions: Combine shortening, boiling water, sugar and salt in a bowl and let cool.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water; beat eggs and add to yeast mixture.
Add yeast mixture to shortening.
Gradually add flour.
Mix thoroughly; cover and let rise 1 hour.
Knead dough down.
Pinch off chunks and dip into 1 stick melted butter or margarine.
Drop chunks in tube pan.
(Only use 3/4 dough in tube pan; whole recipe makes pan too full.)
If you wish to have a fancy bread, roll chunks in a mixture of cinnamon/sugar before putting into tube pan.
Let rise for 1 hour in a warm place.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool about 5 minutes and turn out onto a plate.
Dribble a glaze of powdered sugar and water over bread.
(I leave the icing off for dinner rolls.)

title: zucchini cobbler
directions: Cut butter into flour and sugar until it resembles coarse crumbs.
Put half of mixture into 8-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: pork chops creole
directions: Brown pork chops.
Remove from pan and saute onion and bell pepper in oil.
Place pork chops over onion and bell pepper.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce and water.
Simmer over low heat for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve chops and gravy over rice.

title: ice cream
directions: Mix eggs, Eagle Brand milk, sugar and vanilla with enough milk to blend.
Mix good in blender.

title: amish baked chicken
directions: Place the oil and butter in a shallow cooking pan (a jelly roll pan or cookie sheet).
Place in preheated 375° oven to melt. Set aside.

title: sausage balls
directions: Cut cheese into cubes; place in top of double broiler.
Cook over hot water, stirring frequently until melted.
Place sausage, Bisquick and cheese in large mixing bowl; mix well.
Shape into small balls and place on cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated oven for 15 minutes.
May be frozen before baking.
Place on cookie; freeze until firm, then place in freezer bags.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed on box.
Combine pineapple and sugar and cook until thickened.
Pour over cake.
Prepare pudding according to package directions and pour over pineapple.
Top with Dream Whip prepared according to package directions.
Refrigerate.

title: chewy cake
directions: Melt shortening and butter over low heat. Remove from heat and mix in sugar, eggs and vanilla. Stir in flour and nuts. Spread in pan and bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°. Cool before cutting.

title: country cornmeal bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Blend eggs, milk, butter and honey. Add to dry ingredients, stirring until moistened.
Pour into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake in a 400° oven for 30 minutes, or until done and brown.

title: fish in beer batter
directions: Beat together biscuit mix, beer, egg and salt. Coat fish fillets with batter. Skillet fry in hot oil until done, 4 to 5 minutes on each side.

title: copper pennies
directions: Layer carrots, bell pepper and onion in casserole dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Let set for 4 hours or overnight.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix meal, milk, oil and eggs.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch roasting pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 400° until golden brown.

title: spinach salad
directions: Wash and dry spinach, then tear into bite size pieces. Then add rest of the ingredients. Use dressing following.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into 4 parts.
Combine sugar and 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon.
Roll biscuit pieces in mixture.
Oil Bundt pan and place biscuits in bottom.
Melt oleo; add brown sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Slowly pour mixture over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Turn out on plate.

title: kielbasa(crock-pot)
directions: Mix cornstarch and Coke together.
Add ketchup and mix.
Put in crock-pot and simmer for 2 hours.

title: caramel-layered brownies
directions: Microwave chocolate and butter in large bowl on High 2 minutes or until butter is melted.
Stir until chocolate is completely melted.
Stir sugar into melted chocolate mixture.
Mix in eggs and vanilla until well blended.
Stir in flour.
Remove 1 cup of batter; set aside.
Spread remaining batter in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with chips and 1 cup of the nuts.
Microwave caramels and milk in same bowl on High 4 minutes, stirring after 2 minutes.

title: fast and easy chili con queso
directions: Heat all ingredients over low heat, mixing well.
Use as a dip with flour tortillas.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Bring all
ingredients	to
a boil. Reduce heat. Simmer for 5 minutes. Serve with cubes of chicken or pork.

title: hash
directions: Cook stew beef in crock-pot at 200° for 24 hours. Pull off fat and tear apart with fingers. Mix together bacon drippings, brown sugar, butter, Worcestershire sauce, catsup, black pepper, onions, vinegar, mustard, salt, beef broth and liquid smoke. Cook together until onions are done, then add meat and simmer 1 hour.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Cream together sugar, flour and softened butter until smooth. Add 2 slightly beaten egg yolks, juice of lemon and milk.
Fold in beaten thick egg whites and then pour into pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 8 minutes and at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cottage cheese pakoras
directions: Sift graham flour; add water to make a batter of coating consistency.
Beat the batter until it floats in the water; add seasonings.
Cut the cottage cheese into small pieces size 1 1/2 x 3/4-inch and sprinkle seasonings on it.
Coat the cheese pieces with batter and deep-fry to golden brown.

title: cheese strata
directions: Butter bread, alternate layers of bread and cheese in greased 12 x 7 x 2-inch pan, ending with cheese.
Mix remaining ingredients, pouring over layers.
Chill 6 hours or overnight. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown hamburger with onions.
Line bottom and sides of 12 x 9-inch baking dish with flour tortillas (about 6).
Pour hamburger mixture over tortillas.
Pour Ranch beans on top of hamburger.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of cheese.
Cover with another layer flour tortillas.
Mix Ro-tel tomatoes and chicken soup in another bowl and pour evenly on top of tortillas. Bake for 25 minutes.
Take out and cover with remaining cheese. Bake 10 more minutes.
Wah Lah!

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in
the	1/3
cup of water.
Put soda in the milk.
Make well in sifted flour.
Put Crisco in the well. Pour milk, yeast
and
sugar
in
well.	With
hand, mix until dough is stiff
and
elastic
like.
Place in refrigerator 24 hours.
Roll and
use
as needed like you would biscuit dough. Will keep 4 or 5 days in refrigerator.

title: secret cake
directions: Mix the sugar and plain flour well.
Bring to boil the margarine, Crisco, water and cocoa.
Pour hot mixture over sugar and flour; blend well.
Add the remaining ingredients with flour mixture; beat well.
Grease a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes only (according to stove test for doneness).
While cake is baking, make icing.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place into greased pie plate.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 325°.
Makes 1 pie.

title: barnyard cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat together until fluffy the almond extract, shortening, brown sugar, milk, vanilla and egg.
In a separate bowl, combine flour, salt and soda.
Add flour mixture to other ingredients, blending well.
Stir in chips, pecans and cereal.
Place rounded teaspoonfuls of dough on an ungreased cooking sheet, leaving 2 inches between cookies.
Bake 10 to 13 minutes or until golden around the edges.
Makes 5 dozen cookies.

title: sugarless cake
directions: Slow boil the raisins in water and juice until liquid is gone. Add applesauce, sweetener and oil; then add eggs.
Mix well. Blend in soda and flour.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Pour into a greased square cake pan and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: coconut-pecan frosting
directions: Combine milk, sugar, egg yolks, and butter in a heavy saucepan; bring to a boil and cook over medium heat for 12 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla, coconut, and pecans, stir until frosting is cool and of spreading consistency.
Yield: enough for one 3 layer cake.

title: espresso kisses
directions: Heat oven to 250°.
Line baking sheets with foil.
On medium speed, beat egg whites until peaks form.
Beat in sugar gradually, along with pinch of salt.
Add lemon zest, Espresso and vanilla extract.
Beat on high.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown beef and onion. Drain really well. Add other ingredients, using liquids from all cans. Simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Combine the cake and pudding mixes, then add the eggs, oil and 7-Up. Bake at 350°f. 180°c. gas mark 4 for 30 minutes.
Makes a 3 layer cake.

title: chocolate lush
directions: Layer in bowl as follows:
Crumble cake on bottom.
Sprinkle Kahlua on cake.
Spread prepared chocolate pudding on cake.
Spread Cool Whip on pudding.
Sprinkle Heath or Skor bars onto Cool Whip. Continue layering ingredients until gone.
Top with cherries.

title: bourbon-pecan-pumpkin pie
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes; reduce heat to 350° and bake 40 minutes or until set, then cool.

title: halushki(noodles and cabbage)
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Chop cabbage very fine and fry in butter, stirring quite frequently, until browned.
Mix noodles, cabbage and bacon and pour about 4 to 6 tablespoons melted butter over it.

title: peanut butter cream pie
directions: Cook until thick, then add 1/2 cup peanut butter and pour into baked pie shell.
Do not skimp on the peanut butter.

title: chocolate oatmeal chip cookies
directions: Soften margarine, then beat margarine and sugars until creamy. Add eggs, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Add flour, soda and salt; mix well.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in 375° oven for 9 to 10 minutes for a chewy cookie or 12 to 13 minutes for a crisp cookie.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: pistachio freeze
directions: Mix together.
Pour into glass pan and chill thoroughly.

title: pot roast
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
In a 5-quart Dutch oven or roasting pan, heat oil over medium-high heat.
Brown meat about 5 minutes on each side.
Drain excess fat, if desired.
Sprinkle pepper on all sides of meat.
Add 1 onion, 1 stalk of celery and bay leaf to meat.
Dissolve bouillon in 3/4 cup hot water and pour over roast. Bring to boil; cover.
Bake at 325° for 60 minutes.
Add remaining vegetables; cover and bake an additional hour and a half or until vegetables and meat are tender.

title: breakfast pie
directions: Cook sausage until done.
Crumble, then drain.
Prepare a 9-inch pie shell.
Mix cheese and sausage; sprinkle in shell. Lightly beat eggs in bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients; add to egg mixture.
Pour in shell.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes. Cool on rack 10 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: lentil soup
directions: Cook onion and green pepper in olive oil until golden.
Stir in flour and cook until bubbling.
Do not brown.
Add tomatoes, carrots, salt, lentils and water.
(Add lentils right from package.)
Cook, covered, over low heat for 2 hours.
Stir occasionally.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: steak in rich gravy
directions: Brown steak.
Pour onion soup mix over steak and cook 5 minutes.
Then pour cream of mushroom soup (put soup in bowl and add warm water) over meat and onion soup mix.
Cook 1 to 2 hours at 250° in electric skillet.
Add 1/4 water if needs to be thinned.

title: jack robinson's cake
directions: Sift the flour; measure and add baking powder, salt and sugar. Sift again in a large mixing bowl.
Add shortening, milk and vanilla.
Beat 2 minutes with an electric mixer at low speed.
Add unbeaten eggs.
Beat 1 minute longer.
Pour into an 8 1/2 x 13 1/2 x 2-inch pan which has been greased.

title: orange and rum salad
directions: Peel oranges and cut up into small pieces.
Put into a mixing bowl and add syrup, rum and cinnamon, tossing gently.
Cover and refrigerate overnight or in a few hours until flavor penetrates the oranges well.
Put into pretty salad bowls and add toasted walnuts.
Remember to toast walnuts; this gives it a very good crunchy texture.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: Heat oil in a wok or large frying pan.
Over medium-high heat, saute chicken.
Cut pepper and onion into strips and add to chicken.
Add water and taco seasoning.
Simmer for 10 minutes. Squirt the juice of a lime and serve in warm tortillas.
Add the desired toppings.

title: potato, bacon, cheese soup
directions: Cook bacon in pan or microwave.
Boil water; add potatoes, onions, bacon with half of grease or less, salt, pepper and celery salt or celery.
Cook potatoes until tender.

title: quick cake(dutch chocolate)
directions: Put in 9-inch square pie dish which has been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.

title: berry cream coffee cake
directions: Cut cream cheese and butter into biscuit mix until crumbly. Blend in the 1/3 cup milk.
Turn onto floured surface.
Knead 8 to 10 times.
On waxed paper, roll dough to an 8 x 12-inch rectangle.
Turn onto greased baking sheet.
Remove paper.
Spread preserves down center of dough.
Make 2 1/2-inch cuts at 1-inch intervals on long sides.
Fold strips over filling.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: turkey hot dish
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in butter.
Cook rice in 2 1/2 cups water and bouillon cubes.
Simmer for about 25 minutes.
Mix rice, onion, pepper, mushrooms, water chestnuts and turkey in a casserole.
Stir in mushroom soup.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: polish mistakes
directions: Brown and drain meats.
Put back in skillet and add remaining 3 ingredients. Melt cheese slowly. Spread on party rye bread. Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: hot coleslaw
directions: In a medium frying pan over medium heat, add olive oil and melt butter.
Stir in coleslaw and saute for approx. 7-8 mins.
In a large pot
of boiling water, cook the cavatelli for approx. 10 mins.
Drain and set aside.
When coleslaw is done, stir in cavatelli.
Add salt & pepper.
Serve immediately.

title: toasted mushroom roll-ups
directions: Chop mushrooms fine and saute in butter for 5 minutes. Sprinkle flour over butter mixture and add cream and seasonings. Spread filling on slices of bread with crust removed.
Cut in half, roll and fasten with toothpicks.
Place on cookie sheet and toast in oven.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: mushrooms, peppers and onions
directions: Slice mushrooms, bell pepper and onion.
In skillet, melt butter.
Add sliced mushrooms, onion and bell pepper to butter. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and simmer on low for about 1 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: saturday night supper
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Cook turkey in 10 inch skillet over medium heat 8 to 10 minutes, stirring occasionally, until no longer pink; drain. Spoon turkey into ungreased 2 quart casserole. Stir in vegetables, tomato sauce, pasta, garlic salt and pepper. Cover and bake about 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender; stir. Sprinkle with cheese.

title: hamburger or sausage casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add onion, celery, curry powder, bell pepper, salt and pepper.
Cook long grain rice as directed.
Layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan the meat, rice, layer of cheese, rice, then top with cream of mushroom soup plus 1/2 cup milk mixed together. Heat in oven for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: italian meat balls
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mixing well, form in small balls. Brown slowly in hot olive oil (2 tablespoons) in large frying pan. Put in favorite tomato sauce and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: corn flake cookies
directions: Cream shortening; add sugars and eggs.
Slowly add dry ingredients after stirring together.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: strawberry puree
directions: Wash and hull fresh berries.
In the blender, puree berries. Add the almond and vanilla extracts.
Sweeten with sugar.
Serve as a sauce with fresh berries, melons, apricots, peaches or as a sauce over ice cream (fat-free), pancakes, waffles or French toast.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Saute onions.
Grease pan and line pan with Doritos.
Cover with chicken pieces. Mix soups with tomatoes and milk.
Add onions, then pour over chicken.
Top with grated cheese.
Cook at 350° for 30 or 40 minutes.

title: louise's crispy pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and slice as thin as possible.
Combine with chopped onions and bell peppers.
Add salt; let stand at least 3 hours.
Drain.
In large pot, combine vinegar, sugar and spices, except turmeric.
Bring to a boil.
Add vegetables that are well drained.
Heat thoroughly, but do not boil.
Add turmeric.
Pack into hot, sterilized jars and seal at once.

title: chinese chews
directions: Beat eggs and add to sugar.
Sift all dry ingredients; add dates and nuts.
Add flour mixture to other ingredients.
Beat well.
Line 6 x 11-inch pan with waxed paper and spread dough to depth of 1/2 inch.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Makes 22 (1 x 3-inch) bars.

title: cream of zucchini soup
directions: Combine zucchini, water, 3/4 teaspoon salt, sugar and basil in saucepan.
Bring to boil; cover and simmer until tender, about 15 minutes.
Puree zucchini and liquid in a blender.
Set aside.

title: 15-minute super sundae pie
directions: Stir ice cream until smooth.
Spoon ice cream into pie crust and cover.
Freeze until hard.
To serve, let pie stand for 10 minutes to soften.
Put strawberry topping on a serving plate. Cut pie and place a slice on plate.
Garnish with other toppings as desired.
Return unused portion to freezer.
Makes 8 servings.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix together in a large bowl. May add food coloring to change color.
Freeze first batch for ice.

title: tree bark
directions: Put chocolate in bottom of a microwavable bowl.
place peanut butter chips on top of chocolate, and then peanut butter. Microwave 2 minutes.
Stir.
Add pretzels and peanuts.
Stir. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Spread with a wooden spoon.
In a cool place, let chill.
Flip sheet and break it up.

title: caramel icing
directions: Mix sugar, flour, milk or cream and butter or margarine.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; beat until creamy.
Add flavoring; mix well.
Spread on cake and sprinkle pecans on top.

title: million dollar pound cake
directions: Combine sugar and butter.
Cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one.
Add flour to creamed mixture, alternating with milk.
Beat well.
Stir in flavoring.
Pour into a well-greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 40 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: homestyle "shake and bake" chicken nuggets
directions: Cut up chicken breasts into bite sized pieces.
Rinse and pat dry.
Put bread crumbs, parsley and soup mix into large plastic bag and shake to mix.
Mix egg in bowl.
Put some of chicken pieces into egg mixture, then put in plastic bag and shake to coat with crumbs.
Continue with other pieces of chicken until they are all coated.
Let them dry on plate for a few minutes.
You can either stir-fry them in small amount of oil for a few minutes or microwave them until done.
Turn often.
Microwave nuggets won't get browned, so you may want to stir-fry them at the end with some garlic or onion.
Serve with rice and green salad.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, butter, cocoa and milk in pan and bring to a boil. Boil 1 minute at a full rolling boil.
Have 1/2 cup peanut butter ready; stir this into hot mixture, then add 3 cups oatmeal.
Mix well and add vanilla. Drop onto waxed paper; cool in refrigerator.

title: oriental beef
directions: Braise diced beef.
Saute vegetables in a little oil; mix beef and vegetables together.
Add the chow mein vegetables and soy sauce.
Simmer until tender, at least an hour.
Thicken with cornstarch.
Serve over hot rice.
This can be made ahead of time and frozen until time to use.

title: coffee bars
directions: Mix sugar and eggs.
Beat well.
Mix in the rest of the ingredients and stir up.
Put in large cookie sheet (11 x 17 x 1-inch).
Line top with one 16 ounce package of chocolate morsels and one cup of chopped walnuts.

title: chili con carne
directions: In a large kettle, cook ground beef, green pepper, onion and garlic until meat is browned.
Drain off fat.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, kidney beans, tomato sauce, chili powder, basil, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer about 20 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: sour cream casserole
