directions: Combine cream cheese, sour cream and chopped onion (include some of the green portions of onions).
Allow to stand 2 hours. Combine and brown ground beef and seasonings; add tomato sauce and simmer 20 minutes.
Meanwhile, cook noodles according to directions on box.
To assemble in casserole:
begin with layer of noodles, then sour cream mixture, then sauce.
Top with grated cheese (Parmesan type).
Makes two small (2-inch deep) casseroles. Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes with foil covering.

title: sweet potato cake
directions: Cream oil and sugar until smooth.
Add egg yolks.
Beat until creamy.
Add hot water, then dry ingredients, which have been sifted together.
Stir in potatoes, nuts and vanilla.
Mix well. Beat egg whites stiff and fold into mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes (three 9-inch layers).

title: next best thing to robert redford
directions: Stir together and press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: church punch
directions: Boil water and sugar; cool.
Combine this mixture with ginger ale, pineapple juice and almond extract; chill.
Makes 20 punch cups.

title: game bird basting sauce
directions: Heat all ingredients in saucepan to slow boil.
Baste on turkeys, pheasants or quail.

title: crabmeat dressing duhon
directions: Combine all ingredients except crab and bread crumbs.
Mix well.
Add bread crumbs; gently mix in crabmeat.
Spoon into greased baking dish; do not pack down.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, covered.
Remove cover; bake 10 minutes more, uncovered.

title: macho nachos
directions: Spread beans in bottom of cookie sheet.
Brown meat and season to taste.
(I use Tony's seasoning.)
Spread meat on top of beans. Spread taco sauce on top of meat.
You can use more sauce if you like.
Stir sour cream in carton to make spreadable.
Spread this on top of meat and sauce.
Grate cheese (as much as you like) and sprinkle on top.
Put in oven until cheese is melted.
Serve in pan as a dip with Tostitos.

title: banana split pie
directions: Mix crumbs and one stick of melted butter for pie crust.
Line bottom of pie pan.
Beat eggs, 2 sticks soft butter and confectioners sugar for 10 minutes.
Pour mixture into crust. Slice bananas and place on top of mixture, then add pineapple. Spread on Cool Whip and top with pecans.
Refrigerate a few hours before serving.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: In large bowl, mix all dry ingredients (flour, sugar, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg).
In a separate bowl, mix eggs, water, oil and pumpkin.
Add pumpkin mixture to flour mixture; blend well.
Add walnuts and raisins.
Grease and flour 2 bread loaf pans or prepare for cupcakes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: delicious cheese potatoes
directions: Boil the potatoes and beat only with fork so that they are lumpy. Add the sour cream, Swiss cheese, salt, pepper and butter. Scoop into a 9 x 9-inch casserole dish. Sprinkle with paprika and bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: marinated tomatoes
directions: Chill for about 1 hour.

title: game soup
directions: Joint your game neatly.
Cut the ham and onions into small pieces and fry all in butter to a light brown.
Put into soup pot with the beef, cut into strips, and a little pepper.
Pour on the water.
Heat slowly and stew gently for 2 hours.
Take out the pieces of bird and cover in a bowl.
Cook the soup 1 hour longer. Strain and cool.
Drop in celery and simmer 10 minutes.
Pour upon fried bread in the tureen.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Roll out dough large enough for small pizza pan.
Bake according to package directions. Cool.

title: chicken soup supreme
directions: Remove hen from broth; cool and shred white meat (not too fine).
Reserve dark meat for another use.
Strain the broth.
Do the following only just shortly before you are going to serve the soup.
Add to the broth, eggs, asparagus, mushrooms and pimentos. The ingredients should not be cut up too fine.
Now, add the white chicken meat to the broth, which has been heated and slightly thickened with cornstarch.
Do not boil the sauce very much after you add the cornstarch; just cook until the mixture clears.
Be careful as to the time cooked; if not overcooked, you can enjoy it reheated.
The quantities of ingredients varies according to how much broth and chicken you have.
Just have to judge for yourself, but the soup is a flavorful broth with a few added ingredients floating through, not thick like a stew.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients.
Allow to drain in a colander for 1 hour.
Bring next 4 ingredients to a boil.
Add cucumber mixture and bring to a boil again.
Ladle into clean jars, adjust lids and process for 10 minutes in a boiling water bath.

title: orange julius
directions: Combine all ingredients, except ice cubes, in blender.
Blend 1-2 minutes, adding ice cubes one at a time.
You may want to add a bit of sugar.

title: gingerbread men
directions: Combine cake mix, flour, eggs, oil, molasses and ginger. Mixture will be soft.
Refrigerate 2 hours.

title: sock-it-to-me cake
directions: Pour half of mix into greased and floured tube pan.
Then sprinkle brown sugar and cinnamon over that.
Pour remaining mixture into pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: buttermilk tea cakes
directions: Mix sugar and butter or margarine.
Add sour milk and soda. Add eggs.
Mix well.
Add flour.
Make into cookies.
Roll out to 1/4-inch thick.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Heat oven to 425°. Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onion in pastry shell. Beat eggs. Add other ingredients and pour into shell.
Bake 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 300° and bake another 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes. Serve in wedges.
May add asparagus or spinach. Serves 6 or 8.

title: menehune pineapple bread
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, butter, flour and pineapple.
Mix in bread.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: shrimp chowder
directions: Fry onion in butter until soft and colored.
Add boiling water and chicken broth.
Add potatoes, seasonings, celery and carrots and simmer for 25 minutes.
Add shrimp and simmer for 5 minutes. Add milk and stir in grated cheese.
Heat, but be sure not to scald, the milk.
Add parsley and simmer 15 minutes.
"Serve with crusty bread or toast."

title: chili
directions: Mix all together and boil for 1 or 2 hours.

title: cranberry pie
directions: Grease and lightly flour a deep 10-inch pie plate or 10 x 2-inch quiche dish.
Place cranberries in bottom.
Sprinkle with pecans and 1/2 cup sugar.

title: coconut pineapple pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add coconut and pineapple and mix well. Pour into pie shells and bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until set.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix ingredients together and bake in a 9 x 13-inch greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash until tender, drain.
Place in shallow casserole dish.
Add chopped eggs, onion, green peppers, salt and pepper. Place cubes of toast on top.
Dot with butter. Bake in 350° oven until onions and peppers are tender.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Mix butter (melted) and graham cracker crumbs together.
Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch Tupperware container.
Cool.
Add sugar, cream cheese and Cool Whip together and mix with electric mixer.
Pour onto crust.
Add layer of pie filling.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Boil chicken and shred.
Mix in chilies and onion.
Wrap mixture in tortillas.
Place tortillas in a casserole dish.
Top with whipping cream and cheese.
Bake at 360 degrees for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: tina's pie crust
directions: In medium bowl, combine flour and salt.
Using pastry blender or fork, cut shortening into flour until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add 1 tablespoon of water at a time while tossing and mixing with fork.
Add water until dough is moist enough to form ball when lightly pressed together.
Shape dough into a ball. Flatten ball into 1/2-inch thickness, rounding and smoothing edges.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add seasonings to your taste. Add tomato sauce and paste; let simmer.
Cook noodles until done; drain.
In a pan, layer the noodles, meat sauce, Provolone cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Add noodles, meat sauce and cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: beans supreme
directions: Mix ingredients, beans, beef and bacon, in large container to allow for stirring.
Mix remaining ingredients separately and add to first mixture. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: hearty potato soup
directions: Combine first eight ingredients in Dutch oven.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in hot water; add to potato mixture.
Bring to a boil over medium flame; cover, reduce flame and simmer 8 minutes, or until vegetables are tender.
Dissolve flour in 1/4 cup of the milk; stir into soup.
Add remaining milk; cook over medium flame until thickened, about 25 minutes.
Makes 10 servings.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Remove fat and gristle from beef.
Cut
to 1/2 inch thick.
Cut across the grain into strips about 2 inches long.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
In large skillet, melt butter and add meat. Brown meat on all sides.
Push meat to one side and add onions. Cook slowly until clear.
Push onions to side and stir flour into drippings.
Add beef broth and bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Stir meat, onions and gravy together.
Lower heat and stir in mustard.
Cover pan and simmer 1 hour, or until meat is tender.
5 minutes before serving, drain mushrooms and add to meat. Add sour cream and wine.
Heat briefly and season to taste.
Serve over steamed rice.

title: raspberry filled cookies
directions: Beat cream cheese and butter together until light and fluffy. Add egg and vanilla. Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture. Blend well.
Chill at least 1 hour.
When chilled, shape into 1-inch balls and place on a cookie sheet.
Press down centers with your thumb and sprinkle with green sugar.
Add raspberry jam to the center of the cookie.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes. Makes 4 dozen.

title: sour cream-chocolate bit cake
directions: Mix butter with the 1 cup sugar until blended, then beat in eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour with baking powder, soda and cinnamon, then blend with creamed mixture.
Mix in the sour cream. Pour batter into a greased and flour dusted 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Scatter the chocolate bits evenly over the batter, then sprinkle with the 1 remaining tablespoon of sugar.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes or until cake just begins to pull away from sides of pan.
Serve warm or cooled (do not refrigerate), cut in rectangles. Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: banana muffins
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients.
Add next 2 ingredients, then fold into flour mixture (flour and nutmeg mixed together) with wooden spoon.
Do not beat.
Place in muffin tins.
Bake 20 minutes in 375° oven.

title: smoked summer sausage
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and refrigerate for three days, mixing every day.
On the fourth day, form into rolls (1 1/2 to 2 inches in diameter).
Preheat smoker to 140° to 150°.
Place sausage rolls on racks.
Keep this temperature for 2 hours.
Serve with sweet and spicy mustard.

title: party meatballs
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients and shape into bite size meatballs. Bake at 350° for 5 minutes.
(They only have to be partially cooked.)
Put the meatballs aside.
Combine chili sauce and grape jelly into pot.
Heat until well combined.
Add meatballs and simmer for 1 hour.
Serve warm.
(Very easy to cook and serve in your crock-pot!)

title: yam fries
directions: Clean and peel potatoes; cut them into wedges.
Place about an inch apart on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Brush with mixture of margarine and brown sugar.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes, turning and brushing occasionally.

title: pumpkin molasses gingerbread muffins
directions: Grease 10 muffin cups or line with paper cups.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl, sift together flours, baking soda, baking powder, spices and salt and set aside.

title: rum tum tiddy
directions: Cut cheese in small pieces.
Mix and stir over low heat or in a double boiler until the cheese melts.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: smothered cabbage wedge
directions: Cut cabbage into 8 wedges.
Boil in salt water until tender. Drain well and place in baking dish.
Cook peppers and onion until tender in pan.
Add salt, pepper and flour, then milk.
Cook until thick.
Pour over cabbage.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° in oven for 20 minutes; remove.
Combine cheese, mayonnaise and chili sauce. Spoon over cabbage and bake 5 more minutes.

title: stuffed eggplant
directions: Prepare the eggplant by slicing off both ends, wasting as little as possible.
Carefully peel four inch wide strips lengthwise from each eggplant, creating a "striped" effect.
Slice in half lengthwise.
With a small knife or citrus spoon, remove most of the inside of each half, leaving a cavity for the stuffing and reserving what is removed.
Rub the eggplant shells with salt to "cure" them while preparing the stuffing.
In a skillet, put the yellow onion in a small amount of the oil and cook over medium heat until tender.
Add the garlic, bell pepper and tomato and continue to cook, stirring frequently, for five minutes.
Add the reserved insides of the eggplants, the oregano and Tabasco; mix thoroughly and cook for two minutes.
Remove from heat and let stand.
Rinse the eggplant shells in cold water.
Pour half the remaining oil in a large skillet that can hold the eggplant shells in one layer. Stuff the shells with the mixture and sprinkle the green onion and ground pepper on top.
Arrange them in the skillet.
Cook over medium heat until hot and then reduce the heat to low/simmer.
Mix the thyme, basil and remaining oil and drizzle over each stuffed half.
Cover and simmer slowly 45 to 60 minutes, until shells are very tender.
Remove carefully with large spoon and serve with brown rice for a nutritious vegetarian meal.
Serves 4.

title: watergate salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and mix all ingredients together. Add juice as needed to mixture.
Serve or refrigerate.

title: early morning potato pancakes
directions: Mash potatoes until smooth with all remaining ingredients. Should be moist to form into patties.
Place on well oiled baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 40 minutes, turning once.
Pancakes should form brown crust.

title: strawberry bread with spread
directions: Save 1/2 cup juice for spread. Mix all dry ingredients.
Make a hole in center.
Pour strawberries, oil and eggs in hole.
Mix well. Add nuts.
Pour into 2 bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes.

title: ozark pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients together first.
Add the rest; mix until moist.
Pour into an 8 or 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts in pan of water on top of stove for 1 hour.
Remove chicken from broth and pull off the white meat. Save 1 cup of the broth.
Melt 1 stick margarine on stove; add 1 bag stuffing mix and stir.
Combine chicken and celery soups. Layer in a casserole dish the stuffing, chicken pieces, soups and 1/2 cup broth.
Repeat, ending with stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: biblical fruit cake
directions: All the ingredients for this fruit cake are found in the Bible. Check it out for yourself.

title: scotcheroos
directions: 1. Combine sugar and syrup in saucepan over moderate heat.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and beat well.
Add vanilla. Combine and sift dry ingredients together.
Add to first mixture. Put in sour cream and milk.
Spoon into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: yuletide toffee squares
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Grease 15 x 10-inch pan.
Combine oats, sugar, margarine, corn syrup, vanilla and salt; mix well.
Firmly press mixture into pan.
Bake 12 minutes or until mixture is brown and bubbly.
Cool completely.

title: decorative pumpkin cake
directions: Whisk all dry ingredients together in large bowl.
Add the eggs and oil from the Quick Shake.
Then add the pumpkin and beat together until smooth.
Place in the Tupperware 3-quart casserole with the cone.
Microwave on 70% power for 18 minutes.
Let stand at least 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar or drizzle with powdered sugar glaze.
For a more decorative touch, frost with orange frosting.

title: diet pumpkin pie
directions: Beat egg whites until just foamy.
Add pumpkin; beat till well mixed.
Add sugars, sweetner, spices, salt, and Milnot.
Mix well. Pour in 9-inch unbaked low fat pie crust.
Bake 450° for 10 minutes then 350° for 40 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and outside comes out clean.
Cool.
Serve with low fat whipped topping.

title: macaroni tuna casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese as directed on package.
Stir in soup, tuna and milk.
Pour into greased 2- quart baking dish. Sprinkle with cheese and parsley if desired.
Bake, uncovered, at 350 degrees for 20 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Yields 4 servings.

title: mushroom business
directions: Clean and slice mushrooms.
Saute in butter until slightly cooked.
Butter 3 slices of bread.
Trim crusts and cut into 1-inch squares.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces.
Roll in the sugar and 1 1/2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Spray a Bundt pan or 2 loaf pans.
Add biscuit pieces.
If you use loaf pans, use 2 cans of biscuits in each pan. Pour over top the brown sugar, 1 tablespoon cinnamon and the melted oleo.
Add nuts, if you like.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: sassy onion dip
directions: In small bowl, beat the cream cheese until fluffy.
Add remaining ingredients;
mix well.
Cover
and chill at least 1 hour.
Stir before serving.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients; drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Cube potatoes and cook until tender.
Boil eggs and cool.
Cut eggs and onions into small pieces.
Mix all ingredients and add to potatoes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Let boil for 5 to 10 minutes to cook onions.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Peel shrimp and devein.
Chop shrimp.
Stir together sour cream and next 4 ingredients in a large bowl; stir in shrimp. Cover and chill 8 hours.
Serve with celery, carrots or crackers.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid and sugar with enough of water to make 2 quarts. Mix the other ingredients to the Kool-Aid.
Add orange sherbet before serving.

title: chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: Stir dry ingredients together.
Cream shortening, sugar, molasses and eggs until light and fluffy.
Stir in flour then oats, raisins and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° about 8 minutes.

title: meal in a loaf
directions: Cut bread in half lengthwise, using care scooping out inside and break into bite sizes.
Combine ground beef, chopped onion and green pepper in large saucepan.
Cook until meat is browned.
Stir in soup, cheese and bread pieces.
Add Italian seasoning.

title: marshmallow fudge cake
directions: Melt butter.
Cream sugar into butter.
Add eggs, then stir in flour, nuts, vanilla and cocoa. Bake in loaf pan for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°. When done, remove from oven and cover top of hot cake with the package of marshmallows.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cut bread into cubes.
Place in shallow baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes, until toasted.
Spray a 12 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish.
Place half of bread cubes in dish.
Set aside.

title: ambrosia
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges.
Combine pineapple, oranges, grapes, marshmallows, coconut and nuts.
Combine sour cream and sugar; pour over fruit and combine.
Chill 2 hours before serving.

title: homemade wheat bread
directions: Soften dry yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Combine shortening. Stir in whole wheat flour and 1 cup white flour.
Beat well.
Stir in softened yeast.
Add 3 cups white flour.
Rest of flour will be used to knead dough.
Knead dough for 1 to 12 minutes.
Shape dough into ball.
Cover in greased bowl big enough to let rise double in size for 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down; shape into 3 smooth balls.
Cover and let it rest for 10 minutes.
Shape into 3 loaves.
Put into greased pans and let rise until double (1 1/2 hours).
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Cover loosely with foil if loaves brown too quickly.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Pour over apples.
Add sugars, nuts, oil and vanilla.
Mix flour sifted with soda, cinnamon and salt.
Blend. Mixture will be very thick.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: caramel pecan bars
directions: Mix butter and brown sugar; let cool.
Add other ingredients. Mix and pour into lightly greased pan.
Bake slowly at 275° until lightly golden brown; do not overbake.
Cut into bars and remove from pan.

title: wonderful chicken casserole
directions: Cook finely chopped onion in butter in frying pan.
Add finely chopped chicken, soup and cooked noodles.
(Cook noodles in chicken stock for 20 minutes.)
Mix and bake in greased casserole (9 x 13 x 2-inch) for 45 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cover with grated cheese 15 minutes just before done.

title: frutti spinach salad
directions: Combine the spinach leaves, strawberries, blueberries and mandarin oranges in a salad bowl and toss to mix.
Mix the poppy seed dressing, lemon juice and sugar in a bowl or place in a shaker and shake to mix.
Drizzle the dressing over the salad and toss to coat well.

title: mardi gras party cake
directions: Grease and flour three 8-inch round cake pans.
Melt butterscotch morsels in water in saucepan.
Cool.
Sift flour with salt, soda and baking powder.
Set aside.
Add sugar gradually to shortening, creaming well.
Blend in eggs.
Beat well after each. Add melted butterscotch; mix well.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Blend well after each addition.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Refer to Butterscotch Filling for Mardi Gras Party Cake and Sea Foam Frosting to finish the cake.

title: water chestnuts
directions: Cut each piece of bacon into 3 pieces and wrap each chestnut. Microwave for 3 or 4 minutes.
Then dip in soy sauce and then into the brown sugar.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Mix ingredients and bake in turkey until turkey is done.
If baked separately, bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: new england gingersnaps
directions: Cream
butter
in
a large mixing bowl; gradually add 1 cup sugar,
beating
until
light
and
fluffy.
Add
egg and molasses and beat well.
Sift together flour, soda and spices. Add
to creamed mixture, beating until smooth.
Chill 2 hours. Shape dough in 3/4 inch balls and roll in additional sugar to coat well.
Place
inches
apart
on greased baking sheet. Bake
for 11 to 12 minutes.
Cool slightly on cookie sheet; remove to wire racks to cool completely.
Yields about 6 dozen.

title: potato soup
directions: Put all ingredients except milk in pan.
Cover and cook on low until potatoes are tender.
Stir in milk the last 15 minutes.
I take potato masher and crush into small pieces.

title: 24 hour slaw
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in a glass bowl.
Then mix all together and let set for 24 hours at least.

title: paydays
directions: Melt milk and peanut butter chips.
Remove from heat.
Add peanuts and Rice Krispies.
Drop onto cookie sheet.
Cool in refrigerator.

title: electric skillet peanut butter fudge
directions: In skillet, combine sugar, butter and evaporated milk.
Set heat at 280°.
Bring to boil and boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Turn heat off.
Add marshmallow cream and peanut butter, then vanilla.
Beat until blended and pour in buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: pineapple zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla until thick.
Stir in remaining ingredients and blend well.
Pour into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour for 2 loaves (45 minutes for 5 loaves in 5 x 3 x 2-inch pans).

title: cheesecake cookies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients until like meal.
Reserving 1 cup of mixture, spread in an 8-inch buttered square pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Put cream cheese in mixing bowl.
Beat together with sugar, egg, lemon juice, milk and vanilla.
Pour over cooked crust; sprinkle remaining crust mixture over top of cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
When cool, cut into squares.

title: chicken with wine-mushroom sauce
directions: Bake chicken at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Mix ingredients and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake for another 1/2 hour.

title: fruited mint tea
directions: Place water in saucepan; bring to a boil.
Add 7 mint sprigs; boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; add tea bags.
Cover and let stand 10 minutes.
Remove mint and tea bags.
Stir in sugar.

title: "the punch bowle"
directions: Put fruit in punch bowl.
Add Sauterne. Refrigerate overnight. Pour more Sauterne, 1/2 fifth vodka and add bottle of champagne right before serving.
Serve cold by filling punch bowl with ice.

title: black bean dip
directions: Place beans in shallow baking dish.
Stir in onion, onion powder, salsa and Tabasco.
Cover with shredded cheeses.
Bake at 350° until bubbles, about 30 minutes.

title: salsa
directions: Mix together and serve with tortilla chips.

title: french vanilla ice cream
directions: Thoroughly combine milk, egg yolks, salt and sugar. Cook slowly in double boiler until mixture thickens and coats spoon. Cool and add vanilla and Half & Half. Place in ice cream freezer and follow instructions.

title: short'nin' bread
directions: Combine flour, cinnamon and nutmeg in a large bowl; mix well and set aside.
Dissolve baking soda in buttermilk; stir well and set aside.
Combine butter or molasses in a heavy saucepan; bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Add to the flour mixture.
Stir in buttermilk mixture and egg.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch cast-iron skillet.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in the center comes out clean.
Cool in skillet 10 minutes.
Invert cake onto plate.
Cut into wedges to serve.
Makes 8 servings each with 370 calories, 10 g fat and 39 mg cholesterol.

title: marvelous meat loaf
directions: Mix meat, onion and catsup.
Beat eggs and add remaining ingredients.
Place half of mixture in pan.
Lay cheese slices on top of loaf.
Place remaining half of mixture on top. Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes. Spread
mushroom soup on top of loaf and bake 1 hour.

title: new york cheesecake
directions: Put cream cheese, Ricotta cheese, sugar, eggs, flour, vanilla, butter and sour cream in large mixer bowl.
Beat at high speed for 20 minutes.
Pour into 9 or 10 inch buttered spring form pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Turn off oven and let stand for 2 hours.
Will keep 4 weeks in refrigerator.
Serves 16.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach as directed; drain thoroughly.
Melt margarine and mix with spinach.
Beat eggs and add onion, cheese and seasonings.
Add to stuffing and spinach.
Chill overnight.
Form into balls and bake in 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: fruit salad cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Add one small can fruit salad, drained, and one egg.
Sprinkle brown sugar and nuts on top.
Bake in 9 x 9 inch greased pan for 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: green chile stew
directions: Cover all ingredients with water in large pot.
Simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: mushroom soup
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan on a gentle heat.
Toss the onions in it; cover and sweat until soft and completely cooked.
Wipe the mushrooms clean.
Chop very finely.
Add to the saucepan and cook for another 3 to 4 minutes.
Stir in the flour and cook for another 2 to 3 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Then add chicken broth and milk gradually, stirring all the time.
Increase heat and bring to a boil.
Taste and add a touch of cream if necessary.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Place first 4 ingredients in casserole dish.
Mix together cream of chicken soup, mayonnaise, salt, minced onion and lemon juice.
Pour into dish and top with grated cheese, slivered almonds and potato chips.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: icebox pie
directions: Make Jell-O, refrigerate until slightly thickened.

title: hot cheesy beef dip
directions: Saute pecans in butter 3 to 5 minutes.
Drain on paper towels and set aside.
Place dried beef in container of electric blender or food processor.
Chop finely and set aside.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Cover the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan with pecan pieces and coconut.
Mix the cake mix as directed; pour over pecans and coconut.
Mix together the melted margarine, powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Spoon over batter by teaspoonfuls; do not stir in. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix up sugar, cream and butter and cook over medium heat on stove.
Stir constantly until it boils.
Let it boil 6 minutes. Take off.
Stir in a jar of marshmallow cream and 3/4 cup of peanut butter.
Pour out.
Let cool, then cut into squares.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: In large nonstick skillet, sprayed with nonstick spray, saute pepper strips, onion strips and garlic until onion is translucent. Move veggies to sides of pan and add chicken breasts.
Brown chicken lightly on both sides, cooking on high heat for about 5 minutes.
Add pineapple chunks with juice; reduce heat to low and cover tightly.
Let this cook slowly for about 30 to 40 minutes. While simmering, add teriyaki sauce.
This is wonderful served over hot rice.

title: luscious coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions, making two 9-inch layers.
When completely cool, split both layers.
Combine sugar, sour cream and coconut; blend well and chill.
Reserve one cup of this mixture for frosting and spread remainder between layers. Combine reserved sour cream mixture with Cool Whip.
Blend until smooth.
Spread on top and sides.
Seal cake in airtight container in refrigerator.
(I make this cake at least 3 days ahead of time, just makes it better.)

title: fresh garden salad
directions: Beat with blender.
Pour over fresh vegetables:
onions, green pepper, cucumber, broccoli, cauliflower and carrots.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Put chicken in saucepan.
Pour sauce and Coke over chicken, making sure chicken is completely covered with sauce.
Cover and cook 30 to 45 minutes at medium heat.
Cook additional 10 minutes on high heat to boil mixture into a thick sauce.
Serve hot.
You may use the same recipe with pork chops.

title: baked apples
directions: Wash apples.
Core out the center to 1-inch diameter, taking care not to core all the way through the bottom of apple; set aside.
In a small bowl, combine the nuts, dates, cinnamon, honey and lemon juice.
Mix well.
Fill the apples with the nut mixture.

title: dad's catfish stew
directions: Fry enough fatback to make 1/2 cup grease.
Add grease to 2 gallons water in large soup pot.
Add fish and cook until done. Debone if not done before cooking fish.
To the fish stock add fish, onions, butter or margarine, milk and tomato paste.
Bring to a boil and then cook slowly about 1 1/2 hours and serve.

title: chuck roast au gratin
directions: Trim fat from meat and place in large baking pan.
Roast at 350° for 1 hour and spoon off fat.
Arrange potatoes and onions around roast.
Pour soup over all.
Cover and bake 2 hours more or until meat and potatoes are tender.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake until cheese melts.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown beef in the oil. Add onions and cook for 6 minutes or until onions are soft. Add cream of celery soup and sour cream. Stir well.
Put in a slightly greased baking dish.
Put biscuits over top of mixture and bake in oven until biscuits are brown.
A green tossed salad is great with this.
Have a dessert and your meat is complete.

title: clinch mountain vinegar pie
directions: Combine sugar, eggs, vinegar, flour (or cornstarch) and water in double boiler and cook until thick and smooth, stirring occasionally.
Just before removing from heat, stir in small lump of butter and some lemon extract.
Pour into baked pie shell.
If desired, the pie may be topped with frosting or whipped cream.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Allow butter, margarine and cream cheese to soften several hours.
Mix butter and margarine.
Add sugar; mix thoroughly.
Add cream cheese, mixing well.
Add flour, then vanilla, then pecans last.
Spoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes, or as soon as edges start to brown.

title: cheese omelet
directions: Beat eggs, water, onion and pepper.
Melt margarine in small skillet.
Add egg mixture, letting juice out on all sides and cook on medium heat until set on bottom.
Sprinkle with cheese and salt over half of omelet.
With spatula, gently fold other side over cheese; brown and turn over.
If done, slide onto plate.

title: fried beef with spring onion
directions: Clean and slice beef thinly across the grain.
Season with salt, soy sauce, pepper, tapioca flour and bicarbonate of soda. Mix thoroughly.
Rub a pinch of salt into the sliced ginger and wash away the salt.
Beat the egg with pepper and 1/2 tablespoon oil.
Heat oil and lightly fry the ginger for a minute.
Add the sliced beef, spring onion and 1 cup water.
Cover the pan and let cook for 3 minutes.
Mix the ingredients well for a few minutes. When the beef has changed color and the ingredients are well mixed, turn off the heat.
Make a well in the center of the ingredients and pour in the beaten egg.
Mix well.
Serve immediately.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding with cold milk.
Beat until dissolved.
Slowly beat in condensed milk; fold in Cool Whip.
Layer vanilla wafers, sliced bananas and pudding mixture.
Repeat layers, ending with pudding mixture.

title: ice cream sandwiches
directions: In medium size mixing bowl, stir together corn syrup and peanut butter.
Add Rice Krispies.
Stir until well coated. Press mixture evenly in bottom of buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Place in freezer or coldest part of refrigerator until firm.

title: coffee punch
directions: Combine coffee and sugar. Stir until sugar dissolves. Chill thoroughly. Add to this milk and vanilla; stir thoroughly. Pour into punch bowl. Add partially softened ice cream by spoonfuls, folding it into punch.

title: oakley's sunday dressing
directions: Cook chicken until done.
Cool and take off the bone.
Leave broth in pot.
Crumble cornbread in large bowl and mix with rice. Cook the chopped celery, white onion and green onions with butter in a skillet for about 4 to 5 minutes.
Pour chicken broth into bowl with cornbread and rice.
Add cream of chicken soup and eggs. Then add sauteed celery and onions.
Add salt and pepper to suit your taste.
Bake for about an hour or until done at 350°.

title: chicken noodle stir-fry
directions: Debone chicken. Cut meat into bite size pieces. (Save skin and bones for broth.)
Bring water to a boil;
add noodles.
Set aside flavor packets.
Cook noodles 2 minutes. Drain and set aside.
In large skillet over medium heat, stir-fry onion and garlic until onion is clear. Add chicken and stir-fry until chicken is cooked, about 6 minutes.
Push to side of pan. Add to center of pan the carrots, celery and contents of flavor packets. Stir-fry 2 minutes.
Add cabbage and stir-fry all ingredients about 2 minutes. Add noodles and broth, stirring until heated through, about 2 minutes. Serve with chow mein noodles as garnish.
Yields 4 servings.

title: cranberry fluff
directions: Combine cranberries, marshmallows and sugar.
Cover and chill overnight.
Add apples, grapes, walnuts and salt.
Fold in whipped cream.
Chill.
Turn into a serving bowl or spoon into individual cups.
Trim with a cluster of green grapes, if desired.
Makes 8-10 servings.

title: crispy marble bars
directions: In 2 1/2-quart casserole dish, microwave on High corn syrup and sugar for 4 minutes, stirring twice.
Stir in peanut butter. Add Rice Krispies, stirring until coated well.
Add chocolate chips, stirring until they start to melt.
Press into 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Press the ground meat into the bottom of a 2-quart casserole dish.
Spread the cream of mushroom soup over the meat.
Spread cheese over the soup.
Cover the top of the casserole with a layer of Tater Tots.
Put casserole in oven and cook for approximately 1 hour.
Enjoy.

title: low-fat muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine ingredients and fill paper-lined muffin tin cups 1/2 full.
Bake 14 to 16 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cheese ball
directions: Beat cream cheese on high speed until soft. Add remaining ingredients. Mix well and form into a ball. Roll in crushed pecan pieces. Refrigerate. Very good with Captain Wafer crackers.

title: low-fat mexican salad
directions: In food processor bowl, fitted with metal blade and motor running, drop in garlic cloves; process 10 seconds.
Through feed tube, add peas, cilantro, onion, lemon juice, pepper and hot pepper sauce.
Process until smooth.

title: john's favorite pepper shrimp
directions: Melt butter over medium heat. Add garlic and simmer for 5 minutes. Spread raw shrimp evenly in 13 x 9 Pyrex dish. Pour melted garlic butter over shrimp. Toss gently with your hands. Sprinkle pepper over all the shrimp. Just when you think you've put enough pepper, add more. You can't add too much. Toss again with your hands. Put in 350° preheated oven and bake for 15 to 20 minutes. Shrimp should be pink. Toss with spoon and bake only 5 minutes more. Save the juice off of this; it's very good for dipping toasted bread.

title: micro-meat loaf
directions: In a large bowl, combine first 7 ingredients and mix well. Shape into a loaf and place in microsafe baking dish.
Combine the sugar and catsup.
Set aside.
Cover meat loaf with waxed paper. Microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Pour off any juices.
Microwave covered at Medium power for 10 minutes.
Remove waxed paper. Spread top of meat loaf with catsup mixture.
Microwave uncovered 5 minutes longer or until meat loaf is done.

title: spaghetti chop suey
directions: Cook spaghetti as directed on package.
Melt butter in a frying pan and add green pepper, onions and celery.
Cook slowly for 15 minutes.
Stir a few times; add tomatoes, salt, sugar and pepper.
Continue cooking until slightly thick; add drained spaghetti and continue cooking for 20 minutes.
Cook steak until crumbly and slightly brown.
Spread on top of spaghetti mixture.

title: baked potato soup
directions: Saute 1 small onion in butter or margarine until tender.
Add flour and stir until smooth.
Add one cup of water with bouillon cube and milk.
Stir constantly, until thickened.
Add potatoes. Cook and stir until potatoes are well mixed in white sauce.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add 1/2 to 1 teaspoon basil to taste.
Serve hot with bacon, Cheddar cheese and chopped green onion.
Yields 4 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Yields 8 servings.

title: bacon southern baked beans
directions: In frying pan, brown together the bacon, hamburger, onion, some garlic and pepper.
Add all ingredients together.
Put in crock-pot or oven and heat thoroughly.
Serve warm.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix green beans, mushroom soup and part of onions.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Place in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Cover with rest of onions.
Bake 5 more minutes.

title: boiled dinner
directions: Cut meat into serving sized pieces, cover with water and bring to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer for 3 hours. Remove meat and keep warm.
Scrub the vegetables and cut into quarters or cubes. Cut the cabbage into 6 wedges.
Bring the broth to a boil.
Add carrots, turnips, onions and potatoes.
Cook for 15 minutes.
Add cabbage and cook for 15 to 20 minutes longer.
Arrange meat on serving platter and place vegetables around the meat in an attractive pattern.
Sprinkle well with fresh ground black pepper. Yield: 6 servings.
Carbohydrate 36 g, protein 38 g, fat 34 g, calories 606.

title: antipasto salad
directions: Cook cauliflower and carrots until partly cooked.
Add all ingredients and boil until completely heated.
Put in pint jars and seal.
Makes 15 pints.

title: raspberry layer salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water. Melt marshmallows in hot milk. Combine pineapple, cheese and nuts; add gelatin. Fold mixture into marshmallows. Fold in whipped topping. Place in 9 x 13-inch pan. Chill until firm.

title: linguine with herbed shrimp(yield:  4-6 servings)
directions: 1. Cook the shrimp in 1/4 cup olive oil in a medium saucepan with the thyme, parsley, bay leaves, salt and pepper.
Cook just until shrimp turns pink and is slightly firm.

title: ranch beans
directions: Sort and wash beans. Cover with water 2-inches above beans and soak for 8 hours. Drain beans and put in Dutch oven. Add water and next 8 ingredients. Bring to boil. Reduce heat. Simmer 1 1/2 hours or until beans are tender, stirring occasionally. Add tomatoes and simmer an additional 30 minutes.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Cook cake according to directions on box.
Combine sugar and pineapple and heat to a boil.
When cake is done, put pineapple mixture on cake.
After it cools, spread on pudding.
Top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: easy ice cream
directions: Mix and freeze in refrigerator or freezer.

title: swedish sugar cookies
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients; add eggs and vanilla and mix well. Add last 3 ingredients and mix well; chill.
When ready to bake, roll into walnut size balls and flatten with the bottom of a glass dipped in sugar; a heavy glass with a patterned bottom works well. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt butter and mix all ingredients together. Spray an 8 x 11 oblong baking dish with Pam or other cooking spray. Pour mixture into sprayed pan and bake for 1 hour or until done in the middle. Can check with toothpick in the middle of casserole. If it comes out clean, casserole is done.

title: mexican style deep dish pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Cut biscuits into quarters. Place biscuits in large bowl. Stir in 1 cup of salsa, 2 cups of cheese, bell pepper, onion, olives, garlic and hamburger; mix well. Spread mixture into a greased 13 x 9 baking pan. Pour the rest of the salsa over top. Sprinkle with the rest of cheese. Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: mushroom chicken
directions: Cut
chicken
into
pieces.
Brown
chicken in oil in a 14-inch
Dutch
oven.
Pour
soup in oven.	Chop the potatoes, carrots and onions.
Add these vegetables to the oven.
Cook 1 hour with 12 coals on top and 12 coals on the bottom.

title: chili sandwich
directions: Open can of chili.
Toast bread and put chili on bread. Viola!
Quick meal and it's good, too!

title: easy cherry chocolate cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
In large bowl, beat eggs. Stir in cake mix, cherry pie filling and oil until well blended. Spread in pan.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Prepare pudding.
Spread over cake.

title: (zucchini) corn bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Beat egg, oil and milk together. Add zucchini and liquid mixture to dry ingredients.
Stir well. Pour batter into a greased 9 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: coconut pie
directions: Combine sugar,	flour,	milk
and
egg	yolks.	Cook in double boiler until thick.
Remove; add coconut and flavoring. Pour in baked
pie shell and cover with meringue made with egg whites and 6 tablespoons sugar.
Brown in 400° oven.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oil, eggs and sour cream all together.
Pour 1/2 of the mixture into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix brown sugar and cinnamon together.
Sprinkle 1/2 of this on top of the batter in your pan.
Pour remaining batter over this.
Then add remaining sugar and cinnamon over this batter.
Swirl through mixture with a knife.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: cheese salad
directions: Mix well with mixer.
Great with sliced tomatoes, aspic or veggie strips.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease 2-quart casserole.
In mixing bowl, sift flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Stir in caraway seed.
With pastry blender or 2 knives, cut in butter until like coarse cornmeal; stir in raisins.
Combine buttermilk, egg and soda; stir into flour mixture until just moistened.
Turn dough onto lightly floured surface; knead lightly until smooth and shape into ball.
Place in casserole.
With sharp knife, make 4-inch cross, 1/4 inch deep in top center.
Brush with beaten egg yolk. Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes or until done.
Cool in pan 10 minutes. Remove.
Cool before slicing.

title: key lime pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In large mixing bowl, beat egg yolks with Eagle Brand milk, lime juice and food coloring, if desired. Pour into prepared crust or pie shell and bake for 30 minutes. Cool and chill.
Top with whipped topping.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and add 1/3 cup cold water.
Cook at the temperature of 400°.

title: crisco no-cook cake frosting
directions: Beat together sugar and egg.
Mix well.
Then add Crisco, milk, flour, vanilla and salt.
Beat until creamy (about 10 minutes).
Spread on cake.
You can sprinkle with nuts or coconut.

title: bonnie's pumpkin bread
directions: Add oil to sugar and beat.
Add eggs.
Add pumpkin alternately with dry ingredients.
Bake in greased tube pan at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Cool upright.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Drain carrots after cooking.
Cook onion in butter.
Stir in soup, salt and pepper.
Add cheese and carrots.
Put in 2-quart casserole.
Toss stuffing with melted butter and spoon over carrot mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain, chop and arrange in greased baking dish. Place chicken on top of broccoli.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder together.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle cheese over this and then sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Pour melted margarine over crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven until bubbling, about 30 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes, slice thin.
Place half of potatoes in baking dish.
Sprinkle with half mixture of salt, pepper and onion.
Then layer rest of potatoes, then sprinkle remaining salt, pepper and onion.
Cut butter and lay on top.
Add milk.
Bake in 350° oven until potatoes are tender.
Cover with cheese when potatoes are done.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine cream cheese and peanut butter in a large mixing bowl. Beat until fluffy.
Gradually add whipped topping and sugar. Spoon into crust and freeze for 8 hours.
Remove from freezer 15 to 20 minutes before serving.

title: brownies-fudgekins
directions: Melt oleo and chocolate over hot water; cool.
Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Beat eggs until light; add sugar, then chocolate mixture and blend.
Add flour, vanilla and nuts and mix well.
Bake in 8 x 8-inch pan for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: super mexican dip
directions: Heat oil in heavy skillet over medium heat.
Add beef and onions.
Cook until beef is brown, breaking up beef with fork, about 5 minutes.
Drain.
Season with salt and pepper.
Spoon half of the beans into a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Top with half the beef mixture, 1/2 chiles, 1/2 salsa and 1/2 Cheddar cheese. Repeat remaining ingredients.
Can be prepared 1 day ahead, covered and chilled.
Bake at 350° until heated through and cheese melts, about 30 minutes.
Top with sour cream, green onions and olives. Serve with chips.

title: a basic recipe for cream pies(recipe from general foods, unpublished)
directions: Blend egg yolks with tablespoon of milk.
Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt in a medium saucepan; gradually add remaining milk, stirring until smooth.
Bring to a full boil over medium heat and boil one minute; stir constantly.
Remove from heat and gradually stir in egg yolks; beat until smooth.
Bring to a boil over medium heat and boil for 2 minutes; stir constantly.
Remove from heat and pour into bowl.
Stir in butter and vanilla and cool.
Whip chilled cream until soft peaks will firm; fold into mixture and spoon into pie shell.

title: pistachio salad or watergate salad
directions: Mix pineapple and pudding mix.
Add marshmallows, nuts and Cool Whip.
Let stand in refrigerator.

title: taco salad
directions: Toss all ingredients together.
When ready to serve, add 1 package crushed taco chips.

title: holiday dill dip
directions: Blend mayo, parsley, minced onion, dill weed, Bon Appetit and cream cheese.
Stir in sour cream.
Refrigerate for several hours or overnight to allow flavors to blend.
Serve with chips or cut up vegetables (raw carrots, celery, green peppers, cucumbers, cauliflower, broccoli, etc.).

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1 cup warm water.
Combine milk and cold water and heat.
Pour hot liquid over margarine, sugar and salt; stir until dissolved.
Cool to lukewarm.
Stir in some flour and oats.
Add yeast.
Add more flour and oats to make soft dough form ball.
Cover, let rise in warm place about 1 hour (double in size).
Punch down.
Place on floured board; cut into loaves or rolls.
Put in pans.
Let rise.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Remove from baking pans.
Place on rack to cool, butter top while hot.
Enjoy!

title: sunshine slush
directions: Mix together and freeze (allow 2 days).
Mix with Sprite or 7-Up.

title: breakfast before casserole
directions: Brown sausage.
Drain well and set aside.
Beat eggs.
Add milk, salt and dried mustard to egg mixture.
Layer bread cubes, then sausage and cheese in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish coated with vegetable cooking spray.
Pour egg mixture over top. Refrigerate overnight.

title: lasagna
directions: Mash garlic clove with salt; brown with chopped onion in oil. Add ground beef and pork; cook until meat is done.
Add the tomato sauce, tomato paste and water.
Add Worcestershire sauce, Tabasco sauce, oregano, basil, bay leaf and pepper; simmer for 45 minutes. Cook and drain lasagna noodles (add small amount of oil to water while cooking).
Alternate layers of sauce, pasta, Mozzarella cheese and Ricotta cheese, beginning and ending with sauce.
Top with a generous sprinkling of grated Romano cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Cool 10 minutes before cutting.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Brown chicken breast in oil until chicken is cooked through. Add golden mushroom soup, soy sauce and garlic powder.
Mix well. Cook for a few minutes.
Stir in frozen broccoli.
Cover and cook until broccoli is tender, stirring occasionally.
Make rice as directed.
Serve over rice.

title: marble squares
directions: Beat until creamy the butter, sugars, vanilla and water.
Beat in the egg.
Sift and then mix in the dry ingredients.
Add the nuts and spread in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with the chips.
Bake at 375° for 1 minute.
Run knife through dough to marbleize.
Bake 12 to 14 minutes more.

title: 1 cup salad
directions: Mix and refrigerate overnight.

title: squirrel stew 2
directions: Cut the squirrels into serving size pieces and roll them in salt and peppered flour.
Brown them in cooking oil in a large stew pot.
Slowly add about 1 quart of water.
Add the bay leaf, garlic and vegetables.
Cook slowly for about 2 hours, until carrots and meat are tender.
Add water as needed during the cooking.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: cream puff dessert
directions: Melt margarine in water and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and add flour, stirring until you can form a ball.
Beat eggs into mixture, one at a time.
Spread in pan that is well greased.
I form a long narrow puff by dividing pan with well greased tinfoil down center.
Bake at 400° to 425° for 25 minutes until done.
Cool completely.
Beat cream cheese until softened.
Gradually add milk until smooth; add instant pudding and beat for 2 minutes.
Spread pudding mixture over cooled puff.
Top with layer of whipped topping, then add fresh fruit on top (red raspberries, sliced peaches, blueberries).
For 4th of July, make it red, white and blue.

title: new potato recipe
directions: Boil potatoes until tender; cut in half, if desired.
In separate saucepan, heat beans, milk and cream of chicken soup until hot.
Pour mixture over drained potatoes and sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Combine cake mix, nuts, melted butter and 1 egg.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan (greased).
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar, 2 eggs and vanilla.
Pour over cake foundation.
This topping will be soupy.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until top is pale brown and crusty.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Cream peanut butter and butter.
Add sugar until light and fluffy.
Add beaten eggs and vanilla.

title: spiced wassail
directions: Heat in large pan for 10 minutes sugar, water, cloves and cinnamon.
Add apple cider, orange juice and lemon juice.
Heat 10 more minutes.
(I put this beverage on low in a crock-pot and keep it serving temperature.)

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy and light in color.
Add sugar and beat until thoroughly dissolved.
Add 2 cans Carnation milk, 1 quart whipping cream and 3 tablespoons vanilla.
Pour into freezer can and finish filling with homogenized milk.

title: fried apple tarts
directions: Combine flour, salt and baking powder, cut in shortening until mixture is like coarse corn meal.
Sprinkle milk over mixture, stir lightly and form into a ball.
Divide into 8 parts, roll out to 1/4-inch thickness. Put about 2 tablespoons fruit (apples or peaches) to each pie.
Fold over fruit and seal by dipping fingers in water and pressing edges together.
Then press edges with a fork.
Fry in oil 1/2-inch deep until golden brown.
Turn only once.
Drain on paper towels.
Very good!

title: lemon delight
directions: Mix cheese and sugar. Add Cool Whip. Line a 13 x 9-inch cake pan with graham crackers. Cover with one-half of cheese mixture. Mix pudding with milk. Top with another layer of crackers. Pour in pudding. Spread remaining cheese mixture over pudding. May use any pudding flavor desired.

title: mexican spoon bread
directions: Bake at 325° for 45 minutes in 12 x 8 x 3-inch pan.

title: noodles
directions: Make a well in flour and add egg and rest of ingredients and mix well.
Dough will be stiff and, using quite a bit of flour on board, roll out dough.
Cut into squares and let set for 20 minutes with plenty of flour before slicing thin with sharp knife. Dry for 1 hour, if desired, or may cook immediately in broth.

title: caramel corn
directions: Pop popcorn according to directions.
In pan, mix brown sugar, syrup, margarine and salt and cook on medium heat until boiling. Cook for 5 minutes.
Take off heat and add soda.
Pour over popcorn and place in covered pan.
Put in 200° oven for 1/2 hour.
Stir well and return to oven for 30 minutes.

title: spinach with sour cream and cheese(microwave)
directions: Make slit in top of packages of frozen spinach.
Place packages in circle in microwave and cook on High for 12 minutes. Pour spinach into colander and drain well.
(Use back of spoon to push out moisture.)
Place spinach in 3-quart casserole.
Add onion soup mix and sour cream.
Cook (uncovered) for
7 minutes on High.
Stir and sprinkle cheese on top.
Heat 2 to 2 1/2 minutes until cheese is melted.
Serves 8.

title: raisin squares
directions: Boil
raisins
and water until almost dry.
Remove from heat. Add oleo
and
let it melt.
Mix together in a bowl the sugar, cloves, cinnamon, salt, baking powder and flour.
Pour in oleo and water and raisin
mixture.	Mix
well
(it will be stiff).	Spread on
greased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 10 to
minutes. Spread
with
powdered
sugar icing while warm.
Approximately 60 calories per square.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Put first six ingredients in a salad bowl.
Mix lemon juice, sugar and mayonnaise.
Pour over salad and mix well.

title: jim's famous bologna sandwich
directions: Put together as a sandwich and enjoy.

title: black-eyed sue cookies
directions: Combine biscuit mix, pudding mix, cooking oil and eggs.
Mix well.
Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Top each with chocolate mint or kiss; press to flatten.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 12 to 14 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: pepperoni rolls
directions: Thaw bread at room temperature.
Cut the loaf in half (makes two rolls).
Roll out on floured surface (I use wax paper).
Layer with sauteed onions, 1st cheese, pepperoni and 2nd cheese.
Close roll and brush with egg yolk and milk.
Bake at 325° until golden brown, 15 to 20 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Warm 1/2 cup milk and melt butter in it.
Add sugar, salt and flour and remaining 1/2 cup milk.
Dissolve yeast in warm water and add to mixture.
Add eggs last.
Stir well.
Cover and place in refrigerator overnight.
Two hours before serving, drop by spoonfuls in a well-greased Bundt pan.
Melt 2 to 3 tablespoons oleo and pour warm oleo over dough.
Let rise.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: easy corn fritters
directions: Mix together beaten egg yolks, flour, salt and sugar.
Drain corn and add to other.
Now add the egg whites which have been whipped to a stiff froth.
Drop by tablespoon into pan where butter is sizzling.
Makes 18 small fritters.

title: lemon bars
directions: Cut together 2 cups flour, butter and 3/4 cup confectioners sugar until crumbly.
Pat into bottom 13 x 9-inch pan, building side edges to 1/2-inch high.
Bake 20 minutes at 350° until golden. Beat eggs.
Add sugar, baking powder, salt, 4 tablespoons flour and lemon juice.
Beat 3 minutes.
While crust is hot, pour over it and spread.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
While warm, sift confectioners sugar over top.
Cut into bars.

title: low-fat chicken "fingers"
directions: Soak chicken strips in skim milk for 3 minutes.
Combine next 3 ingredients and roll chicken in crumbs.
Spray a baking sheet with Pam and lay strips, without touching each other, on sheet. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: baked eggplant slices
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cut eggplant crosswise into slices 1/2-inch thick.
Spread both sides with mixture of remaining ingredients.
Place on baking sheet; bake until tender, about 12 minutes, turning once.
Garnish with chopped parsley or chervil.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Beat all ingredients in blender for 1 minute.
Pour mix into 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: taco chicken
directions: Melt butter.
Add chicken and the onion; cook until tender. Mix and cook the mushroom soup, chicken soup, broth, tomatoes and green chilies.
Heat the oven to 350°.
Line bottom of pan with half bag of chips.
Layer chicken next; pour soup mixture on top of chicken.
Add the rest of Doritos chips.
Sprinkle with grated cheese; bake for approximately 30 minutes.

title: helen gardner's country fair carrot cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except carrots and pecans, in a large bowl with mixer on low speed.
Mix well.
Increase speed to medium and beat 2 minutes.
Scrape sides of bowl occasionally.
Stir in carrots and pecans.

title: lentil soup
directions: Heat butter in saucepan. When hot, add celery and onion; cover and cook 3 minutes over medium heat. Add carrot, spices and garlic; cover and continue cooking for 3 minutes. Add lentils and chicken stock; season well and mix. Bring to a boil. Cook soup, partially covered, 2 hours over low heat. Sixteen minutes before end of cooking, add rice and finish cooking. Serve.

title: hot fudge pudding
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and 1/4 c. cocoa. Whisk in milk, butter and vanilla.
Spread into greased 8 inch x 8 inch glass baking dish.
Mix brown sugar and 1/4 c. cocoa. Sprinkle over batter. Pour
boiling water over mixture.
Do not stir.
Bake 30 minutes at 350 degrees.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: easy creamed chicken
directions: Remove skin and bones from chicken; dice.
Saute celery, green pepper and onion in butter in a heavy skillet.
Add chicken and remaining ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Cook on low heat, stirring frequently, for 30 minutes. Serve on rice or noodles.

title: date orange cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs; mix dry ingredients and add alternately with milk.
Bake 2 hours at 275°.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Combine broth, broccoli and onion.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Add salt and pepper.
Stir in milk and cream of mushroom soup.
Heat until the soup thickens.

title: mama's no fail meringue
directions: Beat egg whites until they turn white.
Add sugar gradually while beating.
Add vanilla.
Beat until you think it is ready - then beat some more.
(I use 4 egg whites per pie with 8 Tbsp sugar and 2 tsp vanilla.)
Spread over top of pie or pudding and brown in hot oven.

title: maw roller's apple rings
directions: Put in baking dish.
Place in a 400° oven.
Let get bubbling hot.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Brown ground beef.
Add the cans of soup to the beef and set aside.
Butter the bottom and sides of a 9 inch x 13 inch pan.
Cut the vegetables into 1/4 inch slices and layer the pan with them.
Pour the ground beef mixture over the vegetables and spread it evenly.
Cover tightly with foil and bake 1 hour or until vegetables are done.
Remove foil.
Add your favorite cheese on top, put back in oven to melt.

title: blonde brownies(double for 9 x 13-inch pan)
directions: Soften margarine in the pan you are to bake in.
Measure flour, salt and baking powder together.
In separate bowl, put brown sugar and melted margarine (just soft) and mix.
Add egg, egg yolk and vanilla.
Mix flour into sugar and eggs. Then add nuts.
Spread in the pan where you melted the margarine, dusted with flour.
Drop chocolate chips generously on top and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Cut while still warm.

title: a new twist on potatoes au gratin
directions: Use a "Mandolin" to slice the potatoes very thin, taking care to protect your fingers so you don't slice them along with the potatoes. Put in deep pot and cover with milk. Bring to boil and simmer until potatoes are par-cooked. Season the potatoes with salt and pepper. Layer the potatoes in a buttered casserole dish, alternating them with the cheese and onion. Dot with butter. Add heavy cream and top with sprinkling of bread crumbs. Bake in slow oven until the potatoes are cooked and the dish is slightly browned, about 30 minutes at 325°.

title: pralines
directions: Combine sugar, soda, buttermilk and salt in a 3 1/2-quart heavy saucepan.
Cook for about 5 minutes over high heat or to 210° on a candy thermometer.
Stir often, scraping the bottom of the pan.
The mixture will foam up.
Add butter or margarine and pecans.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Gradually add onion and oil, then poppy seed.
Refrigerate.
This keeps well in the refrigerator. Very good!
Makes about 2 cups.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine Crisco and boiling water.
Stir until Crisco is melted.
Combine eggs, sugar and salt.
Beat in cold water.
Soften yeast in lukewarm water.
Combine the 3 mixtures and add flour.
Dough will be too soft to knead.
Just mix with heavy spoon until flour is completely mixed in.
Cover and chill overnight.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Use 1 cup water with the Jell-O.
Mix and let refrigerate.

title: chili
directions: Mix all ingredients in large pan and simmer 5 hours.

title: now famous cheese ring
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Mold into ring and chill.
When ready to serve, fill ring with strawberry preserves or red pepper jelly.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into pan and bake until golden brown, about 25 minutes.
Cut into pieces.
Serve warm.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Cover jelly roll pan with crescent rolls and bake at 350° until brown (7 to 8 minutes).
Cool 10 to 12 minutes.

title: fruit slaw
directions: In a large salad bowl, combine shredded cabbage, orange sections, halved red grapes and sliced celery.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt butter and mix with stuffing mix.
Spread 1/2 in casserole dish.
Combine squash, carrot, onion, pimento and sugar. Spread mixture over stuffing mix.
Combine soup with sour cream and spread over squash.
Spread other 1/2 stuffing mix over top. Bake at 350° to 400° for 25 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
Cut into wedges and place in large bowl.
Do not peel.
Cut bad spots off of potatoes.
Add hard-boiled eggs after they cool and are sliced.
Mix onion and pickles and add to potatoes and eggs.
Stir in mustard and mayonnaise.
Add more mayonnaise if needed.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Place in refrigerator for at least 1 hour before serving.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Grease an oblong baking dish with butter.
Place slices of bread or English muffins in bottom of dish.
Brown and crumble 1 pound sausage in a large mixing bowl.

title: microwave cheesy chowder
directions: Put potatoes, broccoli, carrot, onion, garlic, pepper and water in a 3 quart microwave safe bowl.
Cover with lid or vented plastic wrap.
Microwave on high 8-10 minutes, stirring once, until vegetable are crisp-tender.
Add milk, beans and soup. Cover and microwave on high 6-8 minutes, stirring once, until vegetables are tender.
Add cheese and hot pepper sauce, stirring until cheese is melted.
Serve hot.

title: simple cheese ball
directions: Mix cheeses, onion and Ranch dressing in food processor until well blended. Take out and roll in ball. Roll ball in chopped pecans.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: Fold all together and chill.

title: puffy chile rellenos
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease cookie sheet.
Cut chiles lengthwise to make 10 pieces.
Remove seeds and ribs.
Cut cheese into 10 (3 x 1/2 x 1/2-inch) pieces.
Wrap each piece of cheese with a chile.
Press or roll each biscuit into a 5-inch circle. Place chile and cheese on biscuit; fold over.
Pinch ends to seal. Place seam side up on prepared cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until light brown.

title: chocolate sheath cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar together in a large bowl.
In saucepan bring oleo, Crisco, cocoa and water to a rapid boil.
Pour over dry ingredients and add buttermilk, eggs, soda and vanilla.
Pour into 16 x 11-inch greased and floured pan and bake 20 minutes at 400°.
Five minutes before removing from oven mix icing.

title: coconut muffins
directions: Cream sugar and margarine and then eggs together.
Blend in other ingredients.
Divide evenly into 12 greased muffin pans and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: paprikahuhner(chicken with paprika - sour cream sauce)
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Saute onion.
Do not brown.
Salt chicken pieces and saute slowly.
Do not brown.
Sprinkle with paprika and stir well.
Saute 3 more minutes.
Add broth and tomato juice. Bring to a boil. Cover and reduce heat.
Simmer for 35 minutes.
Remove chicken and debone.
Blend flour and sour cream.
Stir into sauce.
Return chicken to pan and bring to a boil.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Serve with spatzle (noodles).

title: calico beans
directions: Cook meat.
Drain kidney, Great Northern and lima beans. Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, or simmer in crock-pot.

title: cheesy potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour over hash browns.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 45 minutes and 15 minutes uncovered.

title: broccoli-cauliflower casserole
directions: Thaw the broccoli and cauliflower and separate. Melt the butter. Cook the onion with the butter. Mix vegetables together. Add the rice, soups, water and cheese. Bake, covered, at 325° for 1 hour. Uncover slightly to brown.

title: clay
directions: Mix salt and 2/3 cup water together.
Stir over heat 3 to 4 minutes.
Remove from heat and add cornstarch and 1/2 cup cold water; stir until smooth.
If it's runny, keep cooking until it congeals.

title: baked ziti with veggies
directions: Prepare pasta as label directs; drain.
Meanwhile, in 12-inch skillet over medium heat in hot oil, cook carrots, broccoli and green pepper 5 minutes.
Add garlic, salt and pepper; cook 5 minutes longer or until vegetables are tender, stirring occasionally.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease 2-quart casserole dish.
In large bowl, toss cooked vegetables with pasta and cheeses.
Spoon into prepared casserole dish.
Bake 30 minutes or until mixture is hot and bubbly.

title: cranberry-orange salad(low sugar)
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water and immediately add cranberry sauce, chopping to blend into Jell-O.
Add all other ingredients and pour into mold.
Chill.

title: stuffed round steak
directions: Very lightly salt round steak or use tenderizer salt.
Grate carrots.
Add to prepared bread cubes.
Add sage, thyme and grated onion.
Mix bouillon cube in water until dissolved.
Add to bread and carrots.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix together. Bake at 300° for 30 minutes or until light brown and bubbly.

title: applesauce carrot cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix together the flour, soda, cinnamon and nuts.
Beat eggs; stir in oil, sugar and vanilla.
Add applesauce and carrots to this mixture, stirring just to moisten.
Mix together the flour mixture and egg mixture.
Fold in raisins and nuts.
Pour batter into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan sprayed with vegetable spray.
Bake 45 minutes.
This cake serves 24 to 30 people.
Cut slices small.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Place fresh blackberries in bottom of 8 x 8 greased baking pan.
Combine flour, 1/2 cup sugar, baking powder, milk, vanilla and melted butter and pour over berries.
Mix hot water with 1/2 cup sugar and pour over the mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix with a spoon. Spread mixture on top of the baked pastry, then sprinkle with grated rind of 1 lemon. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, then sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: coconut self crust pie
directions: Combine all ingredients except coconut, in blender. Blend on low for 3 minutes. Pour into greased 9 inch pan. Let set for 5 minutes. Sprinkle coconut on top. Bake at 350 for 40 minutes.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Peel sweet potatoes and cut into quarters.
Put sweet potatoes in boiler; cover with water.
Add 2 1/2 cups sugar, flavoring and butter.
Cook until they are candied.
It takes about 1 hour.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all together and simmer 15 minutes.

title: sherry's carrot cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs until thoroughly blended.
Sift together flour, soda, salt and cinnamon into mixture and beat until smooth.
Stir in all of the remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 1/2 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: blueberry tea cake
directions: Sift 2 cups flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
Beat 1/4 cup margarine with 3/4 cup sugar; add egg.
Add milk and flour mixture alternately.
This mixture will be very stiff.
Carefully fold in berries.
Pour into greased 9 x 9-inch baking dish.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: In a large skillet, saute onion and green pepper in margarine until tender.
Add tomatoes, mushrooms, olives and oregano.
Add ground meat.
Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook spaghetti; add all vegetables.
Sprinkle with olive oil and Season-All.
Don't be skimpy with seasonings.
Can add any vegetable you like.

title: barbecue hot dogs
directions: In oil lightly brown franks and onions.
Add all other ingredients, cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Serve with noodles or rice.

title: miracle soup
directions: Cover vegetables with water; bring to a boil.
Add soup mix; boil soup 10 minutes.
Lower heat and simmer until the vegetables are soft.
You can eat all you want if you are on a diet and not gain weight.
Very good.

title: casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in margarine.
Add 1 cup hot water and pour over dressing mix.
Toss lightly.
Spread meat (uncooked) in 9 x 13-inch pan and place first mixture over meat.
Mix soups (no water), pour over dressing mix and bake 1 good hour at 350°.
Do not cover.

title: gingersnap cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together shortening and sugar until well mixed.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat well.
Add molasses, then dry ingredients that have been combined.
Chill dough; roll into balls and into sugar.
Place on ungreased sheet and bake for approximately 12 to 15 minutes.
(Makes approximately 3 dozen.)

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Cut rhubarb in 1-inch pieces and cover bottom of a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle strawberry Jell-O over rhubarb (dry).
Spread cake mix (dry) over Jell-O.
Dot butter over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Top with Cool Whip when cooled, or ice cream while warm, as you serve it.

title: cabbage dressing
directions: Put into jar and shake well. Use over shredded cabbage. Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: boiled shrimp
directions: Boil 20 minutes; add shrimp and cook until done.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Mash beans well in juice.
Beat eggs.
Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 300°.
Makes 3 pies.
Will freeze well.

title: taco dip
directions: Spread layer of sour cream.
Put taco sauce over sour cream. Cut up onion finely.
Spread over taco sauce.
Spread cheese over onion layer.
Put on lettuce.
Serve with Cool Ranch Doritos.

title: sunday chicken
directions: Spread chicken in greased baking dish.
Mix gravy and broth and heat thoroughly.
Add chicken soup, onions and Worcestershire sauce to gravy.
Heat until bubbly and pour over chicken.
Top with Parmesan and then chow mein noodles.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Let cream cheese reach room temperature.
Blend cream cheese, Marshmallow Creme and orange juice.
Place in a serving dish. Wonderful with all fruits.

title: creamy cornbread
directions: Blend all together well.
Pour into greased/Pam square baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; add garlic powder and onion salt.
Crush one half bag of chips in the bottom of a large casserole dish. Put half of meat mixture on crushed chips.
Mix soups together; pour half over meat.
Pour one cup of cheese over soup.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine Cheddar cheese (the type found in a cup by the cream cheese) and room temperature cream cheese.
Add cloves of fresh garlic, using a garlic press.
Mix all together; refrigerate until firm.
Form mixture into a ball; roll in chili powder.
Serve with crackers.

title: chicken and cheese
directions: Rinse chicken and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place 6 to 8 slices of Swiss cheese on chicken.
Shake bag of stuffing evenly on chicken and cheese.

title: french banana pancakes
directions: Sift flour and confectioners sugar into a mixing bowl. Add milk, eggs, butter, vanilla and salt; beat until smooth. Heat a lightly greased 6-inch skillet; add about 3 Tbsp. batter, spreading to almost cover bottom of skillet. Cook until lightly browned; turn and brown the other side. remove to a wire rack. Repeat with remaining batter (makes 10-12 pancakes), greasing skillet as needed.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Use the metal blades with the food processor.
Put all ingredients in a work bowl and use 4 short pulses to almost combine them.
Run spatula around inside of work bowl and use 1 to 2 more short pulses until just combined.
Do not over process.
Spoon batter into 10 greased 1/2 cup muffin cups.
Do not smooth surfaces.
They should be very irregular.
Bake at 400° until light brown about 25 minutes.
Immediately turn onto wire rack and serve hot.

title: hot texas chili
directions: Braise hamburger; when half done add onion, crushed red pepper, garlic and sugar.
When onions are brown, add paprika, salt, cumin, cayenne pepper, flour, m.s.g. (this stuff is pure protein, use it) and
quart water.
Simmer in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
No Beans!
No Beans!
No Beans!

title: surprise date bread
directions: Pour water over dates; let stand 5 minutes.
Sift together flour, soda, salt and sugar.
Add date mixture, egg, cheese, vanilla and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350°
for 45 minutes to 50 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool on rack.
Makes 1 loaf.
Very good served with softened cream cheese.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Stew chicken.
Melt margarine and stir in dressing.
In large dish,
put a layer of crumbs, a layer of chicken and can of mushroom
soup
diluted
with
chicken broth.
Put another layer of
crumbs,
layer
of chicken and cream of chicken soup (diluted same).
Top
with
crumbs.
Bake
at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: moussaka
directions: Peel eggplants; slice 1/4-inch thick. Brush rimmed cookie sheet with oil. Coat each slice of eggplant on both sides with oil; place on cookie sheet.
Broil close to broiler until brown. Turn; brush with oil, if necessary.
Brown the other side. Repeat with all the eggplant slices.

title: oven roasted potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes in pieces.
Place in plastic bag with oil and soup mix.
Shake until potatoes are coated.
Place in baking dish and bake uncovered at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, combine 3/4 cup sugar, flour, 3 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Blend in milk, butter and vanilla; beat until smooth.
Pour batter into 8 or 9-inch square pan or baking dish.
In small bowl, combine remaining 1/2 cup sugar, 1/2 cup brown sugar and remaining 4 teaspoons cocoa.
Mix these dry ingredients well; sprinkle evenly over batter.
Slowly pour hot water over top.
Do not stir.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until cake center is almost set.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Spoon into dessert dishes, spooning sauce from bottom of pan over top.
Serve with ice cream or whipped cream, if desired.

title: dutch oven cabbage
directions: Slice unripe, unpeeled tomatoes.
Dip in flour, sprinkle salt and pepper.
Fry in vegetable oil until brown on both sides.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix corn, beaten egg, 1 cup cracker crumbs, milk and salt and pepper to taste.
Mix 1/2 cup cracker crumbs and melted butter and sprinkle over mixture.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 30 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Do not drain pineapple. Refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: chicken gumbo soup
directions: Combine all ingredients, cover and cook about two hours.
It can be made in a slow cooker on low setting for two hours.
Yields 1 1/2 quarts.

title: white batter bread
directions: Scald milk, stir in salt, sugar and margarine.	Let cool to lukewarm.
Measure warm water into large bowl.
Add yeast and stir until dissolved.
Add lukewarm milk mixture.
Stir in flour.

title: pot-roasted hamburger loaf with carrots
directions: Mix meat, egg, 1 1/4 teaspoon salt, pepper, bread crumbs and milk.
Shape into a flat loaf.
Dredge with flour and brown on both sides in hot fat in a heavy skillet with a cover.
Add water and remaining 1/2 teaspoon salt.
