Cover and simmer 15 minutes. Then add carrots and cook 1/2 hour longer, or until carrots are tender.
Arrange on hot platter with Potato Pancakes.

title: savory brown rice
directions: Melt margarine in large skillet.
Add onions and mushrooms. Cook and stir until onions are tender.
Dissolve bouillon cube in hot water and add to onion mixture.
Bring to boil.
Stir in rice; simmer 5 minutes.
Cover; remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour and salt in shortening.
Use two knives until particles are of small peas.
Sprinkle in water, one tablespoon at a time, tossing with fork until all flour is moistened.
One to 2 teaspoons of water can be added if necessary.
Roll pastry into halves and shape into 2 rounds.
Prebake the shell slightly about 7 to 10 minutes.

title: frozen puddingwiches
directions: Add milk gradually to peanut butter in deep narrow bowl, blending until smooth.
Add pudding mix.
Beat slowly with hand beater or at lowest speed of electric mixer for 2 minutes or until well blended.
Spread filling 1/2-inch thick on 12 of the crackers.
Wrap and freeze until firm, about 2 hours.

title: lefse
directions: Peel potatoes, cook and mash with butter, salt and cream.
Let cool.
Mix in flour.
On lightly floured board, roll out rounds, about 8 to 12-inch diameter, paper thin.
Bake on ungreased griddle on moderate heat until lightly brown.
Turn once.
Takes only about 1 minute per side.
To eat, spread with butter and sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Roll up and enjoy.

title: golden parmesan potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes; cut into quarters.
Combine flour, cheese, salt and pepper in plastic bag.
Shake a few pieces at a time in bag to coat well.
Melt margarine in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Place potatoes in a single layer in pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour, turning potatoes once during baking.
Serve when golden brown.

title: chocolate dipped frosted strawberries
directions: Prepare 2 or more layers of paper towels to drain washed strawberries.
Wash and clean berries.
Cut caps off, making a flat surface on berries.
Also, cut cross down 1/3 of the pointed end of each berry.
Drain berries on paper towels for about 1 hour or until completely dry.
(Chocolate will not adhere to berries if berries are wet.) Wrap a cookie sheet in aluminum foil.
Melt about half of the chocolate morsels in small dish in the microwave or in a small pan on the stove or in top of double boiler over hot water, stirring with chop stick until smooth.
Do not add any water, milk or other liquid.
Mix cream cheese, confectioners sugar and vanilla, adding the confectioners sugar to cream cheese in small amounts until thick.
Dip a berry into melted chocolate, covering bottom of berry and about 1/4 up the sides.
Place immediately on foil covered cookie sheet.
Melt additional chocolate as needed.

title: sweet potato and pecan casserole
directions: Boil potatoes until done; mash.
Add margarine, eggs, meal, sugar, milk and spices in buttered baking dish.
Top with marshmallows and pecans.
Bake in 350° oven until marshmallows are melted and browned.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add brown sugar and spread evenly over bottom.
Lay a complete wheel of pineapple in the center with maraschino cherry in the center of pineapple.
Place half wheels around with pecans between.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Place cucumbers and onions in a bowl.
Sprinkle salt over. Let stand 3 hours.
Drain in colander.
Heat sugar and vinegar until dissolved.
Add celery seed, turmeric and alum.
Put cucumbers in a glass jar and pour brine over.
Will keep in the refrigerator a very long time.

title: chicken delicious
directions: Place all ingredients in slow cooker; cook 3 hours.
Serve over hot noodles.

title: brown rice plus
directions: Saute onions, broccoli and green pepper in butter, about 3 minutes.
Mix in rice, tomatoes, cheese, parsley, garlic, salt and pepper to taste.
Cook 4 minutes longer, covered, until vegetables are tender-crisp.
Serves 4.

title: grape punch
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in punch bowl.
Add ice.

title: honey apricot bread(norma jean's favorite)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, brown sugar, salt and baking powder.
Mix egg, honey, milk and margarine; add to flour mixture. Stir just until moistened.
Stir in cereal and apricots.

title: prize meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients; mix well. Press firmly into ungreased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Mix zucchini, sugar, oil and eggs.
Combine dry ingredients. Mix well.
Add nuts.
Grease and flour pans.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 3 loaves.

title: spanish rice
directions: Saute onion and pepper in oil.
Add a box of Rice-A-Roni to the skillet.
Stir over medium heat.
Add the other ingredients listed, plus water to suit yourself and lower heat.
Simmer, covered, until rice is done.
Add extra water if necessary.

title: corn relish
directions: Cut corn off the cob.
Chop rest of the vegetables fine.
Mix all together and boil 25 minutes.
Thick with flour, mixed in water, to make paste.
Continue to boil 15 minutes longer.
Seal in sterilized jars.

title: green pepper jelly
directions: Put half the green peppers and half the vinegar into blender container.
Cover and process until pepper is liquefied.
Pour into a large saucepan.
Repeat with remaining peppers and vinegar.
Add the red pepper, sugar and salt.
Bring to a boil and add pectin. Boil until it thickens when dropped from a spoon, about 20 minutes. Add a few drops of green food coloring if desired.
Pour into sterilized hot jars and seal (follow directions with pectin).

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Sprinkle the top with brown sugar and top with strips of bacon.
Heat beans in 350° oven until beans are bubbly, then turn oven down to 250° and simmer for 2 hours.

title: tuna and potato chips
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Empty soup into baking dish.
Add milk and mix well.
Add tuna, 2 cups of potato chips and peas; mix lightly.
Sprinkle remaining potato chips over top.
Bake 25 minutes.

title: cranberry-orange muffins
directions: In a medium bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Make a well in the center.
In a small bowl, combine egg, orange juice and oil.
Add to the flour mixture. Stir until batter is moistened and lumpy.
Fold in cranberries and orange rind.
Put in muffin tins, which have been sprayed with Pam. Fill 3/4 full and sprinkle tops with a little sugar.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all together. Roll into 3/4-inch balls. Bake on oiled cookie sheets at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: caramel dip for sliced apples
directions: Heat all, except vanilla, over medium heat, stirring until sugar dissolves, about 5 minutes.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour into dipping bowl.
Cut up apple in slices and pour caramel over all.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Combine all ingredients, except apples. Beat together until smooth. Pare and slice apples. Grease tube pan. Pour 1/2 of batter into pan. Top with 1/2 of the apples. Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon. Pour remaining batter over apples and top with remaining apples. Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Cool. Turn onto serving plate.

title: 7-up batter for fish
directions: Cover fish which have been dipped in water in 1 cup of the dry pancake mix.
Let set for 20 minutes.
Dip fish into 7-Up and 1 cup of the pancake mix.
Deep fry.

title: cream cheese surprises
directions: Cut cold cream cheese in 32 equal pieces.
Grease hands and flatten cubes with thumb, then wrap each around an olive.
Roll in hands to make a smooth ball, then roll in nuts.
Chill before serving.

title: baked chili beans
directions: Barely cover beans with water after dinner.
Drain and replace the water before bedtime.
In the morning, bring to a boil and boil 2 minutes.
Pour off water; refill with new water, adding salt and soda.
Simmer until almost done, or let soak until 4 hours before dinner.

title: biscuits and sausage gravy
directions: In large skillet, brown and crumble sausage; drain.
Set aside.
Melt margarine on medium heat.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
Stirring constantly, start pouring milk.
Keep pouring until desired consistency is achieved.
Add sausage.
Serve over biscuits.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger meat in skillet; drain.
Add spaghetti sauce and cottage cheese.
While browning meat, cook noodles and drain. Place in baking dish, starting with a layer of meat mixture, noodle layer next and Mozzarella cheese on top.
Cook at 325° for 30 minutes or until cheese is bubbling.

title: basic buttercream frosting
directions: Cream butter until fluffy; beat in sugar, a little at a time, adding alternately with cream.
Mix in vanilla and salt and beat until satiny and of good spreading consistency.
If mixture seems too stiff, thin with a little additional cream.

title: curried chicken and rice salad
directions: In a small bowl, combine first 5 ingredients.
In a salad bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Pour dressing over salad. Serve on salad plates lined with lettuce.

title: crock-pot beef burgundy
directions: Dredge beef with flour and brown on all sides in a skillet lightly coated with oil.
Combine steak, seasonings, bouillon and Burgundy in slow-cooking pot.
Cover and cook on low for 6 to 8 hours or until meat is tender.
Turn control to high.
Add mushrooms; cook on high for 15 minutes.
To thicken the sauce, if desired, dissolve cornstarch in 2 tablespoons cold water and add it with the mushrooms.
Serve over cooked egg noodles or just eat it like a stew!
Serves 6.

title: pineapple orange sherbet
directions: Mix the orange drink and gelatin in blender or mixer bowl. Pour in ice cream freezer and mix until very cold.
Add the milk and turn freezer until it begins to freeze.
Add pineapple and continue turning until frozen.

title: orange julius
directions: Combine ingredients in blender.
Put on low speed. Then turn it up to high, putting 4 to 5 ice cubes in (one at a time).

title: real crazy cake
directions: Stir the first 5 ingredients into an 8-inch square pan.
Make 3 depressions in dry ingredients.
Pour vinegar into one, vanilla into another and salad oil into the third.
Gradually add water; mix well until smooth.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 35 minutes.
When cool, frost or serve with ice cream and chocolate sauce.

title: hi-ho cheeri-o cookies
directions: Heat butterscotch pieces and peanut butter in a 3-quart saucepan until melted.
Mix in marshmallows, cereal and coconut. Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Let stand until firm, about 1 hour.
Makes approximately 3 dozen cookies.

title: tortellini alfredo
directions: Cook tortellini al dente.
Saute chopped shallots in approximately 1 teaspoon of your favorite vegetable oil.
Add white wine and cook over medium heat until reduced by half.
Stir in heavy cream and keep stirring with a wooden spoon until bubbling.
It will naturally thicken as it cooks.
When it starts to thicken, add fresh grated cheese.
Cook and stir until sauce is the consistency you like.
Add warm tortellini and salt and pepper.
Makes 4 appetizer portions.

title: kahlua
directions: Bring the first 3 ingredients to a boil, then simmer for 1 hour.
Cool.
Add the vodka and vanilla extract.
Refrigerate.

title: hearty tuna casserole(how to microwave)
directions: Drain and flake the tuna.
Set aside.
Cook noodles according to package directions.
Drain and rinse in hot water.

title: cherry crisscross
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, margarine, baking powder, baking soda and salt as for pie dough.
Beat the eggs, vanilla and milk. Add it to the dry ingredients. Will be dry.
Take 2/3 of dough and press on cookie sheet.
Put cherry pie filling on dough.
Roll out 1/3 of dough.
Cut in strips and put on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: skillet swiss steak
directions: Coat steak with flour.
Brown on both sides in a small amount of oil in skillet.
Arrange onion over steak.
Cover with tomatoes.
Combine remaining ingredients with 1 soup can of water in bowl.
Pour over all.

title: gooey
directions: Brown hamburger and onion together. Drain. Salt and pepper to taste. Add the rest of the ingredients. Mix well and heat in oven or on top of stove until cheese is melted.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream the butter; add sugar gradually and cream well.
Sift salt and baking powder with flour; add milk gradually to the sugar mixture, then the well-beaten egg, then vanilla and flour gradually to make soft dough.
Turn onto a floured board.
Roll 1/4 inch thick.
Cut with floured cookie cutter.
Place on a slightly buttered pan and bake in a hot oven until slightly brown.

title: dynamite barbecue
directions: Generously sprinkle pork with garlic salt.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
Using pan drippings, make gravy (if additional gravy needed, use packaged or ready-made pork gravy); pour gravy into large saucepan.
Add all other ingredients, blending well; slice pork and add to sauce.
Simmer, uncovered, stirring often, for about 1 hour.
Serve on toasted onion rolls.

title: chicken 'n red potatoes
directions: Spray Pam on a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the seasonings together. Coat chicken pieces with seasonings.
Place potatoes on bottom of pan and cut chicken pieces on top.
Put dabs of margarine on top of the chicken.
Pour water into pan and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until potatoes are soft.
Baste chicken with juices in pan periodically.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Mix chopped nuts, brown sugar and cinnamon together.
Grease and flour Bundt cake pan. Pour in half of batter, then cinnamon, nut mixture, then remaining batter.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: sweet zucchini relish
directions: In a large bowl, mix zucchini, onion and peppers.
Sprinkle with salt and let stand overnight.
Drain and cover with cold water. Drain well and press liquid out. Put in large cooker. Add all other ingredients. Cook gently 1/2 hour.
Put in hot jars. Seal in hot water bath, processing 10 to 15 minutes.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Stem mushrooms; arrange on baking dish.
Combine all other ingredients and fill mushrooms.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, then set oven to broil for 2 minutes.
Serve them hot with mustard.

title: crunchy apple salad
directions: Place apples, bananas and lemon juice in a bowl and toss.
Add pineapple, raisins and pecans.
Toss slightly.
Add mayonnaise. Toss just until mayonnaise is mixed thoroughly.
Spoon into individual lettuce cups or into a salad dish.
Serves 6.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix food coloring with cocoa.
Cream sugar and shortening together.
Add whole eggs and color paste.
With mixer, blend in buttermilk, flour, salt and vanilla.
Remove from mixer and add by hand the vinegar and soda.
Bake in 2 well-greased and floured 8-inch layer pans at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs until light; add sugar and beat again.
Add molasses, melted margarine, pecans salt and vanilla.
Mix well and pour into pie shell.
Bake in 400 degree oven for 10 minutes; lower heat to 350 degrees and cook until custard is set.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream butter, sugar and slightly beaten eggs.
Add flour and buttermilk.
Pour into unbaked pie crust. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325°, bake about 30 to 40 minutes more.

title: honey glazed carrots
directions: Cook carrots in small amount of boiling, salted water about 10 minutes or until tender.
Drain.
In a skillet, melt butter; add sugar and honey.
Simmer mixture for 2 minutes.
Add carrots and cook over low heat, turning until well glazed, about 5 minutes. Serves 6.

title: easy dessert
directions: Spread pie filling in 9 x 13-inch ungreased cake pan.
Spread pineapple, juice and all, over pie filling.
Spread dry cake mix over pineapple.
Pour melted butter over top.
Bake as directed on cake mix box.
Top with Dream Whip.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening, brown sugar and vanilla.
Add egg and beat well.
Add flour, soda and salt.
Mix well, then stir in chocolate chips and walnuts.
Spread in greased 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: cheesecake pie
directions: Beat cream cheese. Beat in eggs and sugar until smooth. Mix in 1/2 c. of the concentrate and reserve rest for the glaze. Pour into baked shell. Bake 30 minutes in preheated 350° oven. Spread warm glaze over hot pie. Chill at least 8 hours.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add thawed strawberries, pineapple and mashed bananas.
Pour half of mixture in a 13 x 9-inch pan; chill until firm.
Spread sour cream on top like frosting.
Cover with remaining jello mixture and chill until firm.

title: e-z dessert
directions: Break angel food cake into bite size pieces.
Fold broken Heath bars into Cool Whip, then combine Cool Whip with cake pieces.
Chill until serving time.

title: delicious sugar cookies
directions: Beat eggs, powdered sugar, granulated sugar and vanilla together.
In separate bowl, combine flour; cut in shortening. Add 1 teaspoon salt, soda and cream of tartar to flour and shortening.
Add oil, then egg mixture.
Beat well.
The dough will be soft (color if desired).
Roll into small balls and press with plastic end of thread spool covered with granulated sugar on a greased and floured cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Do not let them brown.

title: tortellini salad with meat
directions: Cook tortellini and pasta according to package. Drain with cold water. Cut up

all meats and cheese into cube, then combine with olives, peppers, celery, scallions and tomatoes in bowl with pasta. Blend in Italian dressing, salt, pepper and garlic salt. Mix together well. Top off with Parmesan cheese. Serve cold.

title: creamy corn chowder
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, cook vegetables until tender.
Remove from heat.
Stir in milk.
Simmer about 10 minutes, stirring once or twice.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except last two.
Top with buttered crumbs and bake at 350 about an hour or until bubbly.

title: blackberry jam cake
directions: Cream butter. Add brown sugar, creaming until light and fluffy.
Add well beaten egg yolks. Sift soda, spices and flour together and add alternately with jam to sour milk which has been mixed together.
Flour raisins. Add to mixture. Fold in beaten egg whites. Bake in layers in 375° oven. Put together with Caramel Icing.

title: caramel corn(microwave)
directions: Combine the first four ingredients and cook on Full power for 4 minutes, stirring twice.
Remove from oven and add soda and vanilla.
Place popped corn in large grocery bag, preferably a double bag.
Pour caramel over the corn and mix with a wooden spoon to coat.
Cook on Full power 1 1/2 minutes more, shaking bag and turning it every 30 seconds.
Pour out of bag and cool.

title: chicken, water chestnuts and herb cheese triangles
directions: Cut chicken breasts into small pieces; place 1/3 of the pieces in container of electric blender; cover.
Whirl to paste-like consistency.
Remove to a medium-size bowl; repeat with remaining chicken pieces.
(Or, chicken pieces may be very finely chopped.) Add water chestnuts, cheese and salt, if using; blend thoroughly.

title: summer fresh fruit salad
directions: Scoop out watermelon, making balls.
Add to remaining fruits or whatever is in season.
Help out with canned fruits.
For a small party use a large cantaloupe or honeydew melon instead of watermelon.
If melon is placed on a platter and decorated with large leaves, it makes a beautiful table decoration.

title: horace's favorite cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together dry.
Heat deep skillet with 1/2 inch cooking oil (Should be about 400°).
Mix water (cold) with mixture until it will spoon out in thin 1/2 inch patties.
Drop in hot oil.
Cook until golden brown.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill for 2 hours before serving.
Makes 2 pies.

title: creamy vegetable-cheese soup
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons margarine in large skillet and saute onions until tender; add hot water, veggies and chicken seasoning.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce and simmer for 20 minutes or until tender.
Cool completely.
Melt remaining margarine in large pot.
Add flour and stir until smooth.
Cook stirring constantly for 1 minute. Gradually add milk; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thick and bubbly.
Stir in paprika, pepper and cheese. Gradually stir in vegetable mixture and heat until hot.

title: crunchy fudge sandwiches
directions: Combine the butterscotch morsels and the peanut butter in a large glass or microwave-safe bowl.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes; stir.
Continue microwaving in 1 minute increments until the morsels are all melted.
Stir in the Rice Krispies.
Butter an 8-inch square pan or 7 x 11-inch oblong pan.
Press half the Rice Krispies mixture into the pan and chill.
Set the remaining Rice Krispies mix aside while you make the filling.

title: windjammer
directions: Blend the first three ingredients with ice. Strain over fresh ice.
Top with 7-Up.
Spear cherry and orange and put on side of glass, plus straws.
Serve.
Makes one.

title: chiles rellenos casserole
directions: Mix beaten eggs, cream-style cottage cheese, crushed crackers, green chilies, shredded Cheddar and Monterey Jack cheese (save half of cheese to put on top).
Bake in 325° oven for 45 minutes or until inserted knife comes out clean.
Sprinkle remaining cheese over the top, return to oven to melt, 2 to 3 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 6. Note:
Could add some ground beef, cooked and drained.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Cube chicken and brown in skillet. Heat soup, water, cheese and sour cream. Add 1 tablespoon poppy seed. Pour over chicken. Pour chicken mixture into casserole dish. Crumble crackers and mix with melted butter and 1 tablespoon poppy seed. Spread over other ingredients. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: olive puffs
directions: Mix cheese and margarine.
Add other ingredients, except olives, working into stiff dough.
Pinch off small piece and roll olive inside.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes or until slightly browned.

title: zippy potatoes(microwave)
directions: Blend all ingredients in microwave-safe bowl. Microwave on High for 6 minutes; stir well. Microwave on High for 6 more minutes. (May need to adjust time more or less depending on microwave wattages.) Let stand 3 minutes.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until tender and then cube.
Place in a buttered large casserole.
Layer next 6 ingredients and top with cheese. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes until hot and bubbly and cheese melts.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Peel the cucumbers and split them lengthwise into two.
Take out the pulp and seeds.
Cut the cucumbers crosswise into 1/6-inch thin slices.
Put the cucumber slices into a bowl and add salt to it.
Mix them a little and let stand for 15 minutes.
Drain out the excess water.
Add vinegar, sugar, sesame seed, oil, Tabasco sauce and soy sauce to the cucumbers.
Toss well.
Chill and serve.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: crazy cookie creatures
directions: Freeze cookie dough for 30 minutes.
Line 3 cookie sheets with foil.
Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Cut chilled dough into 18 slices.
Dip one side of each slice in sugar; place 6 slices, sugared side up, on each foil-lined cookie cookie sheet.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Heat soups, broth and chopped up tomatoes in a saucepan.
Layer ingredients in a casserole dish as follows: Chicken, onions, Doritos, cheese and sauce. Repeat these layers and end with cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pineapple sherbet
directions: Mix all together with hand mixer.
Pour into ice cream freezer and process.

title: oatmeal fudge cookies
directions: Melt butter.
Add
sugar,
milk
and cocoa.
Boil 2 1/2 minutes.
Remove
from heat; stir in peanut butter.
Add oats, 1 cup at a time.
Drop on wax paper by spoonfuls.

title: chicken and noodles
directions: Prepare chicken.
Saute celery (cut into medium pieces), onion, green pepper and fresh or canned mushrooms (sliced) until soft.
Add cooked, cut-up chicken.
Blend in cream of chicken soup.
Add pepper and Old Bay.
Thin with a little milk if needed.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Mix eggs and sugar together and set aside.
Sift flour, soda and cinnamon together and mix in pumpkin.
Add to egg mixture. Line an 11 x 16 x 1-inch cookie sheet with waxed paper and spray with Pam.
Pour mix on waxed paper and sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Turn out on paper towel sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Roll up with paper towel.
Let cool and unroll.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix together and drop by teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet. Bake in a 400° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Frost when cool.

title: monster munchies (cookies)
directions: Preheat oven to 350° and lightly grease cookie sheets.
In a large bowl, cream butter and sugar until well blended.
Beat in egg and vanilla extract.
Slowly add flour mixing thoroughly.
Add crushed cornflakes and mix well.

title: oven-fried chicken
directions: Remove skin from chicken.
Wash chicken and pat dry.
Dip in soy sauce.
Roll in crumbs.
Place in single layer in pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix chicken, Veg-All, soup, milk and pepper.
Pour into deep dish pie crust.
Cover with another pie crust.
Bake in a 350° oven until golden brown.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch casserole dish and cook in oven on 350° for 1 hour.

title: italian beef sandwiches
directions: In skillet, bring broth, garlic, oregano and pepper to a boil.
Add green pepper.
Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered until tender, about 5 minutes.
Remove green pepper with slotted spoon; keep warm.
Return broth to boil; add beef and cover and remove from heat.
Let stand for 2 minutes or until heated through. Place beef and green pepper on buns.
Serve with broth for dipping.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Prepare cake mix.

When you remove cake from oven, while it is still hot, poke with wooden spoon handle (finger size in thickness) and pour 1 can crushed pineapple (which you have simmered together with 1 cup sugar and is still at boiling point) over cake; poke chunks of pineapple into holes in cake.

When this is thoroughly cooled, cover cake with flaked coconut and pour vanilla pudding (I make with 1 1/2 cups milk instead of 2 cups) over top of cake. Cool thoroughly; cover with 1 small container Cool Whip and top with chopped pecans.
Cool thoroughly for a few hours before cutting and serving.
Good luck.

title: aunt fannie's baked squash
directions: Wash and cut up squash.
Boil until tender.
Drain and mash. Add all ingredients to squash except the butter.
Mix well.
Pour into baking dish.
Spread rest of butter on top.
Sprinkle with some crumbs.
Bake at 375 degrees for 1 hour or until brown on top.

title: hungarian cabbage and noodles
directions: Mix salt and cabbage.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Squeeze out liquid.
In skillet, saute onion in butter until soft and translucent.
Add cabbage.
Mix well and saute about 45 minutes, stirring often.
Add sugar and pepper.
Mix well.
In another pan, cook noodles according to package directions.
Drain well and blend cabbage and noodles and serve.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: scratch 3-layer cake with caramel icing
directions: Whip butter until smooth, then alternate adding flour, sugar and egg yolks.
When flour, sugar and egg yolks have been added, put in 7-Up and then vanilla.
Add egg whites until desired smoothness.
When batter is finished, put in 3 cake pans and cook at 350° until done.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Boil first four items 5 minutes and remove from heat.
Add vanilla, peanut butter and oatmeal.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.
Allow 1 hour to harden and cool (should lose glaze).

title: spiced applesauce cake
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add molasses.
Dredge raisins, dates and walnuts in 1/2 cup flour.
Sift together remaining flour, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves and salt.
Add alternately with applesauce to creamed mixture.
Stir in raisins, dates and nuts.
Pour into 10-inch greased spring-form pan.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool 10 to 15 minutes. Remove from pan.
Frost top and sides with caramel icing.
Garnish with whole walnuts.
Makes 20 servings.

title: swiss cheese veggie dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate before serving.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In medium saucepan, melt butter.
Add sugar and cocoa; stir until well blended.
Remove from heat and set aside.

title: coconut pie
directions: Combine egg yolks, flour, sugar, butter and milk.
Cook until thick, add coconut and vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell and top with egg whites.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onions and celery in butter or margarine.
Prepare rice and broccoli according to package directions.
In a large bowl, mix all ingredients.
Spray 9 X 13 baking dish with Pam.
Add mixture to baking dish and cook for 1 hour at 350°.

title: spaghetti surprise
directions: Heat a skillet over medium-high heat, then add onions, garlic and green pepper.
Reduce heat to medium and saute until onions are melted (about 5 minutes).
Reduce heat to simmer.
Add chicken breasts, tomato paste and tomato sauce.
Simmer about 7 to 10 minutes.
Stir in spaghetti and continue to simmer until heated through (1 to 2 minutes).
Serve hot, sprinkled with low-fat or non-fat cheese.
Yields 4 servings.

title: norwegian pancakes
directions: Grease pancake griddle lightly.
Make a thin pancake, using 1 or 2 tablespoons batter.
When bubbles form, turn and brown other side.

title: hearty potato soup
directions: This soup is an inexpensive, low-fat option for a cold day.

title: seafood au gratin
directions: Be sure to remove skin and bones from fish and cut into small pieces.
For individual servings in ramekins or sea shell servers, divide the fish, seafood and mushrooms into the servers equally. Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Heat the butter in a 1 1/2-quart saucepan.
Stir until thickened into a smooth sauce.
Stir the egg yolks and cream together and add the hot sauce.
Pour the sauce over the fish.
Sprinkle with the bread crumbs, combined with the grated cheese and dot the surface with butter.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes or until bubbling hot.
Makes 4 servings.

title: hot cocoa supreme
directions: Add hot water into cocoa mix and stir.
Top with whipped cream.
Top with chocolate sprinkles and garnish with a maraschino cherry.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli 5 minutes in salted water.
Drain well.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, eggs, onions and cheese together.
Pour mixture over broccoli in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with crushed cheese crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until bubbly.

title: smothered pork chops
directions: Brown chops in skillet.
Place in casserole dish.
In skillet, heat soup and water.
Add sour cream and 1/2 onions.
Mix well and pour over chops.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Remove and sprinkle with other 1/2 onions.
Bake for 5 more minutes.

title: strawberry crepes
directions: Sift flour, salt and 2 tablespoons powdered sugar.
Beat eggs until light and then add milk and mix well.
Add butter.
Pour enough batter in pan to cover bottom.
Grease pan first.
Make sure pan is hot.

title: sliders(this one is great for kids)
directions: Soak onions in hot water until soft.
Mix hamburger, strained beef and beef broth.
Make patties the same size by using 1/4 cup meat mixture to make each patty.
Flatten to 1/4-inch and quickly fry them in oil.
Make three holes in patties while frying.
Cut hot dog rolls in half and then cut off the rounded ends.
Fry 1 teaspoon of onions under each patty as you turn them on the second side.
Slip patty into buns and add mustard, ketchup or cheese. This makes about 16 little sandwiches that are similar to the White Castle burgers you can buy in the freezer section.
These freeze well.

title: cranberry jewel salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; stir in applesauce. Gradually add to cream cheese, beating until smooth.
Chill until partially set; stir in celery.
Gently fold in cranberry cubes. Turn into mold and chill until set.
You can garnish with fresh cranberries and parsley if desired.

title: skinny lasagna
directions: Combine onion and garlic; cook until tender, adding a bit of water to prevent scorching.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, parsley, salt, pepper, oregano and thyme.
Simmer, covered, for about 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Cook lasagna noodles in boiling water for about 12 minutes.
Drain; set aside.
Cover the bottom of a baking dish with 1/4 of the sauce.
Add a layer of noodles. Top with a layer of Ricotta, Mozzarella and a bit of Parmesan. Cover with 1/4 of sauce again, repeating process until all is used.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: heavenly salad
directions: Cook egg yolks and juice until thick.
Add marshmallows and stir until melted.
Remove from heat and cool.
Add pineapple, nuts and cherries; chill.
Top with whipped cream.

title: silly carrots
directions: Dice onion, green pepper and celery.
Set aside.
Cook carrots until tender.
Drain.
Combine remaining ingredients in saucepan. Bring to a boil and reduce heat to simmer 10 minutes.
Pour over carrots.
Serve hot or cold.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix together squash, onion and butter.
Add soup and mix in crumbled cornbread.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour in casserole dish and bake at 350° until brown, 25 to 30 minutes.

title: black bean soup
directions: In 4-quart saucepan over medium heat, cook onion, garlic, cumin and pepper flakes in oil until onion is tender; remove from heat.
In electric blender, puree 2 cans beans and their liquid in batches with chicken broth; add to pot.
Stir in remaining beans, salsa and lime juice.
Heat mixture to boil; reduce heat to low. Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: taco spaghetti
directions: Place spaghetti in salted boiling water until soft.
Drain. Brown 1 pound ground beef and drain.
Mix hamburger, salsa and taco seasoning in skillet.
Let simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Mix spaghetti and meat sauce together.
When serving, add cheese and Tabasco sauce to taste.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Bake cake as directed in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch rectangular pan. When done, punch holes with fork in top of cake (do not take cake out of pan).
Prepare mixture in medium saucepan of the medium can pineapple, juice from small can of pineapple, the milk and sugar; bring to a boil, dissolving sugar.
Pour this mixture over the cake; cover.
(Cake will absorb mixture when refrigerated overnight or 4 hours.)
Top with Cool Whip and remaining pineapple.

title: chicken continental
directions: Cut chicken breasts into bite-size pieces.
Place in large skillet with margarine and mushrooms (drain juice from mushrooms). Brown chicken.
Add cream of mushroom soup and milk; simmer 25 minutes.
Bring to a boil; add precooked rice.
Cook until tender. Add Parmesan cheese for additional flavor.

title: hickory nut or walnut cake
directions: Roll nuts in part of flour.
Cream sugar and butter.
Add yolks of eggs.
Sift all dry ingredients and add mixture gradually with milk.
Add nuts.
Then add beaten egg whites.
Grease and flour pans.
Also line bottom.
Bake in moderate oven until done, about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: applesauce and cottage cheese
directions: Mix hot water and Jell-O; add thick applesauce and chill. When thickened, add remaining ingredients.
Let stand overnight and serve with lettuce.
May be placed in a jello mold.

title: peanut brittle
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, heat together sugar, corn syrup and water, stirring until sugar dissolves.
When syrup boils, blend butter/margarine.
Stir frequently.
Add peanuts when temperature is 200°.
Stir constantly to hard-crack stage, 305°.
Remove from heat; stir in soda.
Mix well.
Pour into 2 buttered cookie sheets.
Loosen from pan.
When hard, break into pieces.

title: fruit cocktail cookies
directions: * Not needed if using self-rising flour.

title: deluxe peach ice cream
directions: Combine peaches and 1 cup sugar; stir well and set aside.

title: date nut bread
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and let stand.
Cream the butter, sugar and eggs.
Add flour, vanilla and salt.
Alternate with date mixture.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into 7 ungreased juice cans and bake for one hour at 325°.
Slice very thin and spread with softened cream cheese.

title: squash pickles
directions: Soak squash in salt water 1 hour.
Drain and rinse well.
Mix with other ingredients and boil 15 minutes.
Put in jars and seal. This is great with peas!

title: sunflower seeds cookies
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients well and add egg and vanilla.
Then add flour, salt, soda and oats.
When mixed well, add seeds, folding in carefully.
Chill a bit, then drop onto cookie sheet. Gently flatten out a bit with fingertips.
Bake at 350° for about ten minutes or until light brown.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: healthy oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream the
margarine and brown sugar in a large bowl.
Add vanilla and salt and beat well.
In a separate bowl, thoroughly combine flour, baking powder, wheat germ and rolled oats.
Blend dry ingredients into margarine mixture, adding a tablespoon or more of water if necessary to hold mixture together.
Drop dough by tablespoon onto greased cookie sheet. Flatten lightly.
Bake until golden, 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.
Contains 1 gr saturated fat.

title: banana split cake i
directions: Mix one stick margarine with graham cracker crumbs.
Pat into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Beat eggs, 2 stick margarine and powdered sugar for 15 minutes.
Spread over crust.
Cover with bananas. Spread pineapple over top.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with cherries and chopped nuts.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: salmon dip for vegetables
directions: Combine; chill and serve with assorted fresh vegetables.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Beat eggs; add cottage cheese, broccoli and onion.
Add corn meal and melted butter.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until brown.

title: rocky road s'mores bars
directions: Beat margarine and sugar well.
Add combined flour and crumbs. Mix well.
Press into bottom of greased 9-inch square pan. Top with marshmallows, chips and nuts.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes until lightly browned.

title: spicy cheeseburger soup
directions: In a large saucepan, combine the first 8 ingredients. Bring to a boil. Reduce the heat, cover and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Stir in beef and 2 cups milk; heat through. Combine flour and remaining milk until smooth. Gradually stir into soup. Bring to a boil. Cook and stir for 2 minutes or until thickened and bubbly. Reduce heat. Stir in cheese until melted. Top with cooked bacon just before serving. Makes about 2 quarts.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix cake mix, sugar and oil together; add eggs.
Mix well. Add sour cream, vanilla, pecans and coconut.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Mix powdered sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over bottom of pan.
Pour in 1/2 of mixture batter, then sprinkle the cinnamon and brown sugar over the batter, then cover with the remaining batter.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.
Let cool in pan 15 minutes before removing from pan.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add beaten egg.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to butter mixture alternately with molasses. Beat well.
Add hot water last.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Set on rack to cool.
While still warm, use spatula and spread with molasses.
Sprinkle with granulated sugar.
Serve warm with lemon sauce, whipped cream or warm applesauce which is our favorite.

title: fruit salad
directions: Stir all ingredients together to chill.

title: old sugar cookies
directions: Cream Butter, oil, and both Sugars, Vanilla and Eggs.

title: saucy pork chops
directions: In skillet, brown chops on both sides; season with salt and pepper.
Top chops with onion slices.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift
together flour, cinnamon, baking powder and salt. In large
mixer
bowl, beat sugar and salad oil for 2 minutes. Beat in	eggs,
one
at	a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Add flour mixture, beating just until blended.
Mix in carrots and pecans.

title: pralines
directions: Combine pecan halves, sugars and butter in a saucepan.
Bring the milk to a boil and pour over the pecan mixture.
Place over medium heat and cook for 7 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat and add the vanilla.
Beat for 30 seconds.
Drop by tablespoons onto waxed paper.
Makes 24 pralines.

title: chicken chili
directions: Saute chicken, onion, garlic and peppers in oil.
Add tomatoes, broth, chili powder, cumin, curry powder, oregano and allspice.
Cook 20 minutes.
Add zucchini, kidney beans, lemon juice and parsley.
Simmer 10 minutes, uncovered.
Adjust seasonings.
Serve over white or brown rice.
Garnish with nonfat plain yogurt, chopped scallions and grated Cheddar cheese.

title: dump cake
directions: Use a 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Cover bottom of pan with any fruit. Dump a box of cake mix in dry form on top of fruit mixture. Melt 1 stick butter and drizzle over cake mix. Bake 1 hour at 350°. Serve hot or cold with whip cream, if desired.

title: stuffed celery
directions: Wash celery and drain.
Cut into desired lengths.
Mix cheeses, pepper and chili powder.
Blend well.
Stuff celery with mix.
Serve with a zip!

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Press into a 2-quart casserole dish. Bake at 350° until brown.
Let cool.

title: chocolate-caramel bars
directions: Melt 1 cup chocolate chips with 1 tablespoon shortening in double boiler over hot water; blend well.
Spread in foil-lined 8-inch square dish.
Chill until firm.
Melt caramels with butter and 2 tablespoons water in double boiler over hot water.
Stir in peanuts.
Spread over chocolate layer.
Chill for 15 minutes or until partially set.
Melt remaining 1 cup chocolate and 1 tablespoon shortening in double boiler over hot water.
Spread over caramel layer.
Chill until firm.
Cut into 1 x 2-inch bars. Store, covered, in refrigerator.
Yield: 1 1/2 pounds.

title: corn muffin casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in greased 8 x 8-inch casserole for 50 minutes at 350°.
Pull rack out and sprinkle 4 ounces of grated cheese on top.
Remove from oven immediately, cheese should be melting.

title: mustard sauce
directions: Stir together all ingredients.
Makes about 1/2 cup.

title: old-fashioned chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook chicken until done. Cool and pick off bone; set aside. Cook noodles as directed and a little longer; do not pour off liquid. Add chicken and strained chicken broth. Add a little margarine and salt and pepper to taste.

title: bleu cheese baked potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Prick the potatoes all over.
Bake 1 1/4 hours or until done.
Melt butter; add finely minced garlic and cook over very low heat for 1 1/2 minutes.
Cool potatoes slightly.
Cut a lengthwise slit in top of each and remove pulp. Mash the potatoes and add garlic, butter, sour cream, cheese, parsley, one tablespoon chives, salt and pepper.
Stuff into potato skins and sprinkle tops with paprika.
Bake 15 minutes. Sprinkle with remaining chives.

title: quick spaghetti
directions: Saute celery, pepper and onions.
Saute hamburger also.
Cook spaghetti until tender.
Drain.
Add spaghetti to sauteed vegetables and spaghetti with hamburger.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Prepare elbow macaroni according to package directions; drain. Melt butter in medium saucepan.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper. Blend in milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly.
Combine macaroni and sauce mixture; mix well.
Stir in cheese.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Dot with butter. Bake in a 350° oven until hot, 20 to 25 minutes.
If desired, broil until lightly browned before serving.
Yields 4 servings.

title: lemon apricot pound cake
directions: Mix cake mix, sugar, oil and nectar.
Next, add one egg at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add butter flavor.
Beat about 2 minutes.
Bake in tube pan for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: ground beef and rice
directions: Cook onion and pepper in oil slow but not brown.
Blend cornstarch with small amount of chicken broth.
Add remaining broth and soy sauce.
Stir chicken and broth in.
Add tomatoes and heat.
Serve over rice.

title: grape juice
directions: In a quart jar, put washed purple grapes with seeds. Add sugar. Fill jar with boiling water. Put on jar lids and rings. Boil in canner for 5 minutes to seal. Juice turns purple as it sets. Strain when ready to drink.

title: rotel potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes with skin on.
Slice and put in a casserole dish. Saut bell pepper, onion and mushrooms.

title: lattice top chicken
directions: Combine soup, salt, milk, chicken, vegetables, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 can French fried onions.
Place in an 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 20 minutes.
Unwrap crescent rolls; separate into two rectangles.
Press together perforated cuts and cut into 3 strips.
Place strips on casserole to form lattice top.
Bake, uncovered, 15 minutes longer.
Top with remaining cheese and onions; bake, uncovered, 3 to 5 minutes or until onions are golden brown.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: shrimp fried rice
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Chop.
Beat eggs with a little salt and fry.
Take out and chop the eggs.
Fry finely chopped onion with chicken bouillon cube.
When clear, add rice, finely chopped celery, bell pepper, egg, bacon and shrimp.
Season with soy sauce.

title: granny's cornbread
directions: Mix flour, cornmeal, milk, egg, salt and baking powder thoroughly. Pour into a greased pan at 425° until light brown.

title: fresh apple nut cake
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Beat eggs, oil and sugar together.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Let cake cool in pan.
Frost, if desired.

title: orange salad
directions: Let Jell-O, boiling water and sherbet stand until slightly jelled.
Add Cool Whip and mix until fluffy.
Add oranges or crushed pineapple.

title: old fashioned chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa well.
Add 2 cups milk and heat.
In a bowl mix egg yolks, flour, salt and 1/2 cup milk.
Beat egg mixture until smooth and add to hot mixture.
Cook, stirring until thickened.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and butter.
Pour into baked pie shell(s).
Beat egg whites, add 8 tablespoons of sugar and spread on top of pie.
Brown in a moderate oven.

title: turkey noodle stir-fry
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Set aside. Brown turkey; set aside.
Add small amount of water to pan and saute peppers, onions and mushrooms.
Add noodles and olives until heated through.
Add turkey and Italian dressing; cook over low heat for 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove from heat; add lemon pepper and serve hot.
